(190, '2026-03-19 12:57:28', 1, NULL, 'template-team', NULL, 'FUR GELJE SHERPA', 'President', '<p>Fur Gelje Sherpa is a respected leader in Nepal\'s mountaineering and mountain tourism, deeply rooted in the Himalayan Solukhumbu region which is the Sherpa heartland for high-altitude expeditions. Raised there, he built a lifelong bond with the Himalayas, fueling over 44 years in tourism, trekking, expeditions, and hospitality in the Everest area. He has steadily grown mountain tourism while creating lasting jobs for local communities.<br>As an accomplished mountaineer, he has summited many 6,000- and 7,000-meter peaks.</p>\r\n<p>His direct high-altitude experience provides real insights into expedition challenges, safety,<br>logistics, and climber needs. This mix of on-the-ground skills and business leadership has<br>made him a trusted voice in Nepal\'s adventure tourism.<br>In August 2025, he won election as President of the Nepal Mountaineering Association<br>(NMA),Nepal\'s top mountaineering body with 342 votes, starting in September. He prioritizes<br>better professional training via basic and advanced climbing courses, guide certifications, and<br>rescue programs. At NMA\'s 52nd anniversary, he outlined expanding these and creating an<br>Adventure Tourism University to train local youth, keep skilled jobs in Nepal, and raise<br>Nepal\'s global profile for safe mountain tourism.<br>His NMA term has boosted ties with global groups like the Union of Asian Alpine Associations<br>and Korean Alpine Federation, advancing teamwork and responsible practices. He shows<br>strong community care by donating NPR 2 million personally to NMA\'s welfare fund for<br>educating children of mountain workers killed on the job.<br>Nationally honored for his vision, he links with key players like Nepal Tourism Board and<br>Nepal Airlines. As NMA President (2025–2028) and Summit 8000 President, his vast experience<br>shapes the company\'s focus on safety, professionalism, community respect, and true<br>Himalayan values.</p>', 'President', 'fur-gelje-sherpa', '1773331448716', 35, NULL, 0, 22, '1773331448.png', 'president-sir-x4jZg.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 112, 'en', '2026-03-13 01:49:08', '2026-04-17 13:23:47'),
(191, '2026-03-31 04:46:48', NULL, NULL, 'template-team', NULL, 'Pasang Sherpa', 'CEO/MD', '<div><span>Amid the towering shadows of the Himalayas, in a remote village of the Solukhumbu</span><br><span>district, on December 25, 1978, Pasang Sherpa was born. For Pasang, the mountains</span><br><span>were never just giant scenery but something deep and spiritual that held utmost</span><br><span>respect.</span></div>\r\n<div><br><span>Life in the highlands was rugged and unforgiving, far from the dreams that stirred</span><br><span>within him. In 1995, armed with little more than courage and ambition, Pasang left his</span><br><span>village for Kathmandu, Nepal’s bustling capital. Determined to rise beyond</span><br><span>circumstance, he dedicated himself to education, completing his SLC examination in</span><br><span>1996. That very year, he began his journey in the mountains as a porter, taking his first</span><br><span>steps on paths that would define his future.</span></div>\r\n<div><br><span>While carrying loads across Himalayan trails, he carried ambitions just as heavy.</span><br><span>Beginning his journey as a porter, Pasang’s dedication, discipline, and strong work ethic</span><br><span>soon set him apart, allowing him to progress quickly into the role of a trusted trekking</span><br><span>guide, leading visitors through the mountains he knew so well. He balanced demanding fieldwork with continued studies and successfully completed his high school education.</span></div>\r\n<div><br><span>These early experiences shaped his vision, and in 2001, alongside completing his</span><br><span>With an undergraduate degree in Business Studies, he founded his own trekking company</span><br><span>, transforming hands-on mountain experience into a purpose-driven enterprise.</span></div>\r\n<div><br><span>With age came a deeper connection to wildlife, nature, and the untamed beauty of the</span><br><span>mountains. His hunger for learning never faded. He fulfilled a lifelong goal by</span><br><span>completing a Master’s in Business Studies, then expanded his intellectual horizon</span><br><span>toward global affairs and governance. This journey culminated in 2025, when he</span><br><span>earned a second Master’s degree(an MPS in Political Science), marking the achievement</span><br><span>of a double Master’s.</span></div>\r\n<div><span>Rooted in mountain wisdom and guided by modern leadership, Pasang dedicated years of</span><br><span>service to Nepal’s tourism institutions. A licensed tourist guide of Nepal, he served as</span><br><span>Secretary of the Trekking Agencies’ Association of Nepal (TAAN) from 2013 to 2025, and as</span><br><span>General Secretary of the Sherpa Tourism Entrepreneurs Association of Nepal (STEAN) from</span><br><span>2022 to 2025. Today, he continues to lead as President of STEAN and shape the future of</span><br><span>sustainable mountain tourism.</span></div>\r\n<div><br><span>Having journeyed across 32 countries, Pasang Sherpa has left his footprints far beyond the</span><br><span>Himalayas. His mountaineering accomplishments include ascents of Mera Peak and</span><br><span>Lobuche Peak, and Mount Kilimanjaro (one of the Seven Summits), which he summited on</span><br><span>his 41st birthday, December 25, 2019. Now serving as one of the Managing Directors of</span><br><span>Summit 8000, his story stands as living proof that the highest summits are not only</span><br><span>conquered with ropes and ice axes, but with vision, resilience, and the courage to chase</span><br><span>dreams.</span></div>\r\n<div><br><span>Pasang Sherpa’s story is one of quiet determination and extraordinary vision. From</span><br><span>carrying loads to carrying responsibility, his journey proves that with hard work, humility,</span><br><span>and purpose, even the most distant dreams can stand firmly at the summit.</span></div>', NULL, 'pasang-sherpa', '1773331960883', 35, NULL, 0, 23, '1773331960.jpg', 'pasang-sherpa-VabIJ.jpg', NULL, 'Pasang Sherpa | CEO & Leader at Summit 8000 Himalayan Expeditions', 'Learn about Pasang Sherpa, the CEO of Summit 8000, a Sherpa‑led Himalayan expedition company guiding climbers on Nepal’s highest peaks with expertise, safety, and responsibility.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 104, 'en', '2026-03-13 01:57:40', '2026-04-17 10:04:41'),
(192, '2026-03-31 05:18:34', NULL, NULL, 'single', NULL, 'Temba Tsheri Sherpa', 'Executive Director', '<div><span>Born on May 9, 1985, Temba Tsheri Sherpa is a famous Nepalese climber, businessman, and</span><br><span>a leader in mountain tourism. He became known worldwide on May 23, 2001, when he</span><br><span>reached the summit of Mount Everest at the age of 16. At that time, he was the youngest</span><br><span>person in the world to reach the top-a record confirmed by Guinness World Records.</span></div>\r\n<div><br><span>Although Jordan Romero later broke this world record in 2010 at age 13, Temba remains the</span><br><span>youngest Nepalese climber to ever stand on the world’s highest peak. This title is now almost</span><br><span>permanent because Nepal’s government no longer gives climbing permits to anyone under</span><br><span>16. Beyond his early records, he has spent his career in the trekking and guiding industry,</span><br><span>using his strength and deep knowledge to help shape the future of mountain climbing in</span><br><span>Nepal.</span></div>\r\n<div><br><span>Growing up in the remote village of Tashi Nam in the Dolakha region, Temba knew the high</span><br><span>Himalayas not just as beautiful peaks, but as the center of daily life. Born into a close-knit</span><br><span>Sherpa family, he was raised by his father, Chhauwa Sherpa, who worked as a cook on</span><br><span>trekking trips, and his mother, Lakpa Diki Sherpa, who worked hard on the family farm and</span><br><span>at home. </span></div>\r\n<div><span></span></div>\r\n<div><span>Along with his two brothers, young Temba balanced the chores of childhood, such</span><br><span>as herding cattle and walking an hour to school each morning. These simple routines, mixed</span><br><span>with hard work and big dreams, gave him the inner strength and a deep bond with the</span><br><span>mountains that would later lead him to greatness.</span></div>\r\n<div><br><span>In 1998, at just 13 years old, Temba left his village for Kathmandu to start fifth grade at</span><br><span>Pashupati Mitra Secondary School. Drawn to the mountains he loved, he began formal</span><br><span>training at age 13, becoming the youngest person to finish the basic climbing course at the</span><br><span>Nepal Mountaineering Association. He was also a great student, earning a full scholarship to</span><br><span>the well-known Siddhartha Vanasthali School. Later, another scholarship allowed him to</span><br><span>study at Wuhan University in China, where he earned a degree in Business Administration,</span><br><span>successfully combining his mountain roots with professional skills.</span></div>\r\n<div><span></span></div>\r\n<div><span>Temba’s journey to the top of the world included both painful setbacks and great success. In</span><br><span>April 2000, he tried his first big climb up the southern side of Everest. After months of hard</span><br><span>training, he got incredibly close to the top(only 22 meters away)before terrible weather and</span><br><span>tiredness forced him to turn back. The way down was even harder, as severe frostbite</span><br><span>caused him to lose five of his fingers. </span></div>\r\n<div><span></span></div>\r\n<div><span>For most people, such a physical and emotional blow</span><br><span>would end their dream, but for the 15-year-old Sherpa, it only made him more determined.</span><br><span>Just one year later, Temba returned to the mountain and reached the summit on May 23,</span><br><span>2001, via the North Ridge in Tibet. This feat turned his past pain into a historic victory of</span><br><span>pure willpower.</span></div>\r\n<div><br><span>After his historic climb, Temba became a global spokesperson for Himalayan climbing and</span><br><span>tourism. Speaking Nepali, Chinese, English, and Hindi, he traveled the world to connect</span><br><span>different cultures and represent Nepal’s climbers. These experiences, along with his</span><br><span>mountain wisdom, helped him build a successful career. More than just leading adventures,</span><br><span>Temba works hard to protect Sherpa traditions, helping every climber feel the deep cultural</span><br><span>and spiritual connection his people have with the mountains.</span></div>\r\n<div><br><span>Throughout his career, Temba has received many high honors for his work. Guinness World</span><br><span>Records recognized him as the youngest Everest climber of his time, and in 2011, the</span><br><span>The government named him a Goodwill Ambassador for Nepal Tourism Year. He has also</span><br><span>received important national awards like the Ganesh Man Prativa Puraskar, the Sundere</span><br><span>Sherpa Rastriya Prativa Puraskar, and the TAAN Everest International Award. </span></div>\r\n<div><span>Today, he</span><br><span>continues to lead the industry as the ED of Summit8000, following his previous work with</span><br><span>Dreamers Destination and the Sherpa Khangri Group. His story remains a powerful example</span><br><span>of courage and humility, inspiring people everywhere to chase their dreams.</span></div>', NULL, 'temba-tsheri-sherpa', '1773332053715', 35, NULL, 0, 24, '1773332053.jpg', 'temba-sherpa-FyvkP.jpg', NULL, 'Temba Tsheri Sherpa – Executive Director of The Summit 8000', 'Discover the inspiring journey of Temba Tsheri Sherpa, Executive Director of The Summit 8000, and learn how he leads one of Nepal’s premier mountaineering organizations.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 111, 'en', '2026-03-13 01:59:13', '2026-04-17 15:47:16'),
(193, '2026-03-31 05:24:58', NULL, NULL, 'single', NULL, 'Zhiming Gan', 'Executive Director', '<div><span>Zhiming Gan is a leading Chinese tourism entrepreneur and one of the Executive Directors at</span><br><span>Summit 8000. He is widely known for his strong efforts in promoting Nepal as a top destination</span><br><span>for adventure and mountain tourism among Chinese travelers. As a Chinese citizen, he has</span><br><span>lived and worked in Nepal for more than 15 years, making the country feel like a second home</span><br><span>while playing a key role in its tourism development.</span></div>\r\n<div><br><span>Over the years, Zhiming has fully immersed himself in Nepal\'s tourism industry. He has gained</span><br><span>real-world experience in organizing treks, coordinating expeditions, marketing destinations,</span><br><span>and building cross-border travel links. His extended time in Nepal has given him a profound</span><br><span>grasp of its operational side, along with its unique cultural values, warm hospitality traditions,</span><br><span>and stunning natural heritage. This insider knowledge lets him introduce Nepal to Chinese</span><br><span>audiences with true authenticity, clear messaging, and full confidence.</span></div>\r\n<div><span>He stands out especiallyfor his outstanding work during the COVID-19 pandemic, when worldwide tourism ground to a halt. In those tough times, Zhiming actively kept promoting Nepal to Chinese travelers and </span><span>tourism partners, sustaining interest and connections when most global efforts paused.</span></div>\r\n<div><br><span>In his role as Managing Director of Summit 8000, Zhiming is essential for tapping into and</span><br><span>growing the massive Chinese tourism market. With his fluency in Chinese, deep cultural</span><br><span>insights, and wide professional network, he effectively links Nepal\'s high-altitude adventures</span><br><span>with one of the world\'s biggest groups of outbound travelers, Chinese climbers, trekkers, and</span><br><span>adventure seekers wanting genuine Himalayan experiences. He acts as a key bridge between</span><br><span>these worlds.</span></div>\r\n<div><span>Zhiming’s career beautifully blends entrepreneurial energy, seamless cultural integration, and</span><br><span>unwavering commitment to tourism progress. His ongoing work strengthens tourism bonds</span><br><span>between Nepal and China, supports sustainable growth, encourages cross-cultural exchanges,</span><br><span>and helps expand Summit 8000\'s presence in the global mountaineering and trekking scene.</span></div>', NULL, 'zhiming-gan', '1773332235630', 35, NULL, 0, 25, NULL, 'zhiming-gan-aCaOy.webp', NULL, 'Zhiming Gan – Executive Director of The Summit 8000', 'Learn about Zhiming Gan, Executive Director of The Summit 8000, and his leadership role in guiding Nepal’s premier mountaineering organization to success.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 79, 'en', '2026-03-13 02:02:15', '2026-04-17 10:21:40'),
(194, '2026-03-31 05:26:25', NULL, NULL, 'single', NULL, 'Phur Lhakpa Sherpa', 'Executive Director', '<div><span>Phur Lhakpa Sherpa is a veteran mountaineer and tourism entrepreneur with nearly 20</span><br><span>years in international adventure travel. He serves as an Executive Director at Summit 8000,</span><br><span>linking global travelers, especially Europeans, with real Himalayan expeditions and treks.</span><br><span>From Nepal\'s Himalayan region and now based in Germany, he leads the company\'s</span><br><span>international operations, building strong partnerships, client ties, and market growth across</span><br><span>Europe and further afield.</span></div>\r\n<div><br><span>Fluent in English, Japanese, German, and Hindi, he excels at cross-cultural communication</span><br><span>with diverse clients. His wide travels cover Japan, the US, most European countries, and Asian</span><br><span>hubs like Hong Kong, Singapore, Qatar, Dubai, and Malaysia. This global experience sharpens</span><br><span>his knowledge of international tourism standards, safety needs, and client service, all woven</span><br><span>into Summit 8000\'s work.</span></div>\r\n<div><span>He has explored nearly all major tourist areas in Nepal, mastering its trekking routes,</span><br><span>expedition zones, and cultural sites. This firsthand expertise lets him create and promote</span><br><span>Himalayan trips with true authenticity and practical know-how.</span></div>\r\n<div><br><span>As an accomplished high-altitude climber, Phur Lhakpa has summited key peaks: Lobuche</span><br><span>East (6,119 m), Island Peak/Imja Tse (6,189 m), Mera Peak (6,476 m), Pisang Peak (6,091 m),</span><br><span>and Baruntse (7,129 m). He has also crossed tough high passes like Amphu Lapcha and Tashi</span><br><span>Lapcha, proving his technical skills in challenging mountain terrain.</span></div>\r\n<div><br><span>This unique mix of climbing success, worldwide exposure, and tourism leadership lets him</span><br><span>view expeditions from both climber and organizer angles. As Summit 8000\'s global face, he</span><br><span>promotes Nepal\'s mountain heritage with professionalism, cultural flexibility, and real</span><br><span>passion.</span></div>', NULL, 'phur-lhakpa-sherpa', '1773332335547', 35, NULL, 0, 26, '1773332335.jpg', 'phur-lakpa-sherpa-i5iHS.jpg', NULL, 'Phur Lhakpa Sherpa – Executive Director of The Summit 8000', 'Discover Phur Lhakpa Sherpa, Executive Director of The Summit 8000, and his leadership in driving one of Nepal’s top mountaineering organizations to new heights.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 85, 'en', '2026-03-13 02:03:55', '2026-04-17 10:04:48'),
(195, '2026-03-12 10:18:14', 1, NULL, 'single', NULL, 'Kamisinge Syanba Tamang', 'Mountain Guide', '<p data-start=\"400\" data-end=\"564\">Meet the expert climbing and trekking guides of Summit 8000 Pvt. Ltd., experienced Himalayan professionals ensuring safe and successful expeditions.</p>', 'Meet the expert climbing and trekking guides of Summit 8000 Pvt. Ltd., experienced Himalayan professionals ensuring safe and successful expeditions.', 'kamisinge-syanba-tamang', '1773333146639', 46, NULL, 0, 27, '1773333146.jpg', '', NULL, 'Experienced Peak Climbing Guides in Nepal | Summit 8000', 'Meet the expert climbing and trekking guides of Summit 8000 Pvt. Ltd., experienced Himalayan professionals ensuring safe and successful expeditions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', NULL, 'en', '2026-03-13 02:17:26', '2026-03-13 02:18:43'),
(196, '2026-04-17 10:42:51', NULL, 'Admin', 'template-blogs', NULL, 'Top 10 Best Peak Climbing in Nepal', '2026/02/04', '<div bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:16,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:111,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:746}\"><span bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:16,&quot;w&quot;:540,&quot;h&quot;:110,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:746}\">Are you planning an expedition in Nepal and wondering which peaks are the best to climb? You’ve come to the right place! In this blog, we’ll guide you through each of the top NMA peaks, helping you choose your adventure wisely and giving you all the tips you need to plan a safe and unforgettable journey. Let’s get started!</span></div>\r\n<h2 bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:147,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:33,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:877}\"><span bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:147,&quot;w&quot;:424,&quot;h&quot;:32,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:877}\">Mera Peak (6,476 m) – Everest Region</span></h2>\r\n<div bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:201,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:134,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:931}\"><span bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:201,&quot;w&quot;:535,&quot;h&quot;:132,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:931}\"><span style=\"color: #236fa1;\" bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:201,&quot;w&quot;:73,&quot;h&quot;:21,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:931}\"><a href=\"/trip/mera-peak-climbing\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color: #236fa1;\" bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:201,&quot;w&quot;:73,&quot;h&quot;:21,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:931}\">Mera Peak</a></span> is often called the highest “trekking peak” in Nepal, and for good reason. The climb offers stunning views of Everest, Lhotse, and Cho Oyu. It’s moderately challenging and requires basic mountaineering skills, making it perfect for first-time climbers who want a taste of the high Himalayas. The approach itself passes through Sherpa villages, glacial rivers, and dramatic landscapes.</span></div>\r\n<h2 bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:355,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:67,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1085}\"><span bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:355,&quot;w&quot;:478,&quot;h&quot;:65,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1085}\">Island Peak / Imja Tse (6,189 m) – Khumbu Region</span></h2>\r\n<div bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:442,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:111,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1172}\"><span bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:442,&quot;w&quot;:541,&quot;h&quot;:110,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1172}\"><span style=\"color: #236fa1;\" bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:442,&quot;w&quot;:83,&quot;h&quot;:21,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1172}\"><a href=\"/trip/island-peak-climbing\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color: #236fa1;\" bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:442,&quot;w&quot;:78,&quot;h&quot;:21,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1172}\">Island Peak</a> </span>is a favorite among mountaineers heading to Everest Base Camp. It’s known for its striking pyramid shape and breathtaking panoramas. Climbers enjoy a mix of trekking and light technical climbing, including ice and rock sections. The views from the summit of Everest, Lhotse, and Ama Dablam are unforgettable a reward for all the effort!</span></div>\r\n<h2 bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:574,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:33,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1304}\"><span bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:574,&quot;w&quot;:468,&quot;h&quot;:32,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1304}\">Lobuche East (6,119 m) – Khumbu Region</span></h2>\r\n<div bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:628,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:89,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1358}\"><span bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:628,&quot;w&quot;:544,&quot;h&quot;:88,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1358}\"><span style=\"color: #236fa1;\" bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:628,&quot;w&quot;:97,&quot;h&quot;:21,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1358}\"><a href=\"/trip/lobuche-peak-climbing\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color: #236fa1;\" bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:628,&quot;w&quot;:93,&quot;h&quot;:21,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1358}\">Lobuche East</a> </span>is a thrilling peak with a short but steep climb that challenges your balance and stamina. It’s less crowded than Mera and Island Peak, which makes it a peaceful yet rewarding climb. From the summit, you’ll see some of the most iconic Himalayan peaks up close a photographer’s dream!</span></div>\r\n<h2 bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:737,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:33,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1467}\"><span bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:737,&quot;w&quot;:408,&quot;h&quot;:32,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1467}\">Baruntse (7,129 m) – Makalu Region</span></h2>\r\n<div bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:791,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:111,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1521}\"><span bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:791,&quot;w&quot;:545,&quot;h&quot;:110,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1521}\"><span style=\"color: #236fa1;\" bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:791,&quot;w&quot;:65,&quot;h&quot;:21,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1521}\"><a href=\"/trip/baruntse-expedition-in-nepal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color: #236fa1;\" bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:791,&quot;w&quot;:65,&quot;h&quot;:21,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1521}\">Baruntse </a></span>is a higher-altitude NMA peak and demands more technical skill. It’s often recommended for climbers who want to bridge the gap between trekking peaks and big Himalayan expeditions. The ascent passes through stunning glaciers and offers views of Makalu, the fifth-highest mountain in the world.</span></div>\r\n<h2 bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:922,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:33,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1652}\"><span bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:922,&quot;w&quot;:479,&quot;h&quot;:32,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1652}\">Chulu West (6,419 m) – Annapurna Region</span></h2>\r\n<div bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:976,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:111,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1706}\"><span bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:976,&quot;w&quot;:544,&quot;h&quot;:110,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1706}\"><a href=\"/trip/chulu-west-peak-climbing\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:976,&quot;w&quot;:84,&quot;h&quot;:21,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1706}\"><span style=\"color: #236fa1;\" bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:976,&quot;w&quot;:80,&quot;h&quot;:21,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1706}\">Chulu West</span> </a>is a popular peak in the Annapurna region, offering a moderate climb with a mix of rock and snow. Its approach takes you through traditional villages and lush valleys, giving you a full taste of Nepalese culture. The summit rewards you with panoramic views of Annapurna I, Dhaulagiri, and the surrounding peaks.</span></div>\r\n<h2 bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1108,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:33,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1838}\"><span bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1108,&quot;w&quot;:485,&quot;h&quot;:32,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1838}\">Pisang Peak (6,091 m) – Annapurna Region</span></h2>\r\n<div bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1161,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:89,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1891}\"><span bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1161,&quot;w&quot;:532,&quot;h&quot;:88,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1891}\">Pisang Peak is smaller but no less exciting. It’s ideal for climbers with some prior experience and looking for a shorter expedition. The peak provides an excellent opportunity to practice technical climbing skills while enjoying the spectacular Annapurna scenery.</span></div>\r\n<h2 bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1271,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:33,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2001}\"><span bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1271,&quot;w&quot;:468,&quot;h&quot;:32,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2001}\">Chulu East (6,584 m) – Annapurna Region</span></h2>\r\n<div bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1324,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:89,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2054}\"><span bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1324,&quot;w&quot;:545,&quot;h&quot;:88,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2054}\"><span style=\"color: #236fa1;\" bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1324,&quot;w&quot;:78,&quot;h&quot;:21,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2054}\"><a href=\"/trip/chulu-east-peak-climbing-in-nepal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color: #236fa1;\" bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1324,&quot;w&quot;:73,&quot;h&quot;:21,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2054}\">Chulu East</a> </span>is slightly taller than Chulu West and a bit more technical. The climb includes mixed snow and rock sections, and the summit views are simply spectacular. It’s a quieter peak, perfect for climbers who enjoy solitude and serene mountain landscapes.</span></div>\r\n<h2 bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1434,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:33,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2164}\"><span bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1434,&quot;w&quot;:440,&quot;h&quot;:32,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2164}\">Tent Peak (5,663 m) – Langtang Region</span></h2>\r\n<div bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1487,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:89,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2217}\"><span bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1487,&quot;w&quot;:540,&quot;h&quot;:88,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2217}\"><span style=\"color: #236fa1;\" bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1487,&quot;w&quot;:66,&quot;h&quot;:21,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2217}\"><a href=\"/trip/tent-peak-climbing-in-nepal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color: #236fa1;\" bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1487,&quot;w&quot;:66,&quot;h&quot;:21,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2217}\">Tent Peak</a></span> is an approachable peak in the Langtang region, great for beginners. It has a gentler climb, but don’t be fooled, the scenery is anything but mild. You’ll enjoy panoramic vistas of Langtang Lirung and the surrounding Himalayan range.</span></div>\r\n<h2 bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1597,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:33,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2327}\"><span bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1597,&quot;w&quot;:436,&quot;h&quot;:32,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2327}\">Yala Peak (5,500 m) – Langtang Region</span></h2>\r\n<div bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1650,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:89,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2380}\"><span bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1650,&quot;w&quot;:549,&quot;h&quot;:88,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2380}\">Yala Peak is one of the more accessible NMA peaks, making it perfect for first-timers who want to experience high-altitude climbing. The trek to the base and the summit is filled with serene landscapes, glacial views, and small alpine lakes, making it both peaceful and rewarding.</span></div>\r\n<h2 bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1760,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:33,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2490}\"><span bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1760,&quot;w&quot;:440,&quot;h&quot;:32,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2490}\">Kang Guru (6,981 m) – Manaslu Region</span></h2>\r\n<div bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1813,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:89,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2543}\"><span bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1813,&quot;w&quot;:544,&quot;h&quot;:88,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2543}\">Kang Guru is challenging and majestic, offering a serious adventure for climbers ready to step up from easier peaks. The peak is less crowded, so you get a more remote Himalayan experience. From the summit, the views of the Manaslu range and surrounding valleys are absolutely unforgettable.</span></div>\r\n<div bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1903,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:22,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2633}\"><span bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1903,&quot;w&quot;:0,&quot;h&quot;:21,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2633}\"></span></div>\r\n<div bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1925,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:22,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2655}\"><strong bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1925,&quot;w&quot;:142,&quot;h&quot;:21,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2655}\">Read Related Posts</strong></div>\r\n<div bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1925,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:22,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2655}\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #236fa1;\"><a href=\"/blogs/how-to-prepare-for-the-baruntse-expedition-in-nepal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color: #236fa1;\">How to Prepare for the Baruntse Expedition in Nepal</a></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1947,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:22,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2677}\"><span style=\"color: #236fa1;\" bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1947,&quot;w&quot;:321,&quot;h&quot;:21,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2677}\"><a href=\"/blogs/top-8-highest-8000m-peaks-to-climb-in-nepal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color: #236fa1;\" bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1947,&quot;w&quot;:321,&quot;h&quot;:21,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2677}\">Top 8 Highest 8000m Peaks to Climb in Nepal</a></span></div>\r\n<div bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:16,&quot;y&quot;:1947,&quot;w&quot;:550,&quot;h&quot;:22,&quot;abs_x&quot;:440,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2677}\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #236fa1;\"><a href=\"/blogs/when-is-the-best-time-for-baruntse-expedition-season-guide\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color: #236fa1;\">When is the Best Time for Baruntse Expedition? (Season Guide)</a></span><span style=\"color: #236fa1;\"></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #236fa1;\"><a href=\"/blogs/baruntse-expedition-cost\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color: #236fa1;\">Baruntse Expedition Cost</a></span></p>\r\n</div>', 'Dreaming of Himalayan adventures? Nepal’s NMA peaks are your perfect playground! From beginner-friendly climbs like Tent Peak and Yala Peak to more challenging summits like Baruntse and Kang Guru, these top 10 peaks offer jaw-dropping views, charming villages, and a taste of true Himalayan magic. Whether it’s your first climb or your fifth, each peak promises an unforgettable mix of adventure, culture, and epic scenery all without the extreme stress of the 8000m giants. Lace up your boots, grab your gear, and get ready to make mountain memories that last a lifetime!', 'top-10-best-peak-climbing-in-nepal', '1773397579934', 33, NULL, 0, 28, NULL, 'top-of-best-peak-climbing-in-nepal-ov386.jpg', NULL, 'Top 10 Best Peaks to Climb in Nepal| NMA Mountain Adventures', 'Discover the top 10 NMA peaks in Nepal! From beginner-friendly climbs to thrilling summits, plan your Himalayan adventure with epic views and safe trekking.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 104, 'en', '2026-03-13 20:11:19', '2026-04-17 16:10:32'),
(197, '2026-04-13 10:46:27', NULL, 'Dhiren Kumar', 'single', NULL, 'Top 8 Highest 8000m Peaks to Climb in Nepal', '2026/02/06', '<div><span>Are you dreaming of standing on top of the world? Nepal, the land of the Himalayas, is home to some of the most spectacular peaks on Earth. If you’re looking for the ultimate mountaineering adventure, the 8000-meter peaks of Nepal are calling your name! </span></div>\r\n<div><span>These giants are not just mountains; they are legends, each with its own story, challenge, and breathtaking beauty. Let’s take a friendly tour of the </span><span>top 8 highest 8000m peaks in Nepal</span><span> and see what makes them so special.</span></div>\r\n<h2><span>Mount Everest (8,848m)</span></h2>\r\n<div><span>The crown jewel of the Himalayas, <span style=\"color: #236fa1;\"><a href=\"/trip/mount-everest-expedition\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color: #236fa1;\">Everest expedition</a> </span>is the dream of every climber. While it’s the tallest mountain on Earth, it’s surprisingly accessible thanks to guided expeditions and established routes. Of course, it’s no walk in the park, extreme altitude, harsh weather, and the “death zone” make it a real test of endurance. But standing on the summit? Totally worth it.</span></div>\r\n<h2><span>Kangchenjunga (8,586m)</span></h2>\r\n<div><span><span style=\"color: #236fa1;\"><a href=\"/trip/kangchenjunga-expedition-in-nepal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color: #236fa1;\">Kangchenjunga</a>, </span>the “Five Treasures of Snow,” is awe-inspiring and slightly mysterious since it’s less crowded than Everest. Located on the eastern border of Nepal, it offers stunning views and challenging climbs. Climbers often choose it for the adventure and solitude if you’re looking for a quieter expedition with equally breathtaking scenery, Kangchenjunga is your mountain.</span></div>\r\n<h2><span>Lhotse (8,516m)</span></h2>\r\n<div><span>Right next to Everest, <span style=\"color: #236fa1;\"><a href=\"/trip/lhotse-expedition-in-nepal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color: #236fa1;\">Lhotse </a></span>might be overshadowed, but it’s a gem for climbers seeking serious challenges. Its South Face is one of the most formidable walls in the Himalayas. If you’ve conquered Everest, Lhotse could be your next big adventure.</span></div>\r\n<h2><span>Makalu (8,485m)</span></h2>\r\n<div><span><span style=\"color: #236fa1;\"><a href=\"/trip/mount-makalu-expedition\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color: #236fa1;\">Makalu </a></span>is known for its striking pyramid shape and for being tough! It’s a technical climb with sharp ridges and extreme weather, making it perfect for experienced mountaineers. Its remoteness adds to the thrill, offering a sense of true Himalayan adventure far from the crowds.</span></div>\r\n<h2><span>Cho Oyu (8,188m)</span></h2>\r\n<div><span><span style=\"color: #236fa1;\"><a href=\"/trip/mount-cho-oyu-expedition-tibet\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color: #236fa1;\">Cho Oyu</a></span> is often considered the easiest 8000-meter peak to climb, which makes it popular for climbers looking to step into the world of extreme altitudes. It’s beautifully scenic, with views of the surrounding peaks that are nothing short of magical. For first-timers at this height, it’s a fantastic choice.</span></div>\r\n<h2><span>Dhaulagiri (8,167m)</span></h2>\r\n<div><span><span style=\"color: #236fa1;\"><a href=\"/trip/mount-dhaulagiri-expedition\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color: #236fa1;\">Dhaulagiri </a></span>means “White Mountain,” and it certainly lives up to its name. Known for its sheer size and majestic presence, it’s challenging and requires a lot of technical skill. Its remote location makes it less visited, giving climbers a raw, untouched Himalayan experience.</span></div>\r\n<h2><span>Manaslu (8,163m)</span></h2>\r\n<div><span><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Manaslu </span>is the “Mountain of the Spirit,” offering both adventure and serenity. <span style=\"color: #236fa1;\"><a href=\"/trip/mount-manaslu-expedition-in-nepal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color: #236fa1;\">Climbing Mount Manaslu</a></span> is challenging, with avalanche-prone slopes and high-altitude conditions, but the journey rewards adventurers with breathtaking landscapes and a profoundly spiritual experience. It’s becoming more popular among adventurers seeking a balance of thrill and tranquility.</span></div>\r\n<h2><span>Annapurna I (8,091m)</span></h2>\r\n<div><span><span style=\"color: #236fa1;\"><a href=\"/trip/annapurna-expedition-in-nepal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color: #236fa1;\">Annapurna I</a></span> is famous for its massive size and challenging routes. Known as one of the most dangerous 8000m peaks, it tests climbers’ skill, stamina, and patience. But the views? Absolutely jaw-dropping. If you’re looking for adventure mixed with a touch of thrill, Annapurna I is a peak you can’t miss.</span></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><strong>Read Related Blogs</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #236fa1;\"><a href=\"/blogs/top-10-best-peak-climbing-in-nepal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color: #236fa1;\">Top 10 Best Peak Climbing in Nepal</a></span></p>\r\n<span style=\"color: #236fa1;\"><a href=\"/blogs/when-is-the-best-time-for-baruntse-expedition-season-guide\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color: #236fa1;\">When is the Best Time for Baruntse Expedition? (Season Guide)</a></span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #236fa1;\"><a href=\"/blogs/baruntse-expedition-cost\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color: #236fa1;\">Baruntse Expedition Cost</a></span></p>\r\n</div>', 'Climbing an 8000-meter peak is more than just a physical challenge it’s a journey of the heart and mind. Each mountain has its own personality, and each expedition teaches you something new about yourself. Whether you’re aiming for Everest or a slightly less crowded peak like Manaslu, Nepal offers the ultimate playground for adventurers.', 'top-8-highest-8000m-peaks-to-climb-in-nepal', '1773399335579', 33, NULL, 0, 29, 'beautiful-night-views-of-manaslu-expeditions-rYKvZ.webp', 'top-8th-hihest-peaks-in-nepal-gSx6J.jpg', NULL, 'Top 8 Highest 8000m Peaks to Climb in Nepal', 'Discover Nepal’s 8 tallest 8000m peaks! Tips, highlights, and adventures for every climber chasing the ultimate Himalayan challenge.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 74, 'en', '2026-03-13 20:40:35', '2026-04-16 20:35:58'),
(198, '2026-04-12 10:54:19', NULL, 'Dhiren Kumar', 'single', NULL, 'Why Should You Do the Everest Expedition in Nepal?', '2026/02/08', '<div><span>Climbing Mount Everest is the ultimate dream for mountaineers and adventure lovers around the world. Rising to an incredible height of </span><span>8,848.86 meters</span><span>, Everest is the highest mountain on Earth and represents the pinnacle of human endurance, determination, and courage.</span></div>\r\n<div><span></span></div>\r\n<div><span>But beyond the thrill of reaching the summit, doing the Everest expedition in Nepal offers an experience that goes far beyond mountaineering. From breathtaking Himalayan landscapes to the warm hospitality of the Sherpa community, the journey to Everest is as rewarding as the summit itself.</span></div>\r\n<div><span></span></div>\r\n<div><strong>Below are some of the key reasons why Nepal is the best place to attempt the Everest expedition.</strong></div>\r\n<h2><span>The World’s Highest Mountain</span></h2>\r\n<div><span>The most obvious reason to climb Everest in Nepal is that this is where the </span><span>highest point on the planet</span><span> stands. For decades, Everest has inspired explorers and climbers to push their limits and pursue extraordinary achievements.</span></div>\r\n<div><span>The first successful ascent of the mountain in 1953 by Sir Edmund Hillary and Tenzing Norgay turned Everest into a global symbol of adventure and determination. Since then, climbers from all over the world have traveled to Nepal to follow the historic South Col route and experience the challenge of reaching the summit.</span></div>\r\n<div><span>Standing on the top of Everest is more than just a climb it’s a moment that represents years of preparation and a lifetime dream fulfilled.</span></div>\r\n<h2><span>The Iconic Everest Base Camp Journey</span></h2>\r\n<div><span>Most Everest expeditions begin with a trek to Everest Base Camp, which is already one of the most famous trekking routes in the world. This journey allows climbers to gradually acclimatize while experiencing the beauty of the Everest region.</span></div>\r\n<div><span>The trek passes through charming Sherpa villages, lush valleys, and rugged mountain trails. Along the way, trekkers cross suspension bridges, walk through pine forests, and enjoy stunning views of surrounding Himalayan peaks such as Lhotse, Nuptse, and Ama Dablam.</span></div>\r\n<div><span>Reaching Everest Base Camp itself is an incredible milestone, where climbers prepare for the challenging ascent ahead.</span></div>\r\n<h2><span>The Expertise of the Sherpa Community</span></h2>\r\n<div><span>Another major reason to climb Everest in Nepal is the extraordinary support provided by the </span><span>Sherpa community</span><span>. Sherpas are world-renowned for their strength, resilience, and deep knowledge of the Himalayan environment.</span></div>\r\n<div><span>During the expedition, Sherpas help climbers navigate technical sections such as the dangerous Khumbu Icefall, set up high-altitude camps, fix ropes along the climbing route, and ensure the overall safety of the team.</span></div>\r\n<div><span>Their experience and dedication play a crucial role in the success of many Everest expeditions, making them an essential part of the journey.</span></div>\r\n<h2><span>Spectacular Himalayan Scenery</span></h2>\r\n<div><span>Nepal is home to </span><span>eight of the world’s fourteen mountains above 8000 meters</span><span>, which makes it one of the most spectacular mountain regions on Earth. During the Everest expedition, climbers are surrounded by some of the most breathtaking peaks in the Himalayas.</span></div>\r\n<div><span>Mountains such as Makalu, Cho Oyu, and Pumori dominate the skyline, creating unforgettable panoramic views. The combination of glaciers, icefalls, and towering peaks creates a landscape that is both dramatic and inspiring.</span></div>\r\n<div><span>For many climbers, the scenery of the Everest region is one of the most rewarding parts of the expedition.</span></div>\r\n<h2><span>Rich Culture of the Everest Region</span></h2>\r\n<div><span>Climbing Everest in Nepal also provides the opportunity to experience the unique culture of the Khumbu region. Along the trekking route, climbers pass through vibrant Sherpa villages such as Namche Bazaar and Tengboche.</span></div>\r\n<div><span>These villages are known for their colorful prayer flags, ancient monasteries, and welcoming communities. Visiting the famous Tengboche Monastery and learning about the Buddhist traditions of the region adds a spiritual dimension to the expedition.</span></div>\r\n<div><span>This cultural immersion makes the Everest journey more meaningful than just a climbing challenge.</span></div>\r\n<h2><span>A Life-Changing Personal Achievement</span></h2>\r\n<div><span>Climbing Everest is one of the most demanding adventures a person can undertake. The expedition usually takes </span><span>six to eight weeks</span><span>, requiring careful acclimatization, physical endurance, and mental resilience.</span></div>\r\n<div><span>However, reaching the summit brings an unparalleled sense of accomplishment. Standing on the top of Mount Everest, surrounded by the vast Himalayan landscape, is a moment that few people on Earth will ever experience.</span></div>\r\n<div><span>For many climbers, the Everest expedition becomes a </span><span>life-changing journey</span><span> that proves the power of determination and perseverance.</span></div>\r\n<div><span></span></div>\r\n<div><strong>Suggested Reads</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #236fa1;\"><a href=\"/blogs/when-is-the-best-time-for-baruntse-expedition-season-guide\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" style=\"color: #236fa1;\">When is the Best Time for Baruntse Expedition? (Season Guide)</a></span></p>\r\n</div>', NULL, 'why-should-you-do-the-everest-expedition-in-nepal', '1773400057928', 33, NULL, 0, 30, NULL, 'why-should-you-do-the-everest-expeditions-in-nepal-wpmUz.jpg', NULL, 'Why Do the Everest Expedition in Nepal? Top Reasons to Climb Mount Everest', 'Discover why doing the Everest expedition in Nepal is the ultimate adventure stunning Himalayas, Sherpa support, and the challenge of climbing Mount Everest.', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 74, 'en', '2026-03-13 20:52:37', '2026-04-16 20:36:23');
