INSERT INTO `cl_trip_faqs` (`id`, `trip_detail_id`, `title`, `content`, `ordering`, `status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(177, 361, 'What food will be served during the expedition?', 'All kind of meals is served during our expedition by our professional chefs at base camp and on the higher camps.', 12, 1, '2023-02-09 06:23:00', '2023-02-09 06:23:00'),
(178, 361, 'How long does it take to climb Dhaulagiri?', 'The length of time it takes to climb Dhaulagiri will depend on several factors, including the route being taken, the climber\'s experience and ability, and the weather conditions. A typical expedition to the summit of Dhaulagiri can take anywhere from seven to eight weeks.', 13, 1, '2023-02-09 06:23:00', '2023-02-09 06:23:00'),
(179, 164, 'What is the best time for EBC Trek ?', 'The most popular months for trekking in the Everest region are March, April, May, October and November, as these months are when the conditions are at their best. The spring and the autumn tend to offer reasonable temperatures, clear skies, little-to-no rain, and less chance of problematic snowfall.', 1, 1, '2024-08-23 17:01:38', '2024-08-23 17:01:38'),
(180, 164, 'Is Everest Base Camp trek worth it?', 'The Everest region is a beautiful place to visit and a trek to Everest Base Camp is an ambition for many trekkers. Trekking to the base of the world’s highest mountain is a fantastic achievement and it is well worth the effort. Most people think the positives outweigh the drawback of walking on busier trails', 2, 1, '2024-08-23 17:01:38', '2024-08-23 17:01:38'),
(181, 164, 'Training for EBC Trek ?', 'Most people will benefit from aerobic conditioning and strength endurance for Everest Base Camp. Although the trek is typically slow and steady, you will be trekking 5-8 hours per day and gaining on average 300m (1000 ft) in elevation each day', 3, 1, '2024-08-23 17:01:38', '2024-08-23 17:01:38'),
(182, 164, 'How difficult is Everest Base Camp Trek Trek ?', 'Trekking to Everest Base Camp is an adventure of a lifetime. This trek can be a life-changing experience for many people.  The difficulty level of the Everest Base Camp is moderate. The trekking time often requires two weeks. Even though the EBC Trek requires no prior trekking expertise, it is suggested that the trekker should be determined and be physically fit.  Altitude is by far the most challenging aspect of the trek and is what makes it more difficult than your average trek of the same length', 4, 1, '2024-08-23 17:01:38', '2024-08-23 17:01:38'),
(183, 165, 'When is the best time to do the trek?', 'The best times for the Annapurna Base Camp trek are during the spring (March to May) and autumn (September to November) seasons. These months offer clear skies, mild temperatures, and stunning views.', NULL, 1, '2024-08-23 17:32:31', '2024-09-11 14:49:54'),
(184, 165, 'What is the level of difficulty for the trek?', 'The Annapurna Base Camp Trek is considered to be of moderate difficulty. It involves some steep ascents and descents, but it doesn’t require technical climbing skills. Basic fitness and prior trekking experience are recommended.', NULL, 1, '2024-08-23 17:32:31', '2024-09-11 14:49:54'),
(185, 131, 'What is the best time for EBC Trek?', 'The most popular months for trekking in the Everest region are March, April, May, October and November, as these months are when the conditions are at their best. The spring and the autumn tend to offer reasonable temperatures, clear skies, little-to-no rain, and less chance of problematic snowfall.', NULL, 1, '2024-08-23 21:09:40', '2024-09-09 15:55:28'),
(187, 167, 'How difficult is Mardi Himal trek?', 'Mardi Himal trek is rate easy because it is one of the shorter treks and the path does not take you to difficult places but beginner trekkers do rate it as a medium difficult level trek. Exhausting long walks and uphill climbs make it medium level trek for beginners. Each day you walk around 5 to 6 hours on the foothills of Mardi Himal.', 1, 1, '2024-08-26 16:42:07', '2024-08-26 16:42:07'),
(188, 167, 'How long is Mardi Himal trek?', 'The total distance of Mardi Himal Trek is 41 km. The path follow from Kande to Australian Camp, Pothana, Deurali, Forest Camp, Badal Danda(Middle Camp), High Camp And finally Mardi HImal Base Camp then back to Low camp to Siding Village and drive to Pokhara.', 2, 1, '2024-08-26 16:42:07', '2024-08-26 16:42:07'),
(189, 167, 'How many days do we need for Mardi Himal trek?', 'This trek can be done within 4 days to 10 days. If you have short time period you can make the shortest (4 days) but you need to fly in and Fly out to Pokhara to Kathmandu. It can save your 2 days’ time. If you have more than a week’s time then you can take a bus to Pokhara for your trip and you can extend your trekking to Annapurna Base Camp or Annapurna Sunrise (Punhill Trek )  Taking Kathmandu to Pokhara and Pokhara to Kathmandu flights to start the trek on the same day is ideal for those who has holidays of less than a week. For customization for the tri  let us know your preference', 3, 1, '2024-08-26 16:42:07', '2024-08-26 16:42:07'),
(190, 138, 'What is the best time to climb Mera Peak?', 'We recommend climbing Mera Peak in late April, May, late September, October, and November. We find that when we climb on Mera Peak, generally the best months are May and October. If you decide to climb in late March, early April or late October into November, you need to be ready for colder conditions.', NULL, 1, '2024-08-26 18:20:10', '2024-08-26 18:20:10'),
(191, 138, 'How difficult is Mera Peak', 'Climbing Mera peak itself is not very technical and doesn’t consist of a steep technical climb but the high altitude reaching 6461m at the summit makes this a challenging climb. Unlike other trekking peaks in Nepal, the climb to Mera peak is straightforward.', NULL, 1, '2024-08-26 18:20:10', '2024-08-26 18:20:10'),
(192, 138, 'What preparation is required for Mera Peak Ski', 'FITNESS Climbers must be in excellent physical shape to join this expedition. This is perhaps the most important aspect of high altitude climbing, and cannot be stressed enough. Regular, challenging exercise for many months in advance of departure is the only way to gain the necessary level of fitness that is needed on big peaks. We highly recommend a structured training regime with a gym or personal trainer to assist you in preparing for climbing at altitude. Please contact us for more information on physical training.  TECHNICAL EXPERIENCE Skiers must be competent on a variety of terrain and snow conditions. Skiers must be able to link turns in steep terrain (up to 45 degrees) while maintaining control. Skiers must also have basic snow climbing experience including use of ice axe and crampons.  ALTITUDE EXPERIENCE It is required that climbers have prior experience at altitudes up to 14,000′ and it is strongly recommended that climbers have prior experience at altitudes over 15,000′', NULL, 1, '2024-08-26 18:20:10', '2024-08-26 18:20:10'),
(194, 168, 'What is the Everest Panorama Trek?', 'The Everest Panorama Trek is a short and scenic trek in the Everest region of Nepal that offers stunning views of Mount Everest and other Himalayan peaks. This trek is ideal for those who want to experience the beauty of the Everest region without committing to a longer and more challenging trek.', 1, 1, '2024-08-27 15:06:47', '2024-08-27 15:06:47'),
(195, 168, 'What is the best time to go on the Everest Panorama Trek?', 'The best time to embark on the Everest Panorama Trek is during the spring (March to May) and autumn (September to November) seasons. These months offer clear skies, mild temperatures, and the best views of the Himalayan peaks.', 2, 1, '2024-08-27 15:06:47', '2024-08-27 15:06:47'),
(196, 168, 'What is the Everest Panorama Trek?', 'The Everest Panorama Trek is a short and scenic trek in the Everest region of Nepal that offers stunning views of Mount Everest and other Himalayan peaks. This trek is ideal for those who want to experience the beauty of the Everest region without committing to a longer and more challenging trek.', 1, 1, '2024-08-27 15:06:47', '2024-08-27 15:06:47'),
(197, 168, 'What is the best time to go on the Everest Panorama Trek?', 'The best time to embark on the Everest Panorama Trek is during the spring (March to May) and autumn (September to November) seasons. These months offer clear skies, mild temperatures, and the best views of the Himalayan peaks.', 2, 1, '2024-08-27 15:06:47', '2024-08-27 15:06:47'),
(198, 171, 'How hard is Gokyo Trek ?', 'The Gokyo lake trek is moderately difficult. You need to be in good shape and stamina for this trek as it requires walking about 5 to 6 hours, excluding the acclimation days. The rugged trails, steep terrains, and high passes prove to be more burdensome.', 1, 1, '2024-08-27 15:32:03', '2024-08-27 15:32:03'),
(199, 171, 'What is the best time for Gokyo Valley Trek ?', 'October and November or April and May are widely considered to be the best times for this trekking. The weather during these two seasons is generally clear and dry, and so it’s not too cold when heading into high altitudes.', 2, 1, '2024-08-27 15:32:03', '2024-08-27 15:32:03'),
(200, 172, 'What is the best time to for this Trek ?', 'The best time for the Everest Luxury  Trek is in the pre-monsoon season, i.e., from March to May, and the post-monsoon season, i.e., from late September to December. It is also possible to do this trek in February and early September but the trek is best preferred during the above months.', 1, 1, '2024-08-27 18:14:23', '2024-08-27 18:14:23'),
(201, 173, 'What is the best time to for this Trek ?', 'The best time for the Everest Luxury  Trek is in the pre-monsoon season, i.e., from March to May, and the post-monsoon season, i.e., from late September to December. It is also possible to do this trek in February and early September but the trek is best preferred during the above months.', 1, 1, '2024-08-27 18:16:07', '2024-08-27 18:16:07'),
(202, 174, 'What is the best time to for this Trek ?', 'The best time for the Everest Luxury  Trek is in the pre-monsoon season, i.e., from March to May, and the post-monsoon season, i.e., from late September to December. It is also possible to do this trek in February and early September but the trek is best preferred during the above months.', 1, 1, '2024-08-27 18:17:11', '2024-08-27 18:17:11'),
(203, 174, 'How difficult is Everest Luxury Trek ?', 'Everest Luxury Trek is considered challenging due to high altitudes. The trail is relatively easier following good paths and yak trails but due to the increasing altitude, it’s graded challenging. The trek reaches a maximum elevation of 5545m/18,193ft at Kalapathar with a maximum overnight elevation of 5140m/16,865ft at Gorekshep.  Please be prepared to walk for 6-7 hrs every day on average carrying your backpack, which will consist of your valuable items, water, extra fleece, snacks, etc. The trek is challenging and it is a longer trek reaching up to an elevation of 5500m where some of the famous mountaineering Base Camps are located and you need to sleep at an elevation of 5000m+ for 1 night at Gorekshep', 2, 1, '2024-08-27 18:32:22', '2024-08-27 18:32:22'),
(204, 174, 'How do i train for the trek ?', 'Everest Base Camp Trek is a premier trek that most ardent backpackers, hikers, and lovers of wild places aspire to. The trek is graded challenging and training yourself well ahead will definitely improve your performance during the trek. Answering this question can be a challenge because everyone is starting from a different base of fitness, age, lifestyle, and diet (what you eat on a daily basis).  Always consult with your doctor first to establish if you are healthy enough for the challenges of all-day trekking at high elevation for over a week. Once cleared for takeoff, so to speak, consulting with a qualified trainer, and a nutritionist may also prove beneficial, though many do not.', 3, 1, '2024-08-27 18:32:22', '2024-08-27 18:32:22'),
(205, 180, 'what is the best time for this trek ?', 'Regarding the best time, the spring months of March, April, and May along with the autumn months of September, October, and November are peak times.', 1, 1, '2024-08-28 17:48:08', '2024-08-28 17:48:08'),
(206, 180, 'How difficult is Annapurna Balcony Trek ?', 'Annapurna Balcony trekking is a moderately graded trekking adventure suitable for first-timers to all those travel lovers looking forward to experiencing active journeys in Nepal. No particular difficulties on this trek apart from the stone staircase,', 2, 1, '2024-08-28 17:48:08', '2024-08-28 17:48:08'),
(207, 184, 'What is the best time to for Drukpath Trek ?', 'The best times to embark on the Druk Path Trek are between March-June or September-November.', NULL, 1, '2024-08-29 17:12:57', '2024-08-29 17:12:57'),
(208, 184, 'What is the Druk Path Trek difficulty?', 'The trek is rated by the Tourism Council of Bhutan as “medium”, mainly because of the higher elevations that you will reach during the trek. With a maximum elevation of around 4,235 meters, which is at the top of Labana La Pass, which is a long and hard climb.', NULL, 1, '2024-08-29 17:12:57', '2024-08-29 17:12:57'),
(209, 189, 'How is the weather ?', 'In the daytime the weather can get quite sunny and warm in the night it can get to freezing temperature as cold as -30c. So be prepared for the freezing nights inside the tents.', 1, 1, '2024-09-02 11:48:32', '2024-09-02 11:48:32'),
(210, 189, 'When is the best time to climb Himlung 7126M?', 'The best time for Himlung Expedition is during the spring (April-May) and fall (October-November) seasons. During these seasons, the weather is stable, and the skies are clear, making it easier to navigate the mountain.', 2, 1, '2024-09-02 11:48:32', '2024-09-02 11:48:32'),
(211, 189, 'How hard is himlung himal?', 'Himlung Himal (7126 meters) is a classic Himalayan expedition known for being one of the lesser difficult and least technical 7000 meter+ mountains to climb (although it should not be underestimated). It has the highest recorded summit success rate (according to the Himalayan Database) compared to other peaks.', 3, 1, '2024-09-02 11:48:32', '2024-09-02 11:48:32'),
(212, 178, 'What is the best time to climb Saribung', 'The best time to climb Saribung Peak is during the spring (April-May) and autumn (September-November) seasons. These months offer stable weather conditions, clear skies, and good visibility.', 1, 1, '2024-09-02 12:08:15', '2024-09-02 12:08:15'),
(213, 178, 'How hard is Saribung Peak climbing ?', 'Saribung Peak Climbing is a challenging adventure that requires a good level of physical fitness, technical climbing skills, and experience.', 2, 1, '2024-09-02 12:08:15', '2024-09-02 12:08:15'),
(214, 169, 'How hard is mera Peak climbing?', 'Climbing Mera peak itself is not very technical and doesn’t consist of a steep technical climb but the high altitude reaching 6461m at the summit makes this a challenging climb. Unlike other trekking peaks in Nepal, the climb to Mera peak is straightforward.', 1, 1, '2024-09-02 12:18:15', '2024-09-02 12:18:15'),
(215, 169, 'What is the best time to climb Mera Peak', 'We recommend climbing Mera Peak in late April, May, late September, October, and November. We find that when we climb on Mera Peak, generally the best months are May and October. If you decide to climb in late March, early April or late October into November, you need to be ready for colder conditions.', 2, 1, '2024-09-02 12:18:15', '2024-09-02 12:18:15'),
(216, 169, 'Can i see Everest from Mera Peak', 'There are several peaks, and among them, Mera Peak is one of them. It provides the view of five 8000 er including Everest. The peak gives a close-up view of Mount Everest, Cho Oyu, Makalu, Kanchenjunga, and Lhotse', 3, 1, '2024-09-02 12:18:15', '2024-09-02 12:18:15'),
(217, 159, 'What skillset and fitness level are required?', 'This expeditions are within extreme high altitude environments, with differing requirements for ability. Due to the nature of these operational landscapes it is essential you provide concise, honest descriptions of relevant experience and current fitness levels', NULL, 1, '2024-09-02 12:51:21', '2024-09-02 12:51:21'),
(218, 159, 'What is the requirements for this Exped?', 'Attempting any 8,000m peak is a significant endeavour, but our team will help put the peak of Manaslu within reach. We would expect anyone joining this expedition to have summited multiple 6,000m and 7,000m peaks.', NULL, 1, '2024-09-02 12:51:21', '2024-09-02 12:51:21'),
(219, 190, 'How difficult is Three peak climbing', 'Grading: 7-8 (Strenuous)  Three peak climbing is considered strenuous due to longer duration trek/climb in a remote and isolated area that goes above 5500m and you need to sleep at an elevation of 5000m+ for multiple days. Climbers are required to have an excellent physical level. On summit days, you will leave base camp at around 2 am and will only be back to base camp by late afternoon. This grade trip involves usages of climbing equipment (Harness, Ice Axe, Crampons, Mountaineering Boots, Ascender). Previous experience is essential and we also provide a climbing course at base camp before the actual climb where your guides will teach you the proper way to use the equipment.', NULL, 1, '2024-09-02 16:02:28', '2024-09-02 17:13:04'),
(220, 190, 'What physical condition is required ?', 'To partake in Three peaks climb, an excellent physical level is required as this trip involves a longer duration of trek/climb. Previous experience of high altitude treks and climbing smaller peaks is of great advantage while climbing 6000m peaks. While the previous experience of trek/climb is a requirement, our carefully planned itinerary allows people without previous experience to join as well. We begin the trip with an acclimatized trek to Mera peak and afterward cross the Amphu Laptha before heading to Island peak and Lobuche Peak. You should also be both mentally and physically prepared for this trip. A fierce determination, burning desire and teamwork is required. We have allowed ample time for acclimatization and contingency day on our itinerary and there will also be a climbing course at the base camp where your guide will teach you the proper way to use the equipment.', NULL, 1, '2024-09-02 16:03:27', '2024-09-02 16:03:27'),
(221, 190, 'What is the best season to climb Tree peaks ?', 'The best seasons for Three Peaks Climb are Autumn (from October till the end of November) and Spring (April to May). Temperatures will drop considerably as you ascend higher every day. The nights are cold (between 5C to -5C) and the days are sunny and hot (between 10C to 20C).  Mornings are usually clear, with clouds building up in the afternoon and disappearing at night. Trekking and climbing during the monsoon seasons and winters are not recommended as the visibility is poor and limited whilst upper parts and high passes could be covered with snow.  March, April, October, and November are the favored months. Please choose a date that is convenient for you.', NULL, 1, '2024-09-02 16:03:27', '2024-09-02 16:04:41'),
(222, 198, 'What is the best  time for this trek ?', 'The best times for trekking in Nepal are from March to Early May and from September to November. Trekking is possible from December to February and it\'s a good time to avoid the crowds but you will need to be prepared for colder temperatures. June to August is the rainy season and we don\'t generally recommend trekking. If June to August is the only time you can trek send us an email and we can provide some suggestions.', 1, 1, '2024-09-03 21:28:16', '2024-09-03 21:28:16'),
(223, 198, 'Is Everest BC trek worth it?', 'The Everest region is a beautiful place to visit and a trek to Everest Base Camp is an ambition for many trekkers. Trekking to the base of the world’s highest mountain is a fantastic achievement and it is well worth the effort. Most people think the positives outweigh the drawback of walking on busier trails', 2, 1, '2024-09-03 21:28:16', '2024-09-03 21:28:16'),
(224, 198, 'Training for this Trek ?', 'Most people will benefit from aerobic conditioning and strength endurance for Everest Base Camp. Although the trek is typically slow and steady, you will be trekking 5-8 hours per day and gaining on average 300m (1000 ft) in elevation each day', 3, 1, '2024-09-03 21:28:16', '2024-09-03 21:28:16'),
(225, 196, 'What is the best time for Lower Dolpa Trek', 'The best time for Lower Dolpo Trekking is during the Spring (March to May) and Autumn (September to November)', NULL, 1, '2024-09-04 22:18:50', '2024-09-04 22:18:50'),
(226, 195, 'How hard is annapurna circuit Trek', 'Annapurna Circuit Trekking is a moderately challenging trip around the popular Annapurna region suitable for experienced as well as novice hikers who are passionate about walking, exploring, and adventure with a good level of physical and mental fitness level.', 1, 1, '2024-09-05 14:53:58', '2024-09-05 14:53:58'),
(227, 195, 'What is the best time for Annapurna Circuit Trek?', 'For the Annapurna Circuit, October and November or April and May are widely considered to be the best times for trekking. The weather during these two seasons is generally clear and dry, and so it’s not too cold when heading into high altitudes.', 2, 1, '2024-09-05 14:53:58', '2024-09-05 14:53:58'),
(228, 195, 'Can i do this trek in December', 'Annapurna Circuit Trek in December is usually less crowded than any other seasons. The trekking trails are mostly empty and peaceful. The weather condition and temperature of the Annapurna region are bearable during December. The weather might be quite chilly in the higher areas', 3, 1, '2024-09-05 14:53:58', '2024-09-05 14:53:58'),
(229, 194, 'When is the best time to climb island peak?', 'The best time to climb Island peak is Autumn and Spring season. These seasons have very ideal climate and weather for Island peak climbing. The weather is stable with clear visibility of the views. But, this expedition is possible during the Winter and Monsoon season as well.', NULL, 1, '2024-09-05 21:44:51', '2024-09-05 21:44:51'),
(230, 194, 'How hard is island  Peak climbing?', 'Island peak climb is basically recommended for beginners willing to step into the world of mountaineering. Even then, climbing the Island peak requires having the experience of trekking in a high altitude.  Island peak is a difficult climb at an extreme altitude. The foot of the headwall is the toughest part of the climb. The ascent is very steep and the air at its thinnest. However, the climbing route is safe because of fixed lines.', NULL, 1, '2024-09-05 21:44:51', '2024-09-05 21:44:51'),
(231, 194, 'How hard is island  Peak climbing?', 'Grading: 7-8 (Strenuous), Alpine PD+   Climbing Island peak is considered strenuous due to longer duration trek/climb in a remote and isolated area that goes above 5500m. You need to sleep at an elevation of 5000m+ for multiple days. Climbers are required to have an excellent physical level with fierce determination. Daily walking hours include 6-7 hrs on average and summit day can be 10-14 hrs long.  This grade trip involves the usage of climbing equipment (Harness, Ice Axe, Crampons, Mountaineering Boots, Ascender). Previous experience is essential and we also provide a climbing course at base camp before the actual climb where your guides will teach you the proper way to use the equipment.', NULL, 1, '2024-09-05 21:44:51', '2024-09-05 21:44:51'),
(232, 194, 'How to prepare for island peak ?', 'High altitude treks and climbs especially in the Himalayas are challenging and require you to be in the top physical, emotional, and psychological condition. The more fitter you are, the more enjoyable your trip will be.  Do daily physical workouts (jogging, hiking, cycling, gym, etc) prior to a couple of weeks.  Climbing conditioning – pack-loaded uphill hiking, walking, and stair climbing. Strength training – for the lower body and core. Cardiovascular training – including both aerobic and anaerobic workouts without pack weight. Flexibility training.', NULL, 1, '2024-09-05 21:44:51', '2024-09-05 21:44:51'),
(233, 194, 'Which is harder island peak or Mera Peak ?', 'Bringing out typical tastes of peak climbing in Nepal, both Island Peak and Mera Peak have their own set of peculiarities. Mera Peak is slightly higher than Island Peak while Island Peak, with more steep ice climbs, is considered a little more technical than Mera Peak. There are some significant differences in the climbing aspects of  Climbing. While both peaks do not require specific mountaineering skills, many other factors differentiate these two peaks. Mera Peak is deemed the easier one to climb from the safety point, whereas in terms of adventure Island Peak offers more thrills of mountain climbing', NULL, 1, '2024-09-05 21:44:51', '2024-09-05 21:44:51'),
(234, 194, 'Can you see Everest from island peak ?', 'Mt. Everest is not visible from the summit of Island peak as the peak is tucked behind the shoulders of Mt. Lhotse. However, you can marvel at the magnificent views of Mt. Ama Dablam, Mt. Lhotse, and Mera Peak.', NULL, 1, '2024-09-05 21:44:51', '2024-09-05 21:44:51'),
(235, 193, 'How difficult is it to climb Ama Dablam?', 'Climbing Ama Dablam is considered technically challenging, requiring prior mountaineering experience. It includes steep ice and rock sections, exposed ridges, and technical climbing.', 1, 1, '2024-09-07 13:49:47', '2024-09-07 13:49:47'),
(236, 193, 'When is the best time to climb Ama Dablam?', 'The optimal climbing seasons are spring (April to May) and autumn (September to November). During these periods, you’ll find stable weather conditions and clear skies, making for safer and more enjoyable climbs.', 2, 1, '2024-09-07 13:49:47', '2024-09-07 13:49:47'),
(237, 193, 'How long does it take to climb Ama Dablam?', 'The typical Ama Dablam expedition lasts about 30 days how however you can climb Ama Dablam in just 14 days with our Speed summit pakage', 3, 1, '2024-09-07 13:49:47', '2024-09-07 13:49:47'),
(238, 192, 'How difficult is Everest Comfort Trek ?', 'In general, the trek is mostly moderate and slightly difficult at some places. Trekking to Namche Bazaar from Lukla itself is a challenging walk as the trail is very steep and sloppy. The farthest point on the trek is Tengboche at 3,870m (12,697ft.). You will take an acclimatization hike up to Everest View Hotel which is situated at 3,962m (13,000ft.) while you are in Namche Bazaar. This is in fact, the highest point on the trek. If you are physically fit and mentally strong with a strong determination, then this trek is not as difficult as one can reckon. The only factor that attributes to the difficulty of this trek is the altitude and the long walking hours on uneven terrains for several days.', 1, 1, '2024-09-07 13:56:56', '2024-09-07 13:56:56'),
(239, 192, 'What is the best time for this trek ?', 'In general, the trek is mostly moderate and slightly difficult at some places. Trekking to Namche Bazaar from Lukla itself is a challenging walk as the trail is very steep and sloppy. The farthest point on the trek is Tengboche at 3,870m (12,697ft.). You will take an acclimatization hike up to Everest View Hotel which is situated at 3,962m (13,000ft.) while you are in Namche Bazaar. This is in fact, the highest point on the trek. If you are physically fit and mentally strong with a strong determination, then this trek is not as difficult as one can reckon. The only factor that attributes to the difficulty of this trek is the altitude and the long walking hours on uneven terrains for several days.', 2, 1, '2024-09-07 13:56:56', '2024-09-07 13:56:56'),
(240, 191, 'What is the best time for Manaslu Circuit Trek ?', 'This Manaslu trek is best done in pre-monsoon season i.e. from March to May and post-monsoon season i.e. from late September to December. In general, any time during October, November, April and May are considered the best months. Other recommended months for this trek are September, December and March. We do not recommend doing this trek during the rest of the months. Due to heavy snowfall in January and February it becomes very risky to cross the Larkya La Pass. Likewise, heavy rainfall causing flood and landslide can be experienced during June, July and August, so it is better to avoid these months.', NULL, 1, '2024-09-08 14:50:09', '2024-09-08 14:50:09'),
(241, 191, 'How difficult is Manaslu Circuit Trek ?', 'The Manaslu Circuit Trek is a moderate to challenging trek that involves long hours of continuous hiking, steep ascents and descents, and high altitudes', NULL, 1, '2024-09-08 14:50:09', '2024-09-08 14:50:09'),
(244, 179, 'How is Automn  season for Pikey Pamggom Trek', 'The Autumn Season (September, October, and November) is considered as one of the best times for Pikey Peak Trek. During the autumn season, the weather is stable, and the environment is pleasant. The clear skies and. excellent visibility make autumn stand out as the ideal time to embark on this journey. The colorful autumn leaves perfectly complement the surroundings, creating an enchanting scenery. The daylight is beautiful, and crystal-clear views of the Himalayan Landscape can be seen during the autumn. The days are warm and pleasant, which creates favorable walking conditions for the trekkers.', NULL, 1, '2024-09-09 09:38:38', '2024-09-09 09:38:38'),
(245, 179, 'How is Spring Season for Pikey Panggom Trek ?', 'Spring Season (March, April, and May) stands out as the best time for Pikey Peak Trek. The vibrant atmosphere of spring creates a pleasant trekking environment for the trekkers. During the spring season, you will get to walk along the tranquil forests filled with blooming rhododendrons. The sweet aroma of blooming flowers will enhance your walking experience and make the whole journey pleasant. The weather is stable during the spring season, which creates a favorable walking environment for the trekkers.', NULL, 1, '2024-09-09 09:38:38', '2024-09-09 09:38:38'),
(246, 179, 'Where is Panggom Village ?', 'Panggom is a village located at a height of 2900 m.in the Solukhubu District in Nepal, 50 kilometers south of Everest, the world\'s highest peak.', NULL, 1, '2024-09-09 09:52:52', '2024-09-09 09:52:52'),
(247, 199, 'How difficult is the Langtang Valley trek?', 'This one is the most frequently asked question about the Langtang trek. so here I came with the answer. Langtang Valley Trek is an easy to moderate level of trek. even the beginner\'s trekker can complete this trek successfully, I mean you don’t need any other trekking experience.  You should be physically and mentally fit. For the seven days Langtang Trek, on average you should walk around 5-6 hours a day. Walking at a high altitude can be quite tough as you have to wake up early to avoid cold wind. But if you have strong wills and dedication you can easily complete the Langtang Valley Trek without much difficulty', NULL, 1, '2024-09-09 15:39:03', '2024-09-09 15:39:03'),
(248, 199, 'When is the best time to trek Langtang Valley Trek?', 'Trekking throughout the year is possible for Langtang Valley Trek but the spring and autumn season is considered the best among four-season due to the stable warm temperature, clear weather, mindblowing mountain views with clear skies, and this season is considered a safe season to explore as well. Being the best season, many trekkers choose this time of the year to explore so if you want peaceful travel, to avoid the crowd you can trek during winter (January to February) if the cold doesn’t bother you a lot, and during the summer season, these time in the years you will not see many peoples and can get comfortable accommodation with good discount in meals too.', NULL, 1, '2024-09-09 15:39:03', '2024-09-09 15:39:03'),
(249, 131, 'Is Everest Base Camp trek worth it?', 'The Everest region is a beautiful place to visit and a trek to Everest Base Camp is an ambition for many trekkers. Trekking to the base of the world’s highest mountain is a fantastic achievement and it is well worth the effort. Most people think the positives outweigh the drawback of walking on busier trails', NULL, 1, '2024-09-09 15:55:28', '2024-09-09 15:55:28'),
(250, 131, 'How difficult is Everest Base Camp Trek Trek ?', 'Trekking to Everest Base Camp is an adventure of a lifetime. This trek can be a life-changing experience for many people.  The difficulty level of the Everest Base Camp is moderate. The trekking time often requires two weeks. Even though the EBC Trek requires no prior trekking expertise, it is suggested that the trekker should be determined and be physically fit.  Altitude is by far the most challenging aspect of the trek and is what makes it more difficult than your average trek of the same length', NULL, 1, '2024-09-09 15:55:28', '2024-09-09 15:55:28'),
(251, 131, 'Training for EBC Trek ?', 'Most people will benefit from aerobic conditioning and strength endurance for Everest Base Camp. Although the trek is typically slow and steady, you will be trekking 5-8 hours per day and gaining on average 300m (1000 ft) in elevation each day', NULL, 1, '2024-09-09 15:55:28', '2024-09-09 15:55:28'),
(252, 200, 'What is the distance of the Langtang Valley Trek?', 'Langtang Valley Trek is one of the closest treks in Nepal. It is approximately 190 kilometers from Kathmandu and is among the shortest treks in Nepal. The tours last an average of 8 days, but other treks like Gosaikunda will give you more options to explore if you have more time', NULL, 1, '2024-09-09 22:06:10', '2024-09-09 22:06:10'),
(253, 200, 'How Difficult is Langtang Valley Trek?', 'Langtang Valley Trek is among the easy to moderate-level treks in Nepal. For the Langtang Valley Trek, you do not need any experience and also don’t need mountain climbing skills. Throughout the trek, you must walk at least 60-70 kilometers while covering at least 7 hours daily. Langtang Valley trek also takes you over 3000m, which causes a significant risk of altitude sickness. However, if you are better prepared and plan for the trek, you can quickly complete it.', NULL, 1, '2024-09-09 22:06:10', '2024-09-09 22:06:10'),
(254, 200, 'What is the best time to trek Langtang Valley?', 'The best time to trek in the Langang Valley depends on the season you are visiting. In Nepal, two seasons are considered peak seasons: spring and autumn. Similarly, two seasons that are considered off-season are Winter and Monsoon season. As the name suggests, peak season is ideal for trekking, whereas off-season treks are not ideal, especially for beginners.', NULL, 1, '2024-09-09 22:06:10', '2024-09-09 22:06:10'),
(255, 200, 'Do I need to have Travel Insurance?', 'Yes, getting travel insurance will help you in case of an emergency evacuation from a helicopter. It can help you from unexpected costs like medical, loss of baggage, or cancellation fees. Before doing insurance, read the terms and conditions well to ensure to meets your needs', NULL, 1, '2024-09-09 22:08:44', '2024-09-09 22:08:44'),
(256, 232, 'Is Annapurna harder than Kilimanjaro?', 'Annapurna is harder than Kilimanjaro because of the highest fatality rate on the Annapurna along with technical expeditions skills. Were as the Kilimanjaro is just at an altitude of 5,895 m which does not requires the technical climbing skills.', 1, 1, '2026-02-03 22:20:21', '2026-02-03 22:20:21'),
(257, 232, 'Is Annapurna harder than Everest?', 'Both Annapurna and Everest is harder in terms of climbing and both are above 8000 meters. However, Annapurna is considered as the more harder because of its unpredictable weather and the avalanches prone slope.', 2, 1, '2026-02-03 22:20:21', '2026-02-03 22:20:21'),
(258, 232, 'Why is Annapurna called the silent killer?', 'Annapurna is called the silent killer because it has one of the highest fatality rate of 32% which is one of the highest compared to any other 8000 meters peaks.', 3, 1, '2026-02-03 22:20:21', '2026-02-03 22:20:21'),
(259, 232, 'What gear is needed for Annapurna?', 'You will require many gears for Annapurna such as mountain boots which is insulated, crampons, ice axes, helmet, harness, sleeping bags rates -40 C, goggles, headlamps, oxygen system and many more. Please check out packing list for the Annapurna expeditions blogs for detailed list.', 4, 1, '2026-02-03 22:20:21', '2026-02-03 22:20:21'),
(260, 232, 'Is K2 or Annapurna deadlier?', 'Annapurna is deadlier in compared to k2 as well as the k2 expeditions is organized and well maintained by the expeditions teams were as Annapurna cannot be organized well due to it’s unpredictable weather and the unpredictable avalanches.', 5, 1, '2026-02-03 22:20:21', '2026-02-03 22:20:21'),
(261, 232, 'What mountain is forbidden to climb?', 'In Nepal Machapuchhare which is often known as the Fish tail mountain by the trekkers is forbidden to climb as locals consider this as a scared mountain.', 6, 1, '2026-02-03 22:20:21', '2026-02-03 22:20:21'),
(262, 232, 'What is the death rate for the Annapurna Base Camp trek?', 'The death rate of Annapurna base camp trek is very rare as it’s the base camp due to which everything is organized and immediate rescue can happen. However, talking about the peak its 32% fatality rate which is the highest in the world.', 7, 1, '2026-02-03 22:20:21', '2026-02-03 22:20:21'),
(263, 232, 'Can you sleep at Annapurna Base Camp?', 'Yes, you can sleep at Annapurna base camp. The tea houses and lodges are well maintained and run by locals who cares about your comfort,', 8, 1, '2026-02-03 22:20:21', '2026-02-03 22:20:21'),
(264, 122, 'What is the 2 o’clock / 2 pm rule on Everest?', '<p>The 2 o’ clock or known as the 2 pm role on Everest is that climbers must stop summiting if they have not reached the top of the peak till 2 pm because of the unpredictable weather and storms.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-02-03 22:35:48', '2026-02-19 03:10:14'),
(265, 122, 'Is Sleeping Beauty still on Everest?', '<p>No, sleeping beauty (Francys Arsentiev) is not there on Everest as it was removed in 2007 from the main route for the climber’s safety.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-02-03 22:35:48', '2026-02-19 03:10:14'),
(266, 122, 'Can a beginner hike in Everest?', '<p>No, a beginner cannot hike in Everest because the mountain is the worl’ds highest peak and its at an altitude of 8848 meters which is death zone so its always important for you to do some trekking, some 7000 meter expeditions and then climb.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-02-03 22:35:48', '2026-02-19 03:10:14'),
(267, 122, 'Why does it cost $40,000 to climb Mount Everest?', '<p>It costs $40, 000 to climb Mount Everest because of the permits fees fixed by the Nepal government, Sherpa guides, oxygen cylinders, foods, accommodations, gears and equipment and many more.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-02-03 22:35:48', '2026-02-19 03:10:14'),
(268, 122, 'What is the 2 o’clock / 2 pm rule on Everest?', '<p>The 2 o’ clock or known as the 2 pm role on Everest is that climbers must stop summiting if they have not reached the top of the peak till 2 pm because of the unpredictable weather and storms.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-02-03 22:35:50', '2026-02-19 03:10:14'),
(269, 122, 'Is Sleeping Beauty still on Everest?', '<p>No, sleeping beauty (Francys Arsentiev) is not there on Everest as it was removed in 2007 from the main route for the climber’s safety.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-02-03 22:35:50', '2026-02-19 03:10:14'),
(270, 122, 'Can a beginner hike in Everest?', '<p>No, a beginner cannot hike in Everest because the mountain is the worl’ds highest peak and its at an altitude of 8848 meters which is death zone so its always important for you to do some trekking, some 7000 meter expeditions and then climb.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-02-03 22:35:50', '2026-02-19 03:10:14'),
(271, 122, 'Why does it cost $40,000 to climb Mount Everest?', '<p>It costs $40, 000 to climb Mount Everest because of the permits fees fixed by the Nepal government, Sherpa guides, oxygen cylinders, foods, accommodations, gears and equipment and many more.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-02-03 22:35:50', '2026-02-19 03:10:14'),
(272, 228, 'Where is Mount Makalu located?', 'Mount Makalu is located in eastern Nepal near the Nepal–Tibet border, within the Makalu Barun National Park. It lies in a remote Himalayan region close to the Everest area, known for its untouched wilderness.', 1, 1, '2026-02-03 22:49:22', '2026-02-03 22:49:22'),
(273, 228, 'How high is Mount Makalu?', 'Mount Makalu stands at 8,485 meters (27,838 feet), making it the fifth-highest mountain in the world. Its sharp pyramid summit makes it one of the most striking peaks in the Himalayas.', 2, 1, '2026-02-03 22:49:22', '2026-02-03 22:49:22'),
(274, 228, 'How difficult is the Makalu Expedition?', 'Makalu is considered one of the most challenging 8,000-meter expeditions due to steep technical sections and extreme altitude. It is recommended only for climbers with strong high-altitude and mountaineering experience.', 3, 1, '2026-02-03 22:49:22', '2026-02-03 22:49:22'),
(275, 228, 'How long does the Makalu Expedition take?', 'The Makalu Expedition typically takes around 50 to 65 days, including trekking, acclimatization, and summit attempts. The exact duration depends on weather conditions and team progress.', 4, 1, '2026-02-03 22:49:22', '2026-02-03 22:49:22'),
(276, 228, 'What is the best season for Makalu climbing?', 'The best time to climb Makalu is during the spring season (April to May) when weather is more stable. Autumn (September to October) is also possible but tends to be colder.', 5, 1, '2026-02-03 22:49:22', '2026-02-03 22:49:22'),
(277, 228, 'What route is used to climb Makalu?', 'The most common route is the Southeast Ridge, which involves glacier travel, steep snow slopes, and technical summit climbing. Fixed ropes are usually required for safety on higher sections.', 6, 1, '2026-02-03 22:49:22', '2026-02-03 22:49:22'),
(278, 228, 'Do I need previous climbing experience for Makalu?', 'Yes, climbers should have prior experience on peaks above 6,500–7,000 meters and strong technical skills. Makalu is not suitable for beginners because of its demanding terrain and altitude.', 7, 1, '2026-02-03 22:49:22', '2026-02-03 22:49:22'),
(279, 228, 'What permits are required for Makalu Expedition?', 'Climbers need a Makalu climbing permit issued by the Nepal government along with Makalu Barun National Park entry permits. Most expedition operators handle all necessary documentation.', 8, 1, '2026-02-03 22:49:22', '2026-02-03 22:49:22'),
(280, 228, 'How do you reach Makalu Base Camp?', 'The journey usually starts with a flight from Kathmandu to Tumlingtar, followed by a drive and multi-day trek through remote valleys. Reaching base camp generally takes about 8 to 10 days of trekking.', 9, 1, '2026-02-03 22:49:22', '2026-02-03 22:49:22'),
(281, 228, 'Is oxygen used on Makalu?', 'Supplementary oxygen is optional but commonly used during summit attempts due to the extreme altitude. Climbing without oxygen is possible but significantly more difficult and risky.', 10, 1, '2026-02-03 22:49:22', '2026-02-03 22:49:22'),
(282, 228, 'How much does the Makalu Expedition cost?', 'The cost of a Makalu Expedition generally ranges from USD 18,000 to 35,000 or more depending on support level, logistics, oxygen, and Sherpa assistance. Prices vary based on services included in the package.', 11, 1, '2026-02-03 22:49:22', '2026-02-03 22:49:22'),
(283, 228, 'What are the main risks during the expedition?', 'Major risks include altitude sickness, avalanches, extreme cold, crevasses, and sudden weather changes. Proper acclimatization and experienced guides are essential for safety.', 12, 1, '2026-02-03 22:49:22', '2026-02-03 22:49:22'),
(284, 228, 'Can rescue be done during Makalu Expedition?', 'Rescue is possible but challenging because Makalu is very remote. Helicopter evacuation may work in lower regions, but above base camp, rescue becomes extremely difficult.', 13, 1, '2026-02-03 22:49:22', '2026-02-03 22:49:22'),
(285, 229, 'Where is Mount Dhaulagiri located?', 'Mount Dhaulagiri is located in western Nepal, in the Dhaulagiri Himal range, northwest of Pokhara. It stands in a remote region surrounded by deep valleys, glaciers, and some of the most dramatic landscapes in the Himalayas.', 1, 1, '2026-02-03 22:51:56', '2026-02-03 22:51:56'),
(286, 229, 'How high is Mount Dhaulagiri?', 'Mount Dhaulagiri reaches an elevation of 8,167 meters (26,795 feet), making it the seventh-highest mountain in the world. Its massive snowy face and isolated position make it one of Nepal’s most impressive peaks.', 2, 1, '2026-02-03 22:51:56', '2026-02-03 22:51:56'),
(287, 229, 'How difficult is the Dhaulagiri Expedition?', 'The Dhaulagiri Expedition is considered extremely challenging due to steep climbing sections, high avalanche risk, and unpredictable weather. It is recommended only for experienced mountaineers with prior high-altitude expedition background.', 3, 1, '2026-02-03 22:51:56', '2026-02-03 22:51:56'),
(288, 229, 'How long does the Dhaulagiri Expedition take?', 'A typical Dhaulagiri Expedition takes around 50 to 60 days, including trekking to base camp, acclimatization rotations, and the summit push. The schedule may vary depending on weather and route conditions.', 4, 1, '2026-02-03 22:51:56', '2026-02-03 22:51:56'),
(289, 229, 'What is the best season to climb Dhaulagiri?', 'The best season for climbing Dhaulagiri is spring (April to May) when the weather is relatively stable. Autumn (September to October) is also possible but colder and less commonly attempted.', 5, 1, '2026-02-03 22:51:56', '2026-02-03 22:51:56'),
(290, 229, 'What is the normal route for the Dhaulagiri climb?', 'The standard route is the Northeast Ridge, which involves glacier crossings, steep ice slopes, and technical climbing above high camps. Fixed ropes and strong teamwork are essential on the upper mountain.', 6, 1, '2026-02-03 22:51:56', '2026-02-03 22:51:56'),
(291, 229, 'Do I need previous climbing experience for Dhaulagiri?', 'Yes, climbers must have significant experience on peaks above 6,500–7,000 meters and be comfortable with technical ice and snow climbing. Dhaulagiri is not suitable for first-time 8,000-meter climbers.', 7, 1, '2026-02-03 22:51:56', '2026-02-03 22:51:56'),
(292, 229, 'What permits are required for the Dhaulagiri Expedition?', 'Climbers need a Dhaulagiri climbing permit issued by the Government of Nepal along with trekking permits for the approach route. Expedition operators usually manage all necessary paperwork and logistics.', 8, 1, '2026-02-03 22:51:56', '2026-02-03 22:51:56'),
(293, 229, 'How do you reach Dhaulagiri Base Camp?', 'The expedition begins with travel from Kathmandu to Pokhara, followed by a drive to the trekking trailhead. The trek to Dhaulagiri Base Camp usually takes about 8 to 10 days through remote villages and glacial valleys.', 9, 1, '2026-02-03 22:51:56', '2026-02-03 22:51:56'),
(294, 229, 'Is supplementary oxygen used on Dhaulagiri?', 'Supplementary oxygen is optional but often used during the summit attempt because of the extreme altitude and difficult conditions. Some elite climbers choose to climb without oxygen, but it increases the challenge significantly.', 10, 1, '2026-02-03 22:51:56', '2026-02-03 22:51:56'),
(295, 229, 'How much does the Dhaulagiri Expedition cost?', 'The cost generally ranges from USD 20,000 to 40,000 or more depending on group size, Sherpa support, oxygen services, and expedition logistics. Full-service packages are more expensive but provide higher safety and comfort.', 11, 1, '2026-02-03 22:51:56', '2026-02-03 22:51:56'),
(296, 229, 'What are the main risks during the expedition?', 'Major risks include altitude sickness, avalanches, crevasses, frostbite, and sudden storms. Proper acclimatization, expert guides, and strong preparation are critical for a safe climb.', 12, 1, '2026-02-03 22:51:56', '2026-02-03 22:51:56'),
(297, 229, 'Is rescue possible during the Dhaulagiri Expedition?', 'Rescue is possible but difficult because of the remote terrain and technical nature of the mountain. Helicopter evacuation may work from lower camps, but above base camp rescue becomes very limited.', 13, 1, '2026-02-03 22:51:56', '2026-02-03 22:51:56'),
(298, 229, 'Why is Dhaulagiri considered special among 8,000m peaks?', 'Dhaulagiri is known for its isolation, steep faces, and serious expedition atmosphere compared to more commercial peaks. It offers a true high-altitude adventure for climbers seeking one of Nepal’s toughest challenges.', 14, 1, '2026-02-03 22:51:56', '2026-02-03 22:51:56'),
(299, 243, 'What is the difficulty level of Island Peak?', 'Island Peak is considered a moderate technical climb, suitable for climbers with good fitness and basic trekking experience. It requires some technical skills, such as using crampons, ice axes, and ropes, but it is achievable for beginners who have trained properly and are guided by experienced Sherpas.', 1, 1, '2026-02-03 23:01:12', '2026-02-03 23:01:12'),
(300, 243, 'Do I need prior mountaineering experience to climb Island Peak?', 'While prior climbing experience is helpful, it is not mandatory. The climb is designed to teach basic mountaineering skills, including glacier travel, rope techniques, and high-altitude trekking, making it ideal for novice climbers preparing for higher peaks in the future.', 2, 1, '2026-02-03 23:01:12', '2026-02-03 23:01:12'),
(301, 243, 'What is the best time to climb Island Peak?', 'The pre-monsoon (March to May) and post-monsoon (late September to November) seasons are the most suitable. These periods offer stable weather, clear skies, and stunning views of surrounding peaks like Everest, Lhotse, and Makalu. Monsoon and winter months are generally not recommended due to heavy snowfall and harsh conditions.', 3, 1, '2026-02-03 23:01:12', '2026-02-03 23:01:12');
INSERT INTO `cl_trip_faqs` (`id`, `trip_detail_id`, `title`, `content`, `ordering`, `status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(302, 243, 'What permits are required for Island Peak?', 'Climbers need a Peak Climbing Permit from the Nepal Ministry of Tourism, along with a Sagarmatha National Park Permit and a TIMS card. Your trekking agency or guide usually handles the permit process to ensure compliance and smooth access to the region.', 4, 1, '2026-02-03 23:01:12', '2026-02-03 23:01:12'),
(303, 243, 'What kind of training or preparation is needed?', 'Climbers should focus on cardiovascular fitness, strength training, and endurance trekking. Acclimatization hikes are recommended before the expedition, and basic knowledge of climbing techniques is useful. Mental preparation for early starts, cold nights, and high-altitude conditions is equally important.', 5, 1, '2026-02-03 23:01:12', '2026-02-03 23:01:12'),
(304, 243, 'What equipment do I need for the climb?', 'Essential items include mountaineering boots, crampons, ice axe, harness, helmet, gloves, down jacket, and sleeping bag. Most technical gear, ropes, and safety equipment are usually provided by the expedition team, but personal clothing and trekking essentials must be arranged by the climber.', 6, 1, '2026-02-03 23:01:12', '2026-02-03 23:01:12'),
(305, 243, 'How long does the Island Peak climb take?', 'The typical expedition lasts 16 days, combining trekking to Everest Base Camp and acclimatization with the technical climb to Island Peak. Summit day starts early (around midnight) to take advantage of stable weather and minimal winds.', 7, 1, '2026-02-03 23:01:12', '2026-02-03 23:01:12'),
(306, 243, 'Is it safe to climb Island Peak?', 'When properly guided and with appropriate acclimatization, Island Peak is considered a safe climb. Experienced Sherpa guides lead every step, monitor health conditions, and provide emergency support. However, high-altitude risks like altitude sickness, frostbite, and weather changes are always present, so vigilance is required.', 8, 1, '2026-02-03 23:01:12', '2026-02-03 23:01:12'),
(307, 243, 'What can I expect from the summit?', 'From the Island Peak summit (6,189 m), climbers enjoy 360-degree panoramic views of the Himalayas, including Everest, Lhotse, Makalu, Nuptse, and Ama Dablam, along with glaciers, alpine valleys, and the surrounding Khumbu region. It’s a rewarding experience and a perfect introduction to climbing high-altitude peaks, including the world’s 8000m giants.', 9, 1, '2026-02-03 23:01:12', '2026-02-03 23:01:12'),
(308, 243, 'What is the difficulty level of Island Peak?', 'Island Peak is considered a moderate technical climb, suitable for climbers with good fitness and basic trekking experience. It requires some technical skills, such as using crampons, ice axes, and ropes, but it is achievable for beginners who have trained properly and are guided by experienced Sherpas.', 1, 1, '2026-02-03 23:01:19', '2026-02-03 23:01:19'),
(309, 243, 'Do I need prior mountaineering experience to climb Island Peak?', 'While prior climbing experience is helpful, it is not mandatory. The climb is designed to teach basic mountaineering skills, including glacier travel, rope techniques, and high-altitude trekking, making it ideal for novice climbers preparing for higher peaks in the future.', 2, 1, '2026-02-03 23:01:19', '2026-02-03 23:01:19'),
(310, 243, 'What is the best time to climb Island Peak?', 'The pre-monsoon (March to May) and post-monsoon (late September to November) seasons are the most suitable. These periods offer stable weather, clear skies, and stunning views of surrounding peaks like Everest, Lhotse, and Makalu. Monsoon and winter months are generally not recommended due to heavy snowfall and harsh conditions.', 3, 1, '2026-02-03 23:01:19', '2026-02-03 23:01:19'),
(311, 243, 'What permits are required for Island Peak?', 'Climbers need a Peak Climbing Permit from the Nepal Ministry of Tourism, along with a Sagarmatha National Park Permit and a TIMS card. Your trekking agency or guide usually handles the permit process to ensure compliance and smooth access to the region.', 4, 1, '2026-02-03 23:01:19', '2026-02-03 23:01:19'),
(312, 243, 'What kind of training or preparation is needed?', 'Climbers should focus on cardiovascular fitness, strength training, and endurance trekking. Acclimatization hikes are recommended before the expedition, and basic knowledge of climbing techniques is useful. Mental preparation for early starts, cold nights, and high-altitude conditions is equally important.', 5, 1, '2026-02-03 23:01:19', '2026-02-03 23:01:19'),
(313, 243, 'What equipment do I need for the climb?', 'Essential items include mountaineering boots, crampons, ice axe, harness, helmet, gloves, down jacket, and sleeping bag. Most technical gear, ropes, and safety equipment are usually provided by the expedition team, but personal clothing and trekking essentials must be arranged by the climber.', 6, 1, '2026-02-03 23:01:19', '2026-02-03 23:01:19'),
(314, 243, 'How long does the Island Peak climb take?', 'The typical expedition lasts 16 days, combining trekking to Everest Base Camp and acclimatization with the technical climb to Island Peak. Summit day starts early (around midnight) to take advantage of stable weather and minimal winds.', 7, 1, '2026-02-03 23:01:19', '2026-02-03 23:01:19'),
(315, 243, 'Is it safe to climb Island Peak?', 'When properly guided and with appropriate acclimatization, Island Peak is considered a safe climb. Experienced Sherpa guides lead every step, monitor health conditions, and provide emergency support. However, high-altitude risks like altitude sickness, frostbite, and weather changes are always present, so vigilance is required.', 8, 1, '2026-02-03 23:01:19', '2026-02-03 23:01:19'),
(316, 243, 'What can I expect from the summit?', 'From the Island Peak summit (6,189 m), climbers enjoy 360-degree panoramic views of the Himalayas, including Everest, Lhotse, Makalu, Nuptse, and Ama Dablam, along with glaciers, alpine valleys, and the surrounding Khumbu region. It’s a rewarding experience and a perfect introduction to climbing high-altitude peaks, including the world’s 8000m giants.', 9, 1, '2026-02-03 23:01:19', '2026-02-03 23:01:19'),
(317, 227, 'Where is Mount Lhotse located?', 'Mount Lhotse is located in the Everest region of Nepal, near the Nepal–Tibet border. It stands right beside Mount Everest and shares the same approach route through the famous Khumbu Valley.', 1, 1, '2026-02-03 23:12:37', '2026-02-03 23:12:37'),
(318, 227, 'How high is Mount Lhotse?', 'Mount Lhotse rises to an elevation of 8,516 meters (27,940 feet), making it the fourth-highest mountain in the world. It is known for its dramatic south face, one of the steepest and most impressive mountain walls on Earth.', 2, 1, '2026-02-03 23:12:37', '2026-02-03 23:12:37'),
(319, 227, 'How difficult is the Lhotse Expedition?', 'The Lhotse Expedition is extremely challenging due to high altitude, technical climbing sections, and harsh weather conditions. Although the route follows Everest up to Camp 3, the final ascent to the summit is steep and demanding.', 3, 1, '2026-02-03 23:12:37', '2026-02-03 23:12:37'),
(320, 227, 'How long does the Lhotse Expedition take?', 'A typical Lhotse Expedition takes around 45 to 60 days, including trekking, acclimatization, and summit attempts. The duration depends heavily on weather windows and individual climbing pace.', 4, 1, '2026-02-03 23:12:37', '2026-02-03 23:12:37'),
(321, 227, 'What is the best season to climb Lhotse?', 'The best season for climbing Lhotse is spring (April to May), when conditions are most stable in the Everest region. Autumn (September to October) is also possible but less common for summit attempts.', 5, 1, '2026-02-03 23:12:37', '2026-02-03 23:12:37'),
(322, 227, 'What route is used to climb Mount Lhotse?', 'The standard route is via the South Col route, following the Everest Base Camp trail and climbing through the Khumbu Icefall. From Camp 3, climbers separate from the Everest route and ascend the steep Lhotse Couloir to reach the summit.', 6, 1, '2026-02-03 23:12:37', '2026-02-03 23:12:37'),
(323, 227, 'Do I need previous experience to climb Lhotse?', 'Yes, climbers should have strong high-altitude mountaineering experience and prior climbs above 7,000 meters. Lhotse is not suitable for beginners because of its technical terrain and extreme altitude risks.', 7, 1, '2026-02-03 23:12:37', '2026-02-03 23:12:37'),
(324, 227, 'What permits are required for the Lhotse Expedition?', 'Climbers need a Lhotse climbing permit issued by the Government of Nepal, along with Sagarmatha National Park entry permits. Most expedition operators handle all permit arrangements and official paperwork.', 8, 1, '2026-02-03 23:12:37', '2026-02-03 23:12:37'),
(325, 227, 'How do you reach Lhotse Base Camp?', 'Lhotse Base Camp is reached by flying from Kathmandu to Lukla, followed by a trek through Namche Bazaar, Tengboche, and Gorak Shep. The trek usually takes about 8 to 10 days before arriving at base camp.', 9, 1, '2026-02-03 23:12:37', '2026-02-03 23:12:37'),
(326, 227, 'Is oxygen used during the Lhotse Expedition?', 'Yes, supplementary oxygen is commonly used above Camp 3 due to the extreme altitude. While climbing without oxygen is possible, it is much more difficult and only attempted by highly experienced climbers.', 10, 1, '2026-02-03 23:12:37', '2026-02-03 23:12:37'),
(327, 227, 'How much does the Lhotse Expedition cost?', 'The cost of a Lhotse Expedition generally ranges from USD 25,000 to 45,000 or more depending on support services, oxygen supply, Sherpa assistance, and logistics. Prices vary widely based on expedition style and operator quality.', 11, 1, '2026-02-03 23:12:37', '2026-02-03 23:12:37'),
(328, 227, 'What are the main risks during the Lhotse climb?', 'Major risks include altitude sickness, icefall dangers, avalanches, frostbite, and sudden Himalayan storms. Proper acclimatization and experienced guides are essential for a safe and successful ascent.', 12, 1, '2026-02-03 23:12:37', '2026-02-03 23:12:37'),
(329, 227, 'Is rescue possible on Mount Lhotse?', 'Rescue is possible in the lower parts of the Everest region through helicopter evacuation, especially from base camp. However, above higher camps, rescue becomes extremely difficult due to technical terrain and altitude.', 13, 1, '2026-02-03 23:12:37', '2026-02-03 23:12:37'),
(330, 227, 'Why choose Lhotse instead of Everest?', 'Lhotse offers a slightly less crowded but equally thrilling 8,000-meter expedition experience. It is ideal for climbers seeking a world-class Himalayan summit with a more technical and serious final climb than Everest.', 14, 1, '2026-02-03 23:12:37', '2026-02-03 23:12:37'),
(331, 241, 'Where is ama Dablam located?', 'The Ama Dablam peak is located in the Khumbu region of eastern Nepal inside the Sagarmatha National park. It is situated to the south of the mount Everest and can be seen during the walk from the Debuche.', 1, 1, '2026-02-04 00:39:59', '2026-02-04 00:39:59'),
(332, 241, 'What does ama Dablam mean?', 'Ama Dablam means mothers necklace which translate as: Ama means mother and Dablam means double pendant worn by sherpa women', 2, 1, '2026-02-04 00:39:59', '2026-02-04 00:39:59'),
(333, 241, 'Is ama Dablam harder than Everest?', 'Technically yes, Ama Dablam is harder than Everest for its steep rock climbing, exposed ridges, mixed terrains but the altitude is only 6,812 meters (22,349 feet) however Everest altitude is above 8000 meter which is why its more difficult and needs self discipline, endurance, and long expeditions periods.', 3, 1, '2026-02-04 00:39:59', '2026-02-04 00:39:59'),
(334, 241, 'How long does it take to climb ama Dablam?', 'It generally takes 25 to 30 days to climb Ama Dablam including the arrival in Kathmandu and departure.', 4, 1, '2026-02-04 00:40:00', '2026-02-04 00:40:00'),
(335, 241, 'How hard is it to climb ama Dablam?', 'Ama Dablam is rated as the D(Difficult) to TD (very difficult) considering the steep ice walls, narrow exposed ridges, rock climbing up to UIAA grade IV and heavy reliance on the fixed ropes.', 5, 1, '2026-02-04 00:40:00', '2026-02-04 00:40:00'),
(336, 241, 'Can a beginner climb Ama Dablam?', 'No, a beginner cannot climb Ama Dablam climbing the peak requires the previous trekking experience, along with the knowledge of the ice climbing, rope work, crampons, and ascenders.', 6, 1, '2026-02-04 00:40:00', '2026-02-04 00:40:00'),
(337, 241, 'Do you need oxygen to climb ama Dablam?', 'No, you will not need oxygen to climb Ama Dablam as the peak is below than the 7000 meters. Most of the climbers summit the peak without any oxygen.', 7, 1, '2026-02-04 00:40:00', '2026-02-04 00:40:00'),
(338, 241, 'How to prepare for Ama Dablam?', 'You shall start your preparation before by trekking in the mountains, hiking, and then learning about the rope climbing, by doing technical climbing training, by making yourself physically and mentally fit.', 8, 1, '2026-02-04 00:40:00', '2026-02-04 00:40:00'),
(339, 241, 'What is the difficulty level of the Ama Dablam trek?', 'The difficulty level of the Ama Dablam peak is moderate to challenging depending upon your previous experience and physical fitness level.', 9, 1, '2026-02-04 00:40:00', '2026-02-04 00:40:00'),
(340, 241, 'What is the hardest part of Ama Dablam?', 'The hardest part of Ama Dablam is yellow tower which is steep rock climbing, grey tower which is exposed mixed climbing, and the summit ridge which is narrow knife ridge.', 10, 1, '2026-02-04 00:40:00', '2026-02-04 00:40:00'),
(341, 241, 'What are the common mistakes in mountain climbers?', 'The common mistakes in mountain climbers are poor acclimatization, not understanding technical difficulty, carrying excessive weight, inadequate training, ignoring the weather windows and not listening to the sherpa guides.', 11, 1, '2026-02-04 00:40:00', '2026-02-04 00:40:00'),
(342, 241, 'What is the best season to climb Ama Dablam?', 'The best season to climb Ama Dablam is during the autumn which is September to November due to the stable weather and spring which is from march to may for its warm temperatures', 12, 1, '2026-02-04 00:40:00', '2026-02-04 00:40:00'),
(343, 241, 'What is the cost to climb Ama Dablam?', 'The cost to climb Ama Dablam is around 9500 USD to 15,000 USD depending upon various factors like the seasons you are choosing, companies you are selecting, level of service, logistics and supports and many more.', 13, 1, '2026-02-04 00:40:00', '2026-02-04 00:40:00'),
(344, 241, 'What is the Packing list for the Ama Dablam?', 'The packing list for the Ama Dablam depends upon the various factors such as the seasons and company logistics. In average you will need double or triple layer high altitude boots, crampons and axes, climbing harness, helmet, ascenders, down suit and down jackets, technical gloves and mittens, personal medical kit, headlamps and many more.', 14, 1, '2026-02-04 00:40:00', '2026-02-04 00:40:00'),
(345, 241, 'What permits are required for the Ama Dablam summit?', 'You will need three permits for the Ama Dablam summit which are: Ama Dablam Climbing Permit Sagarmatha National Park Permit Khumbu Rural Municipality Permit', 15, 1, '2026-02-04 00:40:00', '2026-02-04 00:40:00'),
(346, 241, 'Note from Dhirendra', 'I could write about the topics below in this package. However, from both Google’s point of view and the user’s point of view, it is important to explain these topics in detail, not just as a short overview. Detailed information helps users understand better and builds trust, which is why separate articles can also be created for each topic. I have provided the short FAQ format for same topic as well to be featured in the google snippet.  The grammar used by me is already correct and natural for both users and Google. Making too many grammatical changes using AI tools may reduce the original feel and credibility of the content. Important topics to explain in detail: Best time to do the Ama Dablam Expedition? Packing list for the Ama Dablam Expedition? How to prepare for the Ama Dablam Expedition? Cost of the Ama Dablam Expedition How to reach the Ama Dablam expedition starting point from Kathmandu? What are the permits required for Ama Dablam Expeditions?', 16, 1, '2026-02-04 00:40:00', '2026-02-04 00:42:27'),
(350, 226, 'What is the best time to climb Kanchenjunga?', 'The ideal time for a Kanchenjunga expedition is during the pre-monsoon season from April to May and the post-monsoon season from late September to November. During these periods, the weather is relatively stable, offering clearer skies, less snowfall, and safer climbing conditions compared to winter or monsoon months.', 1, 1, '2026-02-04 01:18:24', '2026-02-04 01:18:24'),
(351, 226, 'How difficult is the Kanchenjunga climb?', 'Kanchenjunga is one of the most challenging 8,000-meter peaks in the world. It requires advanced mountaineering experience, excellent physical fitness, and prior high-altitude climbing experience due to its technical routes and unpredictable weather conditions.', 2, 1, '2026-02-04 01:18:24', '2026-02-04 01:18:24'),
(352, 226, 'Do I need prior high-altitude climbing experience?', 'Yes, prior experience in climbing high-altitude peaks above 6,000–7,000 meters is highly recommended. Kanchenjunga’s extreme altitude, technical ice and rock sections, and prolonged exposure make it unsuitable for first-time climbers.', 3, 1, '2026-02-04 01:18:24', '2026-02-04 01:18:24'),
(353, 226, 'How long does a typical Kanchenjunga expedition take?', 'A full Kanchenjunga expedition usually lasts around 50 to 60 days, including trekking to base camp, acclimatization, and summit attempts. The approach itself is remote and requires several days of trekking through rugged terrain, making it a long and physically demanding expedition.', 4, 1, '2026-02-04 01:18:24', '2026-02-04 01:18:24'),
(354, 226, 'What permits are required to climb Kanchenjunga?', 'Climbers need a Kanchenjunga climbing permit issued by the Government of Nepal, along with trekking permits for the surrounding areas. These permits ensure legal access and contribute to conservation and local development in the region.', 5, 1, '2026-02-04 01:18:24', '2026-02-04 01:18:24'),
(355, 226, 'Is it necessary to hire a guide or a Sherpa team?', 'Yes, hiring experienced guides and high-altitude Sherpa support is highly recommended for safety, route navigation, and carrying equipment. Most climbers rely on professional teams for setting up camps, fixing ropes, and providing medical and logistical assistance.', 6, 1, '2026-02-04 01:18:24', '2026-02-04 01:18:24'),
(356, 226, 'What equipment is essential for the expedition?', 'Climbers need specialized high-altitude climbing gear including insulated clothing, crampons, ice axes, tents, sleeping bags rated for extreme cold, and oxygen systems. Proper gear is critical for survival and safety at extreme altitudes.', 7, 1, '2026-02-04 01:18:25', '2026-02-04 01:18:25'),
(357, 226, 'What are the main risks associated with Kanchenjunga expeditions?', 'The primary risks include avalanches, crevasse falls, altitude sickness, extreme cold, and unpredictable weather changes. Careful planning, proper acclimatization, and experienced guides are essential to mitigate these risks.', 8, 1, '2026-02-04 01:18:25', '2026-02-04 01:18:25'),
(358, 226, 'How physically fit should I be for the expedition?', 'A high level of cardiovascular endurance, strength, and stamina is required for Kanchenjunga. Training should include long-duration trekking with heavy loads, mountaineering exercises, and acclimatization to high-altitude conditions prior to the expedition.', 9, 1, '2026-02-04 01:18:25', '2026-02-04 01:18:25'),
(359, 226, 'Can anyone join a Kanchenjunga expedition?', 'Due to its extreme difficulty, Kanchenjunga expeditions are not suitable for casual hikers or first-time climbers. Only highly experienced mountaineers with proper training, previous high-altitude experience, and strong physical fitness should attempt this climb.', 10, 1, '2026-02-04 01:18:25', '2026-02-04 01:18:25'),
(360, 231, 'What is the best time to climb Mount Manaslu?', 'The best climbing season is spring (April to May) and autumn (September to November). During these months, the weather is more stable, with clearer skies and lower chances of heavy snow or monsoon rains, making it safer and more enjoyable for the expedition.', 1, 1, '2026-02-04 01:24:26', '2026-02-04 01:24:26'),
(361, 231, 'Do I need prior mountaineering experience to climb Manaslu?', 'Yes, basic high-altitude climbing experience is highly recommended. Manaslu is an 8,163-meter peak, and climbers should have prior experience with high-altitude trekking, glacier travel, and technical skills like using crampons and ice axes.', 2, 1, '2026-02-04 01:24:26', '2026-02-04 01:24:26'),
(362, 231, 'How difficult is climbing Mount Manaslu?', 'Manaslu is considered a challenging expedition. The climb involves steep snow and ice slopes, glacier crossings, and high-altitude risks. Proper acclimatization, physical fitness, and professional support are essential for safety and success.', 3, 1, '2026-02-04 01:24:26', '2026-02-04 01:24:26'),
(363, 231, 'What permits are required for climbing Manaslu?', 'Climbers must obtain the Manaslu Restricted Area Permit (RAP), issued by the Nepal government. Additionally, trekking permits for the Manaslu region and local taxes are required. Expedition operators usually arrange these permits in advance.', 4, 1, '2026-02-04 01:24:26', '2026-02-04 01:24:26'),
(364, 231, 'How long does the Manaslu expedition take?', 'A full expedition, including trekking, acclimatization, and summit rotation, typically lasts 35 days. This allows for proper acclimatization and ensures a safer summit attempt.', 5, 1, '2026-02-04 01:24:26', '2026-02-04 01:24:26'),
(365, 231, 'What level of fitness is required?', 'Climbers should be in excellent physical condition, with strong endurance and prior experience in trekking at high altitudes. Training before the expedition, including long hikes and cardio exercises, is highly recommended.', 6, 1, '2026-02-04 01:24:26', '2026-02-04 01:24:26'),
(366, 231, 'Is it safe to climb Manaslu?', 'While the expedition is professionally supported, climbing Manaslu carries inherent risks such as altitude sickness, avalanches, and harsh weather. Following acclimatization schedules, using guides, and being prepared with proper gear greatly reduce these risks.', 7, 1, '2026-02-04 01:24:26', '2026-02-04 01:24:26'),
(367, 231, 'Do I need a guide or Sherpa support?', 'Yes, professional guides, Sherpas, and support staff are essential for safety, route fixing, and logistics. They also carry equipment, set up camps, and assist with high-altitude challenges.', 8, 1, '2026-02-04 01:24:26', '2026-02-04 01:24:26'),
(368, 231, 'What kind of gear is required?', 'Essential gear includes high-altitude boots, down jacket, insulated sleeping bag, crampons, ice axe, harness, helmet, and layered clothing. A detailed gear list is usually provided by your expedition operator.', 9, 1, '2026-02-04 01:24:26', '2026-02-04 01:24:26'),
(369, 231, 'Can anyone attempt the summit?', 'Due to extreme altitude, technical climbing, and weather conditions, only experienced climbers in excellent health should attempt the summit. Proper acclimatization, training, and professional guidance are mandatory.', 10, 1, '2026-02-04 01:24:26', '2026-02-04 01:24:26'),
(370, 277, 'Why should I choose the North Face route from Tibet?', 'The North Face route offers a less crowded and more accessible path to Everest Base Camp and the summit. It provides spectacular views of the Rongbuk Glacier and the North Face itself, while being strategically advantageous for acclimatization and logistics compared to the South Col route in Nepal.', 1, 1, '2026-02-06 22:28:00', '2026-02-06 22:28:00'),
(371, 277, 'What is the best season to climb Everest from the North Face?', 'The spring season (April to May) is considered the best time for Everest expeditions from Tibet. During this period, the weather is relatively stable, temperatures are moderate, and the climbing conditions are optimal for a successful summit attempt.', 2, 1, '2026-02-06 22:28:00', '2026-02-06 22:28:00'),
(372, 277, 'What permits are required for the expedition?', 'Climbers need a Tibet Travel Permit, an Everest Climbing Permit, and a liaison officer permit. Summit 8000 arranges all the necessary paperwork as part of the expedition package, ensuring a smooth process.', 3, 1, '2026-02-06 22:28:00', '2026-02-06 22:28:00'),
(373, 277, 'How physically fit do I need to be?', 'Climbers should have excellent physical fitness and prior high-altitude trekking or mountaineering experience. Training for cardiovascular endurance, strength, and stamina is essential, as the expedition involves long days at extreme altitudes.', 4, 1, '2026-02-06 22:28:00', '2026-02-06 22:28:00'),
(374, 277, 'How long does the expedition take?', 'The full expedition, including acclimatization, travel, climbing, and return, typically lasts about 60 days, allowing sufficient time for gradual acclimatization and a safe summit attempt', 5, 1, '2026-02-06 22:28:00', '2026-02-06 22:28:00'),
(375, 277, 'Is supplemental oxygen required?', 'Yes, supplemental oxygen is recommended for the summit push. Summit 8000 provides high-quality oxygen cylinders and masks to ensure safety during the high-altitude climb.', 6, 1, '2026-02-06 22:28:00', '2026-02-06 22:28:00'),
(376, 277, 'What kind of support is provided during the climb?', 'The expedition includes professional guides, Sherpas, Base Camp support staff, high-altitude cooking teams, communication devices, medical facilities, and full logistical support throughout the journey.', 7, 1, '2026-02-06 22:28:00', '2026-02-06 22:28:00'),
(377, 277, 'What are the accommodation arrangements?', 'Accommodation is provided in Kathmandu hotels, local hotels along the overland route in Tibet, and well-equipped tents at Base Camp. Higher camps include basic tents with shared cooking and sleeping facilities.', 8, 1, '2026-02-06 22:28:00', '2026-02-06 22:28:00'),
(378, 277, 'How is safety ensured during the expedition?', 'Safety is prioritized through careful acclimatization schedules, experienced guides, high-altitude medical monitoring, communication devices, and emergency evacuation plans. Climbers are closely monitored throughout the expedition.', 9, 1, '2026-02-06 22:28:00', '2026-02-06 22:28:00'),
(379, 277, 'Are there other expeditions I can combine with Everest?', 'Yes, climbers can explore related Himalayan peaks such as Cho Oyu, Lhotse, Shishapangma, and Makalu. These expeditions complement the Everest climb and offer additional mountaineering experiences in the region.', 10, 1, '2026-02-06 22:28:00', '2026-02-06 22:28:00'),
(380, 280, 'test text', '<p>test text</p>', 1, 1, '2026-02-19 15:20:15', '2026-02-19 17:56:52'),
(381, 280, 'test text', '<p>test text</p>', 1, 1, '2026-02-19 15:20:15', '2026-02-19 17:56:52'),
(382, 278, 'Why Shall you do the Baruntse expeditions?', '<p>You shall do the Baruntse expeditions because it is one of the most beautiful climbing peaks that takes you at an altitude of the 7,129m above sea level along with the one of the most beautiful and less explored places such as the Barun valley and the Hinku Valley.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-02-19 22:50:37', '2026-02-19 23:04:30'),
(383, 278, 'What are the best seasons to climb the Baruntse in Nepal?', '<p>The best seasons to climb the Baruntse in Nepal is during the month of the autumn which lies in the September to November and the Spring which is from the March to May.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-02-19 22:50:37', '2026-02-19 23:04:30'),
(384, 278, 'What is the difficulty level of the Baruntse peak climbing?', '<p>The difficulty level of the Baruntse peak climbing is challenging alpine expeditions. You will need to have the prior climbing and trekking experience to climb summit it.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-02-19 22:50:37', '2026-02-19 23:04:30'),
(385, 278, 'How long are the expeditions?', '<p>The Baruntse expeditions can be of 30 to 40 days depending upon the agencies in our case summit 8000 we have organized these expeditions of 32 days.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-02-19 22:50:37', '2026-02-19 23:04:30'),
(386, 278, 'What kind of training is recommended before the expedition?', '<p>You will need to have the Cardiovascular fitness (running, hiking, cycling), Strength training for legs and core, Endurance trekking with a backpack (15–20kg) and the technical climbing practice (ice climbing, fixed rope training).</p>', 5, 1, '2026-02-19 22:50:37', '2026-02-19 23:04:30'),
(387, 278, 'What permits are required for Baruntse peak climbing?', '<p>You will need to have the Baruntse climbing permit, Makalu Barun national park permit, and the Hinku valley trek permit to climb the peak.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-02-19 22:50:37', '2026-02-19 23:04:30'),
(388, 278, 'What are the main challenges on Baruntse?', '<p>The main challenges of the Baruntse are that you will face the high altitude climb where the air is very thin, you will need to do the technical climbing, face the unpredictable weather and the each step will test your endurance and the physical strength.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-02-19 22:50:37', '2026-02-19 23:04:30'),
(389, 250, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2026-02-22 04:13:01', '2026-02-22 04:13:01'),
(390, 282, 'How much does the Everest expedition cost?', '<p>The Everest expeditions cost 40,000 USD to 200,000 USD, depending on your packages, whether you are choosing the standard expeditions options, budget options, or the luxury options. The goal of the package is to reach the top of the peak, but how you reach it and your comfort level, decide the costs.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-02-24 03:35:55', '2026-02-24 03:49:07'),
(391, 282, 'What is the 7000m rule for Everest?', '<p>The 7000m rule for Everest is that the climbers who want to summit the mountain must have prior climbing experience on Nepal’s 7000 m peaks, so that they can easily complete their summit.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-02-24 03:35:55', '2026-02-24 03:49:07'),
(392, 282, 'Why can\'t you climb Everest in the summer?', '<p>You cannot climb Everest in the summer because of the heavy Monsoon rains, along with the fast winds and storms, making it difficult to climb.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-02-24 03:35:55', '2026-02-24 03:49:07'),
(393, 282, 'What is the 2 o’clock / 2 pm rule on Everest?', '<p>The 2 o’clock or known as the 2 pm role on Everest is that climbers must stop summiting if they have not reached the top of the peak till 2 pm because of the unpredictable weather and storms.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-02-24 03:35:55', '2026-02-24 03:49:07'),
(394, 282, 'Is Sleeping Beauty still on Everest?', '<p>No, Sleeping Beauty (Francys Arsentiev) is not there on Everest, as it was removed in 2007 from the main route for the climbers’ safety.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-02-24 03:35:55', '2026-02-24 03:49:07'),
(395, 282, 'Can a beginner hike in Everest?', '<p>No, a beginner cannot hike in Everest because the mountain is the world’s highest peak, and it\'s at an altitude of 8848 meters, which is the death zone, so it\'s always important for you to do some trekking, some 7000-meter expeditions, and then climb.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-02-24 03:35:55', '2026-02-24 03:49:07'),
(396, 282, 'Why does it cost $40,000 to climb Mount Everest?', '<p>It costs $40, 000 to climb Mount Everest because of the permit fees fixed by the Nepal government, Sherpa guides, oxygen cylinders, food, accommodations, gears and equipment, and many more.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-02-24 03:35:55', '2026-02-24 03:49:07'),
(397, 283, 'Is Annapurna harder than Kilimanjaro?', '<p>Annapurna is harder than Kilimanjaro because of the highest fatality rate on Annapurna, along with technical expedition skills. Whereas Kilimanjaro is just at an altitude of 5,895 m, which does not require technical climbing skills.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-02-24 04:23:04', '2026-02-24 04:36:38'),
(398, 283, 'Is Annapurna harder than Everest?', '<p>Both Annapurna and Everest are harder in terms of climbing, and both are above 8000 meters. However, Annapurna is considered harder because of its unpredictable weather and the avalanches prone slope.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-02-24 04:23:04', '2026-02-24 04:36:38'),
(399, 283, 'Why is Annapurna called the silent killer?', '<p>Annapurna is called the silent killer because it has one of the highest fatality rate of 32%, which is one of the highest compared to any other 8000-meter peaks.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-02-24 04:23:04', '2026-02-24 04:36:38'),
(400, 283, 'What gear is needed for Annapurna?', '<p>You will require many gears for Annapurna, such as mountain boots that are insulated, crampons, ice axes, a helmet, a harness, sleeping bags rated to -40 C, goggles, headlamps, an oxygen system, and many more. Please check out the packing list for the Annapurna expeditions blogs for a detailed list.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-02-24 04:23:04', '2026-02-24 04:36:38'),
(401, 283, 'Is K2 or Annapurna deadlier?', '<p>Annapurna is deadlier in compared to k2 as well as the K2 expeditions is organized and well maintained by the expedition teams, were as Annapurna cannot be organized well due to it’s unpredictable weather and the unpredictable avalanches.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-02-24 04:23:04', '2026-02-24 04:36:38'),
(402, 283, 'What mountain is forbidden to climb?', '<p>In Nepal, Machapuchhare, which is often known as the Fish tail mountain by the trekkers, is forbidden to climb as locals consider this as a scared mountain.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-02-24 04:23:04', '2026-02-24 04:36:38'),
(403, 283, 'What is the death rate for the Annapurna Base Camp trek?', '<p>The death rate of the Annapurna base camp trek is very rare, as it’s the base camp due to which everything is organized, and immediate rescue can happen. However, talking about the peak, its 32% fatality rate, which is the highest in the world.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-02-24 04:23:04', '2026-02-24 04:36:38'),
(404, 283, 'Can you sleep at Annapurna Base Camp?', '<p>Yes, you can sleep at Annapurna Base Camp. The tea houses and lodges are well-maintained and run by locals who care about your comfort.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-02-24 04:23:04', '2026-02-24 04:36:38'),
(405, 284, 'Where is Cho Oyu located?', '<p>Cho Oyu is located on the Nepal–Tibet border in the Mahalangur Himal range. With an elevation of 8,188 meters, it is the sixth-highest mountain in the world and one of the most popular 8,000-meter peaks due to its relatively less technical climbing route.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-02-26 23:07:17', '2026-02-26 23:15:42'),
(406, 284, 'How difficult is the Cho Oyu expedition?', '<p>Cho Oyu is considered one of the least technical 8,000-meter mountains, making it ideal for climbers aiming to summit their first 8,000er. However, it is still an extremely demanding expedition that requires excellent physical fitness, strong mental endurance, and prior high-altitude climbing experience.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-02-26 23:07:17', '2026-02-26 23:15:42'),
(407, 284, 'What previous climbing experience is required?', '<p>Participants should have prior experience climbing peaks above 6,000 meters, such as Ama Dablam, Island Peak, Lobuche Peak, or similar mountains. Familiarity with crampons, fixed ropes, ice axe use, and high-altitude camping is essential.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-02-26 23:07:17', '2026-02-26 23:15:42'),
(408, 284, 'What is the best season to climb Cho Oyu?', '<p>The best seasons for the Cho Oyu expedition are spring (April–May) and autumn (September–October). During these periods, weather conditions are relatively stable, visibility is good, and temperatures are more favorable for high-altitude climbing.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-02-26 23:07:17', '2026-02-26 23:15:42'),
(409, 284, 'How long does the Cho Oyu expedition take?', '<p>The complete Cho Oyu expedition typically takes 32 to 35 days, including arrival, acclimatization, rotations, summit push, and return. This duration allows proper acclimatization and increases safety and success rates.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-02-26 23:07:17', '2026-02-26 23:15:42'),
(410, 284, 'Do I need supplemental oxygen to climb Cho Oyu?', '<p>While some elite climbers attempt Cho Oyu without oxygen, supplemental oxygen is strongly recommended for safety and comfort, especially during the summit push. Our expedition includes oxygen support as per the chosen package.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-02-26 23:07:17', '2026-02-26 23:15:42'),
(411, 284, 'How high are the camps on Cho Oyu?', '<ul>\r\n<li>Chinese Basecamp: 5,100 m</li>\r\n<li>Advanced Basecamp: 5,700 m</li>\r\n<li>Camp I: approx. 6,400 m</li>\r\n<li>Camp II: approx. 7,000 m</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The summit is reached from Camp II during a long summit day.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-02-26 23:07:17', '2026-04-10 15:59:08'),
(412, 284, 'What type of accommodation is provided during the expedition?', '<p>Accommodation includes hotels in Kathmandu, lodges in Tibet (Kerung, Tingri, Thingri), and fully equipped expedition tents at Basecamp and high camps. High-altitude camps use shared climbing tents.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-02-26 23:07:17', '2026-02-26 23:15:42'),
(413, 284, 'What kind of food is provided during the expedition?', '<p>We provide full-board meals throughout the expedition, including freshly cooked meals at Basecamp and high camps. The menu includes Nepali, Tibetan, and international dishes designed to meet high-altitude nutritional needs.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-02-26 23:07:17', '2026-02-26 23:15:42'),
(414, 284, 'How is acclimatization managed on this expedition?', '<p>Acclimatization is carefully planned through rest days, gradual ascents, and rotation climbs between Basecamp and higher camps. This systematic approach helps reduce the risk of altitude sickness and improves summit success.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-02-26 23:07:17', '2026-02-26 23:15:42'),
(415, 284, 'Is travel insurance mandatory for Cho Oyu?', '<p>Yes, comprehensive travel insurance covering high-altitude mountaineering and emergency evacuation is mandatory. Climbers must provide proof of insurance before the expedition begins.</p>', 11, 1, '2026-02-26 23:07:17', '2026-02-26 23:15:42'),
(416, 284, 'What permits are required, and are they included?', '<p>All required permits, including Cho Oyu climbing permits, Chinese permits, and liaison officer fees, are included in the expedition cost. We handle all administrative and permit arrangements on your behalf.</p>', 12, 1, '2026-02-26 23:07:17', '2026-02-26 23:15:42'),
(417, 284, 'How safe is the Cho Oyu expedition?', '<p>Safety is our top priority. The expedition is led by experienced guides and Sherpas, with fixed ropes, medical kits, oxygen support, and continuous monitoring at Basecamp. Weather windows are carefully analyzed before any summit attempt.</p>', 13, 1, '2026-02-26 23:07:17', '2026-02-26 23:15:42'),
(418, 284, 'Can the itinerary change during the expedition?', '<p>Yes, the itinerary may change due to weather conditions, climber health, or safety concerns. Flexibility is essential in high-altitude expeditions, and decisions are always made in the best interest of the team.</p>', 14, 1, '2026-02-26 23:07:17', '2026-02-26 23:15:42'),
(419, 284, 'What happens if I cannot reach the summit?', '<p>Reaching the summit depends on weather, health, and individual performance. Even if you do not summit, the expedition still offers an extraordinary high-altitude climbing experience. No refunds are provided for unsuccessful summit attempts, as safety always comes first for summit 8000.</p>', 15, 1, '2026-02-26 23:07:17', '2026-02-26 23:15:42'),
(420, 285, 'Where is Dhampus located?', '<p>Dhampus peak is located inside the Annapurna Conservation Area in the north of the Pokhara city known for its famous Dhampus village hike.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-02-27 02:32:55', '2026-02-27 03:05:35'),
(421, 285, 'What is the altitude of Dhampus (Thapa) Peak?', '<p>The altitude of the Dhampus (Thapa) peak is 6,012 meters (19,724 feet) above sea level, making it a non-technical trekking peak but still a serious high-altitude climb.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-02-27 02:32:55', '2026-02-27 03:05:35'),
(422, 285, 'Is Dhampus Peak suitable for beginners?', '<p>Yes, Dhampus peak is suitable for beginners if you are fit trekker with basic mountaineering training. While it does not require advanced technical climbing skills, prior high-altitude trekking experience and basic knowledge of crampons, ice axe, and rope use are highly recommended.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-02-27 02:32:55', '2026-02-27 03:05:35'),
(423, 285, 'Do I need a climbing permit for Dhampus Peak?', '<p>Yes, you will need a climbing permit for Dhampus peak which are the: • Nepal Government Trekking Peak Permit • Annapurna Conservation Area Permit (ACAP) • TIMS Card • All permits are usually arranged by the summit8000 for you.</p>', 14, 1, '2026-02-27 02:32:55', '2026-02-27 03:05:35'),
(424, 285, 'What is the best time to climb Dhampus Peak?', '<p>The best time to climb Dhampus peak is during the month of the Autumn (Sept to Nov) and Spring (March to May) as during this time the weather is clear and temperature is moderate.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-02-27 02:32:55', '2026-02-27 03:05:35'),
(425, 285, 'How difficult is the climb to Dhampus Peak?', '<p>The difficulty level of the climbing of Thapa peak is moderate to challenging where you will encounter Snow and ice slopes, Use of fixed ropes in some sections and the Long summit day (8–9 hours).</p>', 7, 1, '2026-02-27 02:32:55', '2026-02-27 03:05:35'),
(426, 285, 'Is previous mountaineering experience mandatory?', '<p>Yes, previous mountaineering experience is mandatory to climb the peak as it will comfortable trekking for you above 5,000 meters and follow guide instructions strictly.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-02-27 02:32:55', '2026-02-27 03:05:35'),
(427, 287, 'What is the height of Chulu West Peak?', '<p>Chulu West Peak is 6,419 meters (21,056 feet) high and is located in the Annapurna region of Nepal.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-06 02:12:36', '2026-03-06 02:19:17'),
(428, 287, 'How difficult is climbing Chulu West Peak?', '<p>It is considered technically challenging. Climbers need experience with ice, snow, and rock climbing, as well as good physical fitness.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-06 02:12:36', '2026-03-06 02:19:17'),
(429, 287, 'How many days does the expedition take?', '<p>The full expedition lasts 14 days, including trekking, acclimatization, and summit day.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-06 02:12:36', '2026-03-06 02:19:17'),
(430, 287, 'What is the best time to climb Chulu West Peak?', '<p>The spring (March to May) and autumn (September to November) seasons are the best for climbing, with clear skies and stable weather.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-06 02:12:36', '2026-03-06 02:19:17'),
(431, 287, 'Do I need previous climbing experience?', '<p>Yes, some high-altitude climbing experience is recommended because the route involves technical ice and rock sections.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-06 02:12:36', '2026-03-06 02:19:17'),
(432, 287, 'How much does the expedition cost?', '<p>The cost ranges from $4,500 to $6,000 USD, depending on the group size, duration, and level of support.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-06 02:12:36', '2026-03-06 02:19:17'),
(433, 287, 'What is included in the cost?', '<p>The expedition includes permits, professional guides, Sherpa support, meals and accommodation during trekking and at base camp, transportation within Nepal, and safety support.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-06 02:12:36', '2026-03-06 02:19:17'),
(434, 287, 'What is not included in the cost?', '<p>Expenses like international flights, personal climbing gear, travel insurance, tips, and optional extras such as satellite phones or private chefs are not included.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-06 02:12:36', '2026-03-06 02:19:17'),
(435, 287, 'Where does the trek start?', '<p>The trek usually starts from Chame in the Manang district, after a transfer from Kathmandu and Pokhara.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-06 02:12:36', '2026-03-06 02:19:17'),
(436, 287, 'How do we get to Nepal?', '<p>You need to fly into Tribhuvan International Airport in Kathmandu. From there, the expedition team arranges transfers to the starting point.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-06 02:12:36', '2026-03-06 02:19:17'),
(437, 287, 'Is it safe to climb Chulu West Peak?', '<p>With experienced guides, Sherpa support, and proper acclimatization, it is safe. However, climbers must be physically fit and follow safety instructions carefully.</p>', 11, 1, '2026-03-06 02:12:36', '2026-03-06 02:19:17'),
(438, 287, 'Can beginners attempt Chulu West Peak?', '<p>This peak is not recommended for beginners. It is best suited for climbers with prior experience in high-altitude technical climbs.</p>', 12, 1, '2026-03-06 02:12:36', '2026-03-06 02:19:17'),
(439, 288, 'Where is Mount Dhaulagiri located?', '<p>Mount Dhaulagiri is located in western Nepal, in the Dhaulagiri Himal range, northwest of Pokhara. It stands in a remote region surrounded by deep valleys, glaciers, and some of the most dramatic landscapes in the Himalayas.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-06 20:38:08', '2026-03-06 20:41:06'),
(440, 288, 'How high is Mount Dhaulagiri?', '<p>Mount Dhaulagiri reaches an elevation of 8,167 meters (26,795 feet), making it the seventh-highest mountain in the world. Its massive snowy face and isolated position make it one of Nepal’s most impressive peaks.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-06 20:38:08', '2026-03-06 20:41:06'),
(441, 288, 'How difficult is the Dhaulagiri Expedition?', '<p>The Dhaulagiri Expedition is considered extremely challenging due to steep climbing sections, high avalanche risk, and unpredictable weather. It is recommended only for experienced mountaineers with prior high-altitude expedition background.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-06 20:38:08', '2026-03-06 20:41:06'),
(442, 288, 'How long does the Dhaulagiri Expedition take?', '<p>A typical Dhaulagiri Expedition takes around 50 to 60 days, including trekking to base camp, acclimatization rotations, and the summit push. The schedule may vary depending on weather and route conditions.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-06 20:38:08', '2026-03-06 20:41:06'),
(443, 288, 'What is the best season to climb Dhaulagiri?', '<p>The best season for climbing Dhaulagiri is spring (April to May) when the weather is relatively stable. Autumn (September to October) is also possible but colder and less commonly attempted.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-06 20:38:08', '2026-03-06 20:41:06'),
(444, 288, 'What is the normal route for the Dhaulagiri climb?', '<p>The standard route is the Northeast Ridge, which involves glacier crossings, steep ice slopes, and technical climbing above high camps. Fixed ropes and strong teamwork are essential on the upper mountain.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-06 20:38:08', '2026-03-06 20:41:06'),
(445, 288, 'Do I need previous climbing experience for Dhaulagiri?', '<p>Yes, climbers must have significant experience on peaks above 6,500–7,000 meters and be comfortable with technical ice and snow climbing. Dhaulagiri is not suitable for first-time 8,000-meter climbers.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-06 20:38:08', '2026-03-06 20:41:06'),
(446, 288, 'What permits are required for the Dhaulagiri Expedition?', '<p>Climbers need a Dhaulagiri climbing permit issued by the Government of Nepal along with trekking permits for the approach route. Expedition operators usually manage all necessary paperwork and logistics.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-06 20:38:08', '2026-03-06 20:41:06'),
(447, 288, 'How do you reach Dhaulagiri Base Camp?', '<p>The expedition begins with travel from Kathmandu to Pokhara, followed by a drive to the trekking trailhead. The trek to Dhaulagiri Base Camp usually takes about 8 to 10 days through remote villages and glacial valleys.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-06 20:38:08', '2026-03-06 20:41:06'),
(448, 288, 'Is supplementary oxygen used on Dhaulagiri?', '<p>Supplementary oxygen is optional but often used during the summit attempt because of the extreme altitude and difficult conditions. Some elite climbers choose to climb without oxygen, but it increases the challenge significantly.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-06 20:38:08', '2026-03-06 20:41:06'),
(449, 288, 'How much does the Dhaulagiri Expedition cost?', '<p>The cost generally ranges from USD 20,000 to 40,000 or more depending on group size, Sherpa support, oxygen services, and expedition logistics. Full-service packages are more expensive but provide higher safety and comfort.</p>', 11, 1, '2026-03-06 20:38:08', '2026-03-06 20:41:06'),
(450, 288, 'What are the main risks during the expedition?', '<p>Major risks include altitude sickness, avalanches, crevasses, frostbite, and sudden storms. Proper acclimatization, expert guides, and strong preparation are critical for a safe climb.</p>', 12, 1, '2026-03-06 20:38:08', '2026-03-06 20:41:06'),
(451, 288, 'Is rescue possible during the Dhaulagiri Expedition?', '<p>Rescue is possible but difficult because of the remote terrain and technical nature of the mountain. Helicopter evacuation may work from lower camps, but above base camp rescue becomes very limited.</p>', 13, 1, '2026-03-06 20:38:08', '2026-03-06 20:41:06'),
(452, 288, 'Why is Dhaulagiri considered special among 8,000m peaks?', '<p>Dhaulagiri is known for its isolation, steep faces, and serious expedition atmosphere compared to more commercial peaks. It offers a true high-altitude adventure for climbers seeking one of Nepal’s toughest challenges.</p>', 14, 1, '2026-03-06 20:38:08', '2026-03-06 20:41:06'),
(453, 289, 'What is Gangapurna Peak?', '<p>Gangapurna Peak is a 7,455-meter Himalayan mountain located in the Annapurna region of Nepal. It is part of the Gangapurna mountains and offers a challenging expedition for experienced climbers.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-06 21:13:16', '2026-03-06 21:22:09'),
(454, 289, 'Where is Gangapurna Himal located?', '<p>Gangapurna Himal is situated in the northern part of the Annapurna range, accessible via Manang and the Gangapurna Lake trekking route.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-06 21:13:16', '2026-03-06 21:22:09');
INSERT INTO `cl_trip_faqs` (`id`, `trip_detail_id`, `title`, `content`, `ordering`, `status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(455, 289, 'Why is Gangapurna Lake special?', '<p>Gangapurna Lake is a serene glacial lake at the base of Gangapurna Peak. Its crystal-clear waters reflect the surrounding snow-capped mountains, making it a popular spot for acclimatization and photography.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-06 21:13:16', '2026-03-06 21:22:09'),
(456, 289, 'What is the best time to climb Gangapurna Peak?', '<p>The best climbing seasons are spring (March–May) and autumn (September–November) when the weather is stable, skies are clear, and snow conditions are favorable.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-06 21:13:16', '2026-03-06 21:22:09'),
(457, 289, 'How difficult is Gangapurna Peak climbing?', '<p>Gangapurna Peak is considered a technical climb and requires experience in high-altitude mountaineering, including ice and snow techniques.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-06 21:13:16', '2026-03-06 21:22:09'),
(458, 289, 'Do I need prior climbing experience?', '<p>Yes, climbers are expected to have prior experience with high-altitude peaks or training in technical mountaineering.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-06 21:13:16', '2026-03-06 21:22:09'),
(459, 289, 'How many days does the expedition take?', '<p>A typical Gangapurna Peak expedition lasts about 36 days, including trekking, acclimatization, climbing, and return to Kathmandu.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-06 21:13:16', '2026-03-06 21:22:09'),
(460, 289, 'What is included in the Gangapurna climbing package?', '<p>Packages generally include permits, guides, porters, meals during the trek, base camp accommodation, and group climbing equipment.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-06 21:13:16', '2026-03-06 21:22:09'),
(461, 289, 'What is excluded from the package?', '<p>International flights, personal climbing gear, travel insurance, tips, and personal expenses such as drinks or laundry are not included.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-06 21:13:16', '2026-03-06 21:22:09'),
(462, 289, 'Do I need a climbing permit?', '<p>Yes, a Gangapurna climbing permit from the Nepal Mountaineering Association (NMA) is mandatory.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-06 21:13:16', '2026-03-06 21:22:09'),
(463, 289, 'How physically fit should I be?', '<p>Climbers should have excellent fitness, stamina, and experience with long-duration trekking and high-altitude conditions.</p>', 11, 1, '2026-03-06 21:13:16', '2026-03-06 21:22:09'),
(464, 289, 'Is there a risk of altitude sickness?', '<p>Yes, as Gangapurna Peak rises above 7,400 meters, altitude sickness is possible. Proper acclimatization and hydration are crucial.</p>', 12, 1, '2026-03-06 21:13:16', '2026-03-06 21:22:09'),
(465, 289, 'Can beginners attempt Gangapurna Peak?', '<p>No, this expedition is suitable only for experienced mountaineers due to technical and high-altitude challenges.</p>', 13, 1, '2026-03-06 21:13:16', '2026-03-06 21:22:09'),
(466, 289, 'What gear is required for the climb?', '<p>Essential gear includes crampons, ice axes, climbing harness, helmet, high-altitude boots, insulated jackets, gloves, sleeping bags, and trekking poles.</p>', 14, 1, '2026-03-06 21:13:16', '2026-03-06 21:22:09'),
(467, 289, 'Are there base camps and high camps?', '<p>Yes, the expedition includes a base camp at 4,650m and higher camps as needed for acclimatization and summit attempts.</p>', 15, 1, '2026-03-06 21:13:16', '2026-03-06 21:22:09'),
(468, 289, 'Is there mobile connectivity during the trek?', '<p>Mobile coverage is limited. Some lodges in Manang or near base camp may have Wi-Fi or satellite phone access.</p>', 16, 1, '2026-03-06 21:13:16', '2026-03-06 21:22:09'),
(469, 289, 'Can I visit Gangapurna Lake during the expedition?', '<p>Yes, trekking to Gangapurna Lake is included in the itinerary for acclimatization and photography opportunities.</p>', 17, 1, '2026-03-06 21:13:16', '2026-03-06 21:22:09'),
(470, 289, 'What are the weather conditions on Gangapurna Peak?', '<p>The weather can change rapidly, with cold temperatures, strong winds, and snowfall common at higher altitudes.</p>', 18, 1, '2026-03-06 21:13:16', '2026-03-06 21:22:09'),
(471, 289, 'Why should I choose Summit 8000 for Gangapurna climbing?', '<p>Summit 8000 provides experienced guides, high-quality climbing equipment, reliable logistics, and safety support for a well-organized expedition.</p>', 19, 1, '2026-03-06 21:13:16', '2026-03-06 21:22:09'),
(472, 289, 'Is insurance mandatory for Gangapurna Peak climbing?', '<p>Yes, high-altitude mountaineering insurance covering helicopter rescue and medical emergencies is mandatory for all climbers.</p>', 20, 1, '2026-03-06 21:13:16', '2026-03-06 21:22:09'),
(474, 286, 'What does ama Dablam mean?', '<p>Ama Dablam means mothers necklace which translate as: Ama means mother and Dablam means double pendant worn by sherpa women</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-06 21:30:52', '2026-03-06 21:31:46'),
(477, 286, 'How hard is it to climb ama Dablam?', '<p>Ama Dablam is rated as the D(Difficult) to TD (very difficult) considering the steep ice walls, narrow exposed ridges, rock climbing up to UIAA grade IV and heavy reliance on the fixed ropes.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-06 21:30:52', '2026-03-06 21:31:46'),
(478, 286, 'Can a beginner climb Ama Dablam?', '<p>No, a beginner cannot climb Ama Dablam climbing the peak requires the previous trekking experience, along with the knowledge of the ice climbing, rope work, crampons, and ascenders.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-06 21:30:52', '2026-03-06 21:31:46'),
(479, 286, 'Do you need oxygen to climb ama Dablam?', '<p>No, you will not need oxygen to climb Ama Dablam as the peak is below than the 7000 meters. Most of the climbers summit the peak without any oxygen.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-06 21:30:52', '2026-03-06 21:31:46'),
(480, 286, 'How to prepare for Ama Dablam?', '<p>You shall start your preparation before by trekking in the mountains, hiking, and then learning about the rope climbing, by doing technical climbing training, by making yourself physically and mentally fit.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-06 21:30:52', '2026-03-06 21:31:46'),
(481, 286, 'What is the difficulty level of the Ama Dablam trek?', '<p>The difficulty level of the Ama Dablam peak is moderate to challenging depending upon your previous experience and physical fitness level.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-06 21:30:52', '2026-03-06 21:31:46'),
(482, 286, 'What is the hardest part of Ama Dablam?', '<p>The hardest part of Ama Dablam is yellow tower which is steep rock climbing, grey tower which is exposed mixed climbing, and the summit ridge which is narrow knife ridge.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-06 21:30:52', '2026-03-06 21:31:46'),
(483, 286, 'What are the common mistakes in mountain climbers?', '<p>The common mistakes in mountain climbers are poor acclimatization, not understanding technical difficulty, carrying excessive weight, inadequate training, ignoring the weather windows and not listening to the sherpa guides.</p>', 11, 1, '2026-03-06 21:30:52', '2026-03-06 21:31:46'),
(484, 286, 'What is the best season to climb Ama Dablam?', '<p>The best season to climb Ama Dablam is during the autumn which is September to November due to the stable weather and spring which is from march to may for its warm temperatures.</p>', 12, 1, '2026-03-06 21:30:52', '2026-03-06 21:31:46'),
(485, 286, 'What is the cost to climb Ama Dablam?', '<p>The cost to climb Ama Dablam is around 7500 USD to 15,000 USD depending upon various factors like the seasons you are choosing, companies you are selecting, level of service, logistics and supports and many more.</p>', 13, 1, '2026-03-06 21:30:52', '2026-04-07 13:50:22'),
(486, 286, 'Where is ama Dablam located?', '<p>The Ama Dablam peak is located in the Khumbu region of eastern Nepal inside the Sagarmatha National park. It is situated to the south of the mount Everest and can be seen during the walk from the Debuche.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-06 21:30:52', '2026-03-06 21:31:46'),
(488, 286, 'Is ama Dablam harder than Everest?', '<p>Technically yes, Ama Dablam is harder than Everest for its steep rock climbing, exposed ridges, mixed terrains but the altitude is only 6,812 meters (22,349 feet) however Everest altitude is above 8000 meter which is why its more difficult and needs self discipline, endurance, and long expeditions periods.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-06 21:30:52', '2026-03-06 21:31:46'),
(489, 286, 'How long does it take to climb ama Dablam?', '<p>It generally takes 25 to 30 days to climb Ama Dablam including the arrival in Kathmandu and departure.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-06 21:30:52', '2026-03-06 21:31:46'),
(499, 286, 'What is the Packing list for the Ama Dablam?', '<p>The packing list for the Ama Dablam depends upon the various factors such as the seasons and company logistics. In average you will need double or triple layer high altitude boots, crampons and axes, climbing harness, helmet, ascenders, down suit and down jackets, technical gloves and mittens, personal medical kit, headlamps and many more.</p>', 14, 1, '2026-03-06 21:31:46', '2026-03-06 21:34:53'),
(500, 286, 'What permits are required for the Ama Dablam summit?', '<p>You will need three permits for the Ama Dablam summit which are: • Ama Dablam Climbing Permit • Sagarmatha National Park Permit • Khumbu Rural Municipality Permit</p>', 15, 1, '2026-03-06 21:31:46', '2026-03-06 21:34:53'),
(501, 290, 'Where is Himlung Himal located?', '<p>Himlung Himal is located in the remote Nar Phu Valley of northern Nepal near the border with Tibet. The mountain lies in the Manaslu region of the Nepal Himalayas and reaches an elevation of 7,126 meters (23,379 ft) above sea level. It is part of the Peri Himal range and sits close to other peaks such as Manaslu and Annapurna.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-06 23:00:34', '2026-03-06 23:08:59'),
(502, 290, 'How difficult is the Himlung Himal expedition?', '<p>The Himlung Himal expedition is considered a moderately difficult 7000-meter climb. It is often recommended for climbers who want to gain high-altitude experience before attempting an 8000-meter mountain. While the climb requires good physical fitness and basic mountaineering skills, it is technically less demanding compared to many other Himalayan peaks.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-06 23:00:34', '2026-03-06 23:08:59'),
(503, 290, 'What is the height of Himlung Himal?', '<p>The summit of Himlung Himal stands at 7,126 meters (23,379 feet) above sea level, making it one of the popular 7000-meter expedition peaks in Nepal.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-06 23:00:34', '2026-03-06 23:08:59'),
(504, 290, 'How long does the Himlung Himal expedition take?', '<p>A typical Himlung Himal expedition takes around 25–30 days. This includes travel from Kathmandu, trekking through the Nar Phu Valley, acclimatization days, the climbing period, and the return journey.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-06 23:00:34', '2026-03-06 23:08:59'),
(505, 290, 'Do I need prior climbing experience for Himlung Himal?', '<p>Yes, previous trekking or climbing experience is recommended. Climbers should ideally have experience with high-altitude trekking (above 5,000 meters) and basic mountaineering skills such as using crampons, ice axes, and fixed ropes.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-06 23:00:34', '2026-03-06 23:08:59'),
(506, 290, 'How much does a Himlung Himal expedition cost?', '<p>The cost of the Himlung Himal expedition usually ranges from USD 7,000 to USD 15,000, depending on the expedition company, group size, services provided, and climbing logistics.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-06 23:00:34', '2026-03-06 23:08:59'),
(507, 290, 'How high is Himlung Base Camp?', '<p>Himlung Base Camp is located at approximately 4,900 meters (16,076 feet) above sea level.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-06 23:00:34', '2026-03-06 23:08:59'),
(508, 290, 'Is Himlung Himal a good preparation for 8000-meter peaks?', '<p>Yes, Himlung Himal is considered an excellent training peak for climbers who want to attempt 8000-meter mountains like Mount Everest or Dhaulagiri. The expedition provides valuable experience in high-altitude climbing, acclimatization, and glacier travel.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-06 23:00:34', '2026-03-06 23:08:59'),
(509, 290, 'Is altitude sickness a risk during the expedition?', '<p>Yes, altitude sickness is a potential risk when climbing mountains above 3,500 meters. The itinerary includes several acclimatization days to help climbers adjust gradually to higher elevations and reduce the risk.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-06 23:00:34', '2026-03-06 23:08:59'),
(510, 290, 'Why is Himlung Himal less crowded than other peaks?', '<p>The mountain lies inside the remote Nar Phu Valley, which is a restricted region with limited access. Because of the permit system and remote location, fewer climbers attempt this peak compared to other Himalayan mountains.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-06 23:00:34', '2026-03-06 23:08:59'),
(511, 290, 'Can beginners climb Himlung Himal?', '<p>Beginners with strong physical fitness and some trekking experience may attempt Himlung Himal with a professional expedition team, but it is recommended to have prior mountaineering training.</p>', 11, 1, '2026-03-06 23:00:34', '2026-03-06 23:09:00'),
(512, 291, 'What is the difficulty level of Island Peak?', '<p>Island Peak is considered a moderate technical climb, suitable for climbers with good fitness and basic trekking experience. It requires some technical skills, such as using crampons, ice axes, and ropes, but it is achievable for beginners who have trained properly and are guided by experienced Sherpas.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-07 18:33:20', '2026-03-07 18:41:32'),
(513, 291, 'Do I need prior mountaineering experience to climb Island Peak?', '<p>While prior climbing experience is helpful, it is not mandatory. The climb is designed to teach basic mountaineering skills, including glacier travel, rope techniques, and high-altitude trekking, making it ideal for novice climbers preparing for higher peaks in the future.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-07 18:33:20', '2026-03-07 18:41:32'),
(514, 291, 'What is the best time to climb Island Peak?', '<p>The pre-monsoon (March to May) and post-monsoon (late September to November) seasons are the most suitable. These periods offer stable weather, clear skies, and stunning views of surrounding peaks like Everest, Lhotse, and Makalu. Monsoon and winter months are generally not recommended due to heavy snowfall and harsh conditions.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-07 18:33:20', '2026-03-07 18:41:32'),
(515, 291, 'What permits are required for Island Peak?', '<p>Climbers need a Peak Climbing Permit from the Nepal Ministry of Tourism, along with a Sagarmatha National Park Permit and a TIMS card. Your trekking agency or guide usually handles the permit process to ensure compliance and smooth access to the region.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-07 18:33:20', '2026-03-07 18:41:33'),
(516, 291, 'What kind of training or preparation is needed?', '<p>Climbers should focus on cardiovascular fitness, strength training, and endurance trekking. Acclimatization hikes are recommended before the expedition, and basic knowledge of climbing techniques is useful. Mental preparation for early starts, cold nights, and high-altitude conditions is equally important.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-07 18:33:20', '2026-03-07 18:41:33'),
(517, 291, 'What equipment do I need for the climb?', '<p>Essential items include mountaineering boots, crampons, ice axe, harness, helmet, gloves, down jacket, and sleeping bag. Most technical gear, ropes, and safety equipment are usually provided by the expedition team, but personal clothing and trekking essentials must be arranged by the climber.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-07 18:33:20', '2026-03-07 18:41:33'),
(518, 291, 'How long does the Island Peak climb take?', '<p>The typical expedition lasts 16 days, combining trekking to Everest Base Camp and acclimatization with the technical climb to Island Peak. Summit day starts early (around midnight) to take advantage of stable weather and minimal winds.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-07 18:33:20', '2026-03-07 18:41:33'),
(519, 291, 'Is it safe to climb Island Peak?', '<p>When properly guided and with appropriate acclimatization, Island Peak is considered a safe climb. Experienced Sherpa guides lead every step, monitor health conditions, and provide emergency support. However, high-altitude risks like altitude sickness, frostbite, and weather changes are always present, so vigilance is required.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-07 18:33:20', '2026-03-07 18:41:33'),
(520, 291, 'What can I expect from the summit?', '<p>From the Island Peak summit (6,189 m), climbers enjoy 360-degree panoramic views of the Himalayas, including Everest, Lhotse, Makalu, Nuptse, and Ama Dablam, along with glaciers, alpine valleys, and the surrounding Khumbu region. It’s a rewarding experience and a perfect introduction to climbing high-altitude peaks, including the world’s 8000m giants.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-07 18:33:20', '2026-03-07 18:41:33'),
(521, 292, 'What is the best time to climb Kanchenjunga?', '<p>The ideal time for a Kanchenjunga expedition is during the pre-monsoon season from April to May and the post-monsoon season from late September to November. During these periods, the weather is relatively stable, offering clearer skies, less snowfall, and safer climbing conditions compared to winter or monsoon months.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-07 19:22:28', '2026-03-07 19:24:31'),
(522, 292, 'How difficult is the Kanchenjunga climb?', '<p>Kanchenjunga is one of the most challenging 8,000-meter peaks in the world. It requires advanced mountaineering experience, excellent physical fitness, and prior high-altitude climbing experience due to its technical routes and unpredictable weather conditions.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-07 19:22:28', '2026-03-07 19:24:31'),
(523, 292, 'Do I need prior high-altitude climbing experience?', '<p>Yes, prior experience in climbing high-altitude peaks above 6,000–7,000 meters is highly recommended. Kanchenjunga’s extreme altitude, technical ice and rock sections, and prolonged exposure make it unsuitable for first-time climbers.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-07 19:22:28', '2026-03-07 19:24:31'),
(524, 292, 'How long does a typical Kanchenjunga expedition take?', '<p>A full Kanchenjunga expedition usually lasts around 50 to 60 days, including trekking to base camp, acclimatization, and summit attempts. The approach itself is remote and requires several days of trekking through rugged terrain, making it a long and physically demanding expedition.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-07 19:22:28', '2026-03-07 19:24:31'),
(525, 292, 'What permits are required to climb Kanchenjunga?', '<p>Climbers need a Kanchenjunga climbing permit issued by the Government of Nepal, along with trekking permits for the surrounding areas. These permits ensure legal access and contribute to conservation and local development in the region.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-07 19:22:28', '2026-03-07 19:24:31'),
(526, 292, 'Is it necessary to hire a guide or a Sherpa team?', '<p>Yes, hiring experienced guides and high-altitude Sherpa support is highly recommended for safety, route navigation, and carrying equipment. Most climbers rely on professional teams for setting up camps, fixing ropes, and providing medical and logistical assistance.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-07 19:22:28', '2026-03-07 19:24:31'),
(527, 292, 'What equipment is essential for the expedition?', '<p>Climbers need specialized high-altitude climbing gear including insulated clothing, crampons, ice axes, tents, sleeping bags rated for extreme cold, and oxygen systems. Proper gear is critical for survival and safety at extreme altitudes.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-07 19:22:28', '2026-03-07 19:24:31'),
(528, 292, 'What are the main risks associated with Kanchenjunga expeditions?', '<p>The primary risks include avalanches, crevasse falls, altitude sickness, extreme cold, and unpredictable weather changes. Careful planning, proper acclimatization, and experienced guides are essential to mitigate these risks.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-07 19:22:28', '2026-03-07 19:24:31'),
(529, 292, 'How physically fit should I be for the expedition?', '<p>A high level of cardiovascular endurance, strength, and stamina is required for Kanchenjunga. Training should include long-duration trekking with heavy loads, mountaineering exercises, and acclimatization to high-altitude conditions prior to the expedition.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-07 19:22:28', '2026-03-07 19:24:31'),
(530, 292, 'Can anyone join a Kanchenjunga expedition?', '<p>Due to its extreme difficulty, Kanchenjunga expeditions are not suitable for casual hikers or first-time climbers. Only highly experienced mountaineers with proper training, previous high-altitude experience, and strong physical fitness should attempt this climb.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-07 19:22:28', '2026-03-07 19:24:31'),
(531, 293, 'Where is Mount Lhotse located?', '<p>Mount Lhotse is located in the Everest region of Nepal, near the Nepal–Tibet border. It stands right beside Mount Everest and shares the same approach route through the famous Khumbu Valley.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-07 21:22:53', '2026-03-07 21:24:44'),
(532, 293, 'How high is Mount Lhotse?', '<p>Mount Lhotse rises to an elevation of 8,516 meters (27,940 feet), making it the fourth-highest mountain in the world. It is known for its dramatic south face, one of the steepest and most impressive mountain walls on Earth.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-07 21:22:53', '2026-03-07 21:24:44'),
(533, 293, 'How difficult is the Lhotse Expedition?', '<p>The Lhotse Expedition is extremely challenging due to high altitude, technical climbing sections, and harsh weather conditions. Although the route follows Everest up to Camp 3, the final ascent to the summit is steep and demanding.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-07 21:22:53', '2026-03-07 21:24:44'),
(534, 293, 'How long does the Lhotse Expedition take?', '<p>A typical Lhotse Expedition takes around 45 to 60 days, including trekking, acclimatization, and summit attempts. The duration depends heavily on weather windows and individual climbing pace.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-07 21:22:53', '2026-03-07 21:24:44'),
(535, 293, 'What is the best season to climb Lhotse?', '<p>The best season for climbing Lhotse is spring (April to May), when conditions are most stable in the Everest region. Autumn (September to October) is also possible but less common for summit attempts.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-07 21:22:53', '2026-03-07 21:24:44'),
(536, 293, 'What route is used to climb Mount Lhotse?', '<p>The standard route is via the South Col route, following the Everest Base Camp trail and climbing through the Khumbu Icefall. From Camp 3, climbers separate from the Everest route and ascend the steep Lhotse Couloir to reach the summit.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-07 21:22:54', '2026-03-07 21:24:44'),
(537, 293, 'Do I need previous experience to climb Lhotse?', '<p>Yes, climbers should have strong high-altitude mountaineering experience and prior climbs above 7,000 meters. Lhotse is not suitable for beginners because of its technical terrain and extreme altitude risks.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-07 21:22:54', '2026-03-07 21:24:44'),
(538, 293, 'What permits are required for the Lhotse Expedition?', '<p>Climbers need a Lhotse climbing permit issued by the Government of Nepal, along with Sagarmatha National Park entry permits. Most expedition operators handle all permit arrangements and official paperwork.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-07 21:22:54', '2026-03-07 21:24:44'),
(539, 293, 'How do you reach Lhotse Base Camp?', '<p>Lhotse Base Camp is reached by flying from Kathmandu to Lukla, followed by a trek through Namche Bazaar, Tengboche, and Gorak Shep. The trek usually takes about 8 to 10 days before arriving at base camp.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-07 21:22:54', '2026-03-07 21:24:44'),
(540, 293, 'Is oxygen used during the Lhotse Expedition?', '<p>Yes, supplementary oxygen is commonly used above Camp 3 due to the extreme altitude. While climbing without oxygen is possible, it is much more difficult and only attempted by highly experienced climbers.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-07 21:22:54', '2026-03-07 21:24:44'),
(541, 293, 'How much does the Lhotse Expedition cost?', '<p>The cost of a Lhotse Expedition generally ranges from USD 25,000 to 45,000 or more depending on support services, oxygen supply, Sherpa assistance, and logistics. Prices vary widely based on expedition style and operator quality.</p>', 11, 1, '2026-03-07 21:22:54', '2026-03-07 21:24:44'),
(542, 293, 'What are the main risks during the Lhotse climb?', '<p>Major risks include altitude sickness, icefall dangers, avalanches, frostbite, and sudden Himalayan storms. Proper acclimatization and experienced guides are essential for a safe and successful ascent.</p>', 12, 1, '2026-03-07 21:22:54', '2026-03-07 21:24:44'),
(543, 293, 'Is rescue possible on Mount Lhotse?', '<p>Rescue is possible in the lower parts of the Everest region through helicopter evacuation, especially from base camp. However, above higher camps, rescue becomes extremely difficult due to technical terrain and altitude.</p>', 13, 1, '2026-03-07 21:22:54', '2026-03-07 21:24:44'),
(544, 293, 'Why choose Lhotse instead of Everest?', '<p>Lhotse offers a slightly less crowded but equally thrilling 8,000-meter expedition experience. It is ideal for climbers seeking a world-class Himalayan summit with a more technical and serious final climb than Everest.</p>', 14, 1, '2026-03-07 21:22:54', '2026-03-07 21:24:44'),
(545, 294, 'Can we combine Lobuche Peak climbing with the Everest Base Camp trek?', '<p>Yes, combining the trek to Everest Base Camp with a Lobuche Peak summit attempt is very common. It allows climbers to acclimatize gradually, experience Sherpa culture, and enjoy iconic Himalayan landscapes before attempting the technical climb. Guided by experienced Sherpas with 8,000-meter summit experience, this approach ensures safety and a rewarding adventure.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-07 22:05:42', '2026-03-07 22:07:36'),
(546, 294, 'What is the best time to climb Lobuche Peak?', '<p>The pre-monsoon (March to May) and post-monsoon (late September to November) seasons are ideal. During these periods, the skies are usually clear, weather is stable, and temperatures are moderate, providing excellent climbing and trekking conditions.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-07 22:05:42', '2026-03-07 22:07:36'),
(547, 294, 'How difficult is Lobuche Peak to climb?', '<p>Lobuche Peak is considered a challenging high-altitude climb but suitable for trekkers with prior trekking experience. The climb involves rock, snow, and moraine sections, and requires basic mountaineering skills. With proper guidance from certified Sherpas, the summit is achievable for physically fit and well-prepared climbers.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-07 22:05:42', '2026-03-07 22:07:36'),
(548, 294, 'How long does the expedition take?', '<p>The standard itinerary is 14 days, combining the Everest Base Camp trek with the Lobuche Peak climb. Shorter itineraries are possible for experienced climbers, but a full program is recommended to allow proper acclimatization and reduce the risk of altitude sickness.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-07 22:05:42', '2026-03-07 22:07:36'),
(549, 294, 'What permits are required for Lobuche Peak?', '<p>Climbers need the Lobuche Peak climbing permit, which is issued by the Nepal government, as well as trekking permits for the Sagarmatha National Park and a Khumbu Pasang Lhamu Rural Municipality fee. These permits are arranged by your expedition company as part of the package.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-07 22:05:42', '2026-03-07 22:07:36'),
(550, 294, 'What is included in the cost of the expedition?', '<p>The cost typically covers domestic flights, accommodation in lodges and hotels, all meals during trekking and climbing, Sherpa guides, porter support, climbing permits, and high-quality expedition equipment. Personal gear, travel insurance, and tips are not included.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-07 22:05:42', '2026-03-07 22:07:36'),
(551, 294, 'Can Lobuche Peak be climbed by beginners?', '<p>While some trekking experience is helpful, Lobuche Peak is not for complete beginners. Climbers should have good physical fitness and ideally have previous trekking or climbing experience at high altitudes. Guidance from experienced Sherpas ensures safety for first-time climbers attempting this peak.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-07 22:05:42', '2026-03-07 22:07:36'),
(552, 294, 'What equipment is necessary for the climb?', '<p>Climbers need mountaineering boots, crampons, harnesses, helmet, ice axe, ropes, gloves, and down jackets. While some technical equipment is provided by the expedition company, climbers are responsible for their personal high-altitude gear.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-07 22:05:42', '2026-03-07 22:07:36'),
(553, 294, 'How is acclimatization handled during the trek?', '<p>The itinerary includes two acclimatization days one in Namche Bazaar and another in Dingboche to help your body adjust to high altitude. Optional short hikes on these days prepare climbers for the demands of the summit. Proper acclimatization reduces the risk of altitude sickness and ensures a safer climb.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-07 22:05:42', '2026-03-07 22:07:36'),
(554, 294, 'What are the risks of climbing Lobuche Peak?', '<p>As with any high-altitude expedition, risks include altitude sickness, sudden weather changes, and technical climbing hazards. These risks are minimized by experienced Sherpa guidance, proper acclimatization, and safety protocols. Emergency response and evacuation plans are in place during the expedition.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-07 22:05:42', '2026-03-07 22:07:36'),
(555, 294, 'How physically fit should I be for the climb?', '<p>Climbers should have good cardiovascular fitness, endurance for 6–9 hours of trekking per day, and the ability to handle rocky, icy, and snowy terrain. Training with cardio exercises, hiking with a backpack, and basic climbing practice before the expedition is recommended.</p>', 11, 1, '2026-03-07 22:05:42', '2026-03-07 22:07:36'),
(556, 294, 'What will the summit experience be like?', '<p>Reaching the summit of Lobuche Peak (6,119m) offers breathtaking 360-degree views of Everest, Nuptse, Lhotse, and Ama Dablam. The climb involves steep snow and rocky sections, and summiting provides a tremendous sense of achievement and a rare Himalayan adventure experience.</p>', 12, 1, '2026-03-07 22:05:42', '2026-03-07 22:07:36'),
(557, 294, 'Are there accommodation options along the trek?', '<p>Yes, accommodation is available in teahouses and lodges throughout the Everest region, from Lukla to Lobuche. The lodges provide basic comfort, meals, and hot showers at higher camps, ensuring a safe and comfortable stay.</p>', 13, 1, '2026-03-07 22:05:42', '2026-03-07 22:07:36'),
(558, 294, 'Can the climb be done in a shorter duration?', '<p>Yes, shorter climbs are possible for experienced climbers, but it’s recommended to allow sufficient days for acclimatization. Rushing the expedition can increase risks of altitude sickness and reduce safety.</p>', 14, 1, '2026-03-07 22:05:42', '2026-03-07 22:07:36'),
(559, 294, 'Will I have access to medical support during the expedition?', '<p>Yes, certified guides are trained in high-altitude first aid, and emergency oxygen and medical evacuation arrangements are available. Trekkers are advised to carry personal medications and a first-aid kit.</p>', 15, 1, '2026-03-07 22:05:42', '2026-03-07 22:07:36'),
(560, 294, 'Do I need insurance for the climb?', '<p>Yes, high-altitude trekking and mountaineering insurance is mandatory. The policy should cover emergency evacuation, helicopter rescue, and medical treatment at high altitude.</p>', 16, 1, '2026-03-07 22:05:42', '2026-03-07 22:07:36'),
(561, 294, 'Can Lobuche Peak be used as preparation for higher peaks?', '<p>Absolutely. Many climbers use Lobuche Peak as training for 7,000m and 8,000m expeditions. It provides valuable high-altitude experience, technical climbing practice, and mental preparation for more challenging Himalayan peaks.</p>', 17, 1, '2026-03-07 22:05:42', '2026-03-07 22:07:36'),
(562, 294, 'How many guides and porters accompany the group?', '<p>Each expedition includes experienced Sherpa guides and porters to assist with luggage, route navigation, and safety. The ratio ensures climbers can focus on the climb while minimizing physical strain.</p>', 18, 1, '2026-03-07 22:05:42', '2026-03-07 22:07:36'),
(563, 294, 'What meals are provided during the expedition?', '<p>Meals include breakfast, lunch, and dinner throughout the trek and climbing period. Traditional Nepali cuisine and simple Western options are available, providing the energy needed for high-altitude trekking and climbing</p>', 19, 1, '2026-03-07 22:05:42', '2026-03-07 22:07:36'),
(564, 294, 'What makes this Lobuche Peak expedition special?', '<p>This expedition combines Everest Base Camp trekking, high-altitude mountaineering, Sherpa cultural immersion, and breathtaking Himalayan views, all guided by experienced climbers with 8,000m summit experience. It’s ideal for adventure seekers looking for a short yet memorable Himalayan climbing challenge.</p>', 20, 1, '2026-03-07 22:05:42', '2026-03-07 22:07:37'),
(565, 295, 'Where is Mount Makalu located?', '<p>Mount Makalu is located in eastern Nepal near the Nepal–Tibet border, within the Makalu Barun National Park. It lies in a remote Himalayan region close to the Everest area, known for its untouched wilderness.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-08 20:45:24', '2026-03-08 20:47:58'),
(566, 295, 'How high is Mount Makalu?', '<p>Mount Makalu stands at 8,485 meters (27,838 feet), making it the fifth-highest mountain in the world. Its sharp pyramid summit makes it one of the most striking peaks in the Himalayas.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-08 20:45:24', '2026-03-08 20:47:58'),
(567, 295, 'How difficult is the Makalu Expedition?', '<p>Makalu is considered one of the most challenging 8,000-meter expeditions due to steep technical sections and extreme altitude. It is recommended only for climbers with strong high-altitude and mountaineering experience.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-08 20:45:24', '2026-03-08 20:47:58'),
(568, 295, 'How long does the Makalu Expedition take?', '<p>The Makalu Expedition typically takes around 50 to 65 days, including trekking, acclimatization, and summit attempts. The exact duration depends on weather conditions and team progress.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-08 20:45:24', '2026-03-08 20:47:58'),
(569, 295, 'What is the best season for Makalu climbing?', '<p>The best time to climb Makalu is during the spring season (April to May) when weather is more stable. Autumn (September to October) is also possible but tends to be colder.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-08 20:45:24', '2026-03-08 20:47:58'),
(570, 295, 'What route is used to climb Makalu?', '<p>The most common route is the Southeast Ridge, which involves glacier travel, steep snow slopes, and technical summit climbing. Fixed ropes are usually required for safety on higher sections.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-08 20:45:24', '2026-03-08 20:47:58'),
(571, 295, 'Do I need previous climbing experience for Makalu?', '<p>Yes, climbers should have prior experience on peaks above 6,500–7,000 meters and strong technical skills. Makalu is not suitable for beginners because of its demanding terrain and altitude.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-08 20:45:24', '2026-03-08 20:47:58'),
(572, 295, 'What permits are required for Makalu Expedition?', '<p>Climbers need a Makalu climbing permit issued by the Nepal government along with Makalu Barun National Park entry permits. Most expedition operators handle all necessary documentation.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-08 20:45:24', '2026-03-08 20:47:59'),
(573, 295, 'How do you reach Makalu Base Camp?', '<p>The journey usually starts with a flight from Kathmandu to Tumlingtar, followed by a drive and multi-day trek through remote valleys. Reaching base camp generally takes about 8 to 10 days of trekking.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-08 20:45:24', '2026-03-08 20:47:59'),
(574, 295, 'Is oxygen used on Makalu?', '<p>Supplementary oxygen is optional but commonly used during summit attempts due to the extreme altitude. Climbing without oxygen is possible but significantly more difficult and risky.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-08 20:45:24', '2026-03-08 20:47:59'),
(575, 295, 'How much does the Makalu Expedition cost?', '<p>The cost of a Makalu Expedition generally ranges from USD 18,000 to 35,000 or more depending on support level, logistics, oxygen, and Sherpa assistance. Prices vary based on services included in the package.</p>', 11, 1, '2026-03-08 20:45:24', '2026-03-08 20:47:59'),
(576, 295, 'What are the main risks during the expedition?', '<p>Major risks include altitude sickness, avalanches, extreme cold, crevasses, and sudden weather changes. Proper acclimatization and experienced guides are essential for safety.</p>', 12, 1, '2026-03-08 20:45:24', '2026-03-08 20:47:59'),
(577, 295, 'Can rescue be done during Makalu Expedition?', '<p>Rescue is possible but challenging because Makalu is very remote. Helicopter evacuation may work in lower regions, but above base camp, rescue becomes extremely difficult.</p>', 13, 1, '2026-03-08 20:45:24', '2026-03-08 20:47:59'),
(578, 295, 'Why is Makalu special compared to other 8,000m peaks?', '<p>Makalu is famous for its technical difficulty, remote approach, and less crowded climbing routes. It offers a true wilderness expedition experience for serious mountaineers.</p>', 14, 1, '2026-03-08 20:45:24', '2026-03-08 20:47:59'),
(579, 296, 'Is Mera Peak hard to climb?', '<p>Yes, Mera Peak is moderately difficult. It is not very technical, but the high altitude (6,476 m) makes it physically demanding. Good fitness, proper acclimatization, and some trekking experiences are very important.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-08 22:10:32', '2026-03-08 22:18:19'),
(580, 296, 'What level of fitness is needed for Mera Peak?', '<p>You need a good level of fitness. You should be able to walk 5–7 hours a day for several days. Regular cardio, hiking, and endurance training before the climb will help a lot.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-08 22:10:33', '2026-03-08 22:18:19'),
(581, 296, 'Is Mera Peak a technical climb?', '<p>No, Mera Peak is considered a non-technical or basic mountaineering peak. However, you will need to use crampons, ropes, and an ice axe near the summit, and your guide will train you before the climb.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-08 22:10:33', '2026-03-08 22:18:19'),
(582, 296, 'Can beginners climb Mera Peak?', '<p>Yes, beginners can climb Mera Peak if they are physically fit and well-prepared. Previous trekking experience at high altitude is highly recommended for a safer and more enjoyable climb.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-08 22:10:33', '2026-03-08 22:18:19'),
(583, 296, 'Is Mera Peak good for beginners?', '<p>Yes, Mera Peak is one of the best beginner-friendly trekking peaks in Nepal. It is a great introduction to mountaineering and a perfect preparation for higher peaks in the future.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-08 22:10:33', '2026-03-08 22:18:19'),
(584, 296, 'Do you need oxygen to climb Mera Peak?', '<p>No, most climbers do not need supplemental oxygen. However, the altitude is very high, so proper acclimatization and a slow ascent are essential to avoid altitude sickness.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-08 22:10:33', '2026-03-08 22:18:19'),
(585, 296, 'How difficult is Mera Peak compared to Kilimanjaro?', '<p>Mera Peak is generally harder than Kilimanjaro. While Kilimanjaro is a trekking peak, Mera Peak involves glacier walking, basic climbing skills, and colder, more remote conditions.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-08 22:10:33', '2026-03-08 22:18:19'),
(586, 296, 'How long does it take to climb Mera Peak?', '<p>It usually takes about 14 to 18 days including trekking, acclimatization, and the summit climb. The extra days help your body adjust to the altitude.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-08 22:10:33', '2026-03-08 22:18:19'),
(587, 296, 'How do you train for Mera Peak?', '<p>Focus on cardio exercises like running, cycling, or swimming. Practice long hikes with a backpack, strength training for legs, and endurance workouts at least 2–3 months before the trip.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-08 22:10:33', '2026-03-08 22:18:19'),
(588, 296, 'What is the success rate of Mera Peak?', '<p>Mera Peak has a high success rate when climbers follow a proper itinerary and acclimatize well. Good weather, fitness, and an experienced guide greatly increase your chances of reaching the summit.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-08 22:10:33', '2026-03-08 22:18:19'),
(589, 296, 'Is Mera Peak harder than other trekking peaks?', '<p>Mera Peak is considered one of the easier trekking peaks technically, but its high altitude makes it physically challenging.</p>', 11, 1, '2026-03-08 22:10:33', '2026-03-08 22:18:19'),
(590, 296, 'Can we climb Mera Peak easily?', '<p>No, you cannot climb Mera Peak easily. It is a high-altitude peak that requires good fitness, proper preparation, and trekking experience. However, with training and guidance, it is achievable and a great step toward future high-altitude climbs.</p>', 12, 1, '2026-03-08 22:10:33', '2026-03-08 22:18:19'),
(591, 297, 'Why should I choose the North Face route from Tibet?', '<p>The North Face route offers a less crowded and more accessible path to Everest Base Camp and the summit. It provides spectacular views of the Rongbuk Glacier and the North Face itself, while being strategically advantageous for acclimatization and logistics compared to the South Col route in Nepal.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-09 03:26:09', '2026-03-09 03:31:55'),
(592, 297, 'What is the best season to climb Everest from the North Face?', '<p>The spring season (April to May) is considered the best time for Everest expeditions from Tibet. During this period, the weather is relatively stable, temperatures are moderate, and the climbing conditions are optimal for a successful summit attempt.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-09 03:26:09', '2026-03-09 03:31:55'),
(593, 297, 'What permits are required for the expedition?', '<p>Climbers need a Tibet Travel Permit, an Everest Climbing Permit, and a liaison officer permit. Summit 8000 arranges all the necessary paperwork as part of the expedition package, ensuring a smooth process.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-09 03:26:09', '2026-03-09 03:31:55'),
(594, 297, 'How physically fit do I need to be?', '<p>Climbers should have excellent physical fitness and prior high-altitude trekking or mountaineering experience. Training for cardiovascular endurance, strength, and stamina is essential, as the expedition involves long days at extreme altitudes.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-09 03:26:09', '2026-03-09 03:31:55'),
(595, 297, 'How long does the expedition take?', '<p>The full expedition, including acclimatization, travel, climbing, and return, typically lasts about 60 days, allowing sufficient time for gradual acclimatization and a safe summit attempt</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-09 03:26:09', '2026-03-09 03:31:55'),
(596, 297, 'Is supplemental oxygen required?', '<p>Yes, supplemental oxygen is recommended for the summit push. Summit 8000 provides high-quality oxygen cylinders and masks to ensure safety during the high-altitude climb.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-09 03:26:09', '2026-03-09 03:31:55'),
(597, 297, 'What kind of support is provided during the climb?', '<p>The expedition includes professional guides, Sherpas, Base Camp support staff, high-altitude cooking teams, communication devices, medical facilities, and full logistical support throughout the journey.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-09 03:26:09', '2026-03-09 03:31:55'),
(598, 297, 'What are the accommodation arrangements?', '<p>Accommodation is provided in Kathmandu hotels, local hotels along the overland route in Tibet, and well-equipped tents at Base Camp. Higher camps include basic tents with shared cooking and sleeping facilities.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-09 03:26:09', '2026-03-09 03:31:55'),
(599, 297, 'How is safety ensured during the expedition?', '<p>Safety is prioritized through careful acclimatization schedules, experienced guides, high-altitude medical monitoring, communication devices, and emergency evacuation plans. Climbers are closely monitored throughout the expedition.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-09 03:26:09', '2026-03-09 03:31:55'),
(600, 297, 'Are there other expeditions I can combine with Everest?', '<p>Yes, climbers can explore related Himalayan peaks such as Cho Oyu, Lhotse, Shishapangma, and Makalu. These expeditions complement the Everest climb and offer additional mountaineering experiences in the region.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-09 03:26:09', '2026-03-09 03:31:55'),
(601, 298, 'test', 'test', 1, 1, '2026-03-09 15:02:16', '2026-03-09 15:02:16'),
(602, 298, 'test', 'test', 2, 1, '2026-03-09 15:02:16', '2026-03-09 15:02:16'),
(603, 298, 'test', 'test', 3, 1, '2026-03-09 15:02:16', '2026-03-09 15:02:16'),
(604, 299, 'What is the best time to climb Mount Manaslu?', '<p>The best climbing season is spring (April to May) and autumn (September to November). During these months, the weather is more stable, with clearer skies and lower chances of heavy snow or monsoon rains, making it safer and more enjoyable for the expedition.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-10 02:19:16', '2026-03-10 02:20:06'),
(605, 299, 'Do I need prior mountaineering experience to climb Manaslu?', '<p>Yes, basic high-altitude climbing experience is highly recommended. Manaslu is an 8,163-meter peak, and climbers should have prior experience with high-altitude trekking, glacier travel, and technical skills like using crampons and ice axes.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-10 02:19:16', '2026-03-10 02:20:06'),
(606, 299, 'How difficult is climbing Mount Manaslu?', '<p>Manaslu is considered a challenging expedition. The climb involves steep snow and ice slopes, glacier crossings, and high-altitude risks. Proper acclimatization, physical fitness, and professional support are essential for safety and success.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-10 02:19:17', '2026-03-10 02:20:07'),
(607, 299, 'What permits are required for climbing Manaslu?', '<p>Climbers must obtain the Manaslu Restricted Area Permit (RAP), issued by the Nepal government. Additionally, trekking permits for the Manaslu region and local taxes are required. Expedition operators usually arrange these permits in advance.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-10 02:19:17', '2026-03-10 02:20:07'),
(608, 299, 'How long does the Manaslu expedition take?', '<p>A full expedition, including trekking, acclimatization, and summit rotation, typically lasts 35 days. This allows for proper acclimatization and ensures a safer summit attempt.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-10 02:19:17', '2026-03-10 02:20:07'),
(609, 299, 'What level of fitness is required?', '<p>Climbers should be in excellent physical condition, with strong endurance and prior experience in trekking at high altitudes. Training before the expedition, including long hikes and cardio exercises, is highly recommended.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-10 02:19:17', '2026-03-10 02:20:07'),
(610, 299, 'Is it safe to climb Manaslu?', '<p>While the expedition is professionally supported, climbing Manaslu carries inherent risks such as altitude sickness, avalanches, and harsh weather. Following acclimatization schedules, using guides, and being prepared with proper gear greatly reduce these risks.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-10 02:19:17', '2026-03-10 02:20:07'),
(611, 299, 'Do I need a guide or Sherpa support?', '<p>Yes, professional guides, Sherpas, and support staff are essential for safety, route fixing, and logistics. They also carry equipment, set up camps, and assist with high-altitude challenges.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-10 02:19:17', '2026-03-10 02:20:07'),
(612, 299, 'What kind of gear is required?', '<p>Essential gear includes high-altitude boots, down jacket, insulated sleeping bag, crampons, ice axe, harness, helmet, and layered clothing. A detailed gear list is usually provided by your expedition operator.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-10 02:19:17', '2026-03-10 02:20:07'),
(613, 299, 'Can anyone attempt the summit?', '<p>Due to extreme altitude, technical climbing, and weather conditions, only experienced climbers in excellent health should attempt the summit. Proper acclimatization, training, and professional guidance are mandatory.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-10 02:19:17', '2026-03-10 02:20:07'),
(614, 300, 'Is Nuptse Peak one of the most technical mountains in Nepal?', '<p>Yes. Nuptse Peak is considered one of the most technically demanding mountains in the Everest region due to steep ice walls, mixed climbing, and exposed ridgelines</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-10 03:07:30', '2026-03-10 03:09:47'),
(615, 300, 'Is prior high-altitude climbing experience required for Nuptse Peak?', '<p>Yes. Climbers should have prior experience on 6,000–7,000-meter peaks and be comfortable with technical alpine climbing.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-10 03:07:30', '2026-03-10 03:09:47'),
(616, 300, 'Is Nuptse Peak suitable for beginner climbers?', '<p>No. Nuptse Peak is not recommended for beginners due to its technical difficulty and extreme altitude.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-10 03:07:30', '2026-03-10 03:09:47'),
(617, 300, 'Is Nuptse Peak located near Mount Everest?', '<p>Yes. Nuptse Peak lies west of Mount Everest in Nepal’s Khumbu region and is part of the Everest massif.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-10 03:07:30', '2026-03-10 03:09:47'),
(618, 300, 'Does the Nuptse Peak Expedition start from Everest Base Camp?', '<p>Yes. The expedition is operated from Everest Base Camp, which serves as the main climbing base.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-10 03:07:30', '2026-03-10 03:09:47'),
(619, 300, 'Is the Nuptse climb more technical than standard trekking peaks?', '<p>Yes. Nuptse involves advanced rope work, ice climbing, and mixed terrain, far exceeding trekking peak difficulty.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-10 03:07:30', '2026-03-10 03:09:47'),
(620, 300, 'Is acclimatization included in the Nuptse Peak Expedition itinerary?', '<p>Yes. The expedition follows a structured acclimatization plan with rotation climbs to ensure safety.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-10 03:07:30', '2026-03-10 03:09:47'),
(621, 300, 'Is supplemental oxygen used for the Nuptse Summit?', '<p>No. Supplemental oxygen is generally not used for summit climbing, though emergency oxygen is available for safety.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-10 03:07:30', '2026-03-10 03:09:47');
INSERT INTO `cl_trip_faqs` (`id`, `trip_detail_id`, `title`, `content`, `ordering`, `status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(622, 300, 'Is spring the best season for Nuptse Peak climbing?', '<p>Yes. Spring (April–May) offers the most stable weather and optimal climbing conditions.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-10 03:07:30', '2026-03-10 03:09:47'),
(623, 300, 'Is autumn also suitable for Nuptse Peak Expedition?', '<p>Yes. Autumn (September–October) provides clear skies and stable conditions, though colder than spring.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-10 03:07:30', '2026-03-10 03:09:47'),
(624, 300, 'Is Nuptse Peak higher than 7,800 meters?', '<p>Yes. Nuptse Peak stands at 7,861 meters (25,791 ft).</p>', 11, 1, '2026-03-10 03:07:30', '2026-03-10 03:09:47'),
(625, 300, 'Is the Nuptse Peak Expedition physically demanding?', '<p>Yes. It requires excellent physical fitness, endurance, and mental resilience.</p>', 12, 1, '2026-03-10 03:07:30', '2026-03-10 03:09:47'),
(626, 300, 'Is rescue support available during the Nuptse Expedition?', '<p>Yes. Emergency rescue coordination and medical support are part of the expedition plan.</p>', 13, 1, '2026-03-10 03:07:30', '2026-03-10 03:09:47'),
(627, 300, 'Is travel and rescue insurance mandatory for Nuptse Peak climbing?', '<p>Yes. Comprehensive high-altitude insurance is mandatory for all participants.</p>', 14, 1, '2026-03-10 03:07:31', '2026-03-10 03:09:47'),
(628, 300, 'Is Summit 8000 experienced in handling technical Himalayan expeditions?', '<p>Yes. Summit 8000 has extensive experience with technical peaks and high-altitude expeditions in Nepal.</p>', 15, 1, '2026-03-10 03:07:31', '2026-03-10 03:09:47'),
(629, 300, 'Is the Nuptse Peak Expedition environmentally responsible?', '<p>Yes. The expedition includes Base Camp cleanup and follows ethical climbing and waste management practices.</p>', 16, 1, '2026-03-10 03:07:31', '2026-03-10 03:09:47'),
(630, 301, 'What is Pumori Peak?', '<p>Pumori is a 7,161-meter Himalayan peak in Nepal’s Khumbu region. It is known for its technical ice and snow slopes and breathtaking views of Everest, Lhotse, and Nuptse. The climb is challenging and ideal for experienced mountaineers seeking a rewarding adventure.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-10 03:32:15', '2026-03-10 03:35:05'),
(631, 301, 'Where is Pumori located?', '<p>Pumori lies just 8 km west of Mount Everest in the Khumbu region. It forms part of the Mahalangur Himalaya range and is accessible via the Everest Base Camp trail. Its location offers stunning panoramic views and easy connection to Sherpa villages.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-10 03:32:15', '2026-03-10 03:35:05'),
(632, 301, 'Why is Pumori called the “Daughter of Everest”?', '<p>The name was given by Swiss climber Hermann Buhl and means “Young Female Mountain.” It is called the Daughter of Everest because of its proximity and visual resemblance to Mount Everest. The peak is smaller yet majestic, standing gracefully beside Everest.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-10 03:32:16', '2026-03-10 03:35:05'),
(633, 301, 'What is the best time to climb Pumori?', '<p>The ideal climbing seasons are pre-monsoon (March–May) and post-monsoon (September–November). During these months, the weather is relatively stable, the skies are clear, and climbing conditions are safer.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-10 03:32:16', '2026-03-10 03:35:05'),
(634, 301, 'How difficult is Pumori Peak climbing?', '<p>Pumori is considered a technical climb with steep snow and ice slopes. It requires prior high-altitude experience and mountaineering skills. Climbers should be physically fit and prepared for challenging conditions.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-10 03:32:16', '2026-03-10 03:35:05'),
(635, 301, 'Which route is used for Pumori Peak climbing?', '<p>The most common path is the West Face Route, known for safety and established camps. The route includes base camp, advanced base camp, and staged higher camps. Fixed ropes and technical sections test climbing skills while offering breathtaking views.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-10 03:32:16', '2026-03-10 03:35:05'),
(636, 301, 'How long does a Pumori expedition take?', '<p>A standard Pumori expedition lasts about 34 days, including trekking, acclimatization, climbing, and return to Kathmandu. This schedule allows proper acclimatization to minimize altitude sickness risks.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-10 03:32:16', '2026-03-10 03:35:05'),
(637, 301, 'What is the cost of a Pumori expedition?', '<p>The cost typically ranges from $20,000 to $35,000 USD, depending on support, logistics, and services included. Costs cover permits, guides, base camp support, food, and accommodation.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-10 03:32:16', '2026-03-10 03:35:05'),
(638, 301, 'Do I need a climbing permit for Pumori?', '<p>Yes, a permit from the Nepal Mountaineering Association (NMA) is mandatory. It is usually arranged through a registered expedition operator.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-10 03:32:16', '2026-03-10 03:35:05'),
(639, 301, 'What kind of training is needed for Pumori?', '<p>Climbers should have experience with high-altitude trekking and technical ice climbing. Physical fitness and previous expedition experience increase the chances of a successful summit.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-10 03:32:16', '2026-03-10 03:35:05'),
(640, 301, 'Is it possible to trek to Pumori Base Camp without climbing?', '<p>Yes, trekkers can reach Pumori Base Camp to enjoy spectacular Himalayan views without attempting the summit. It is an excellent option for adventure enthusiasts who prefer trekking over technical climbing.</p>', 11, 1, '2026-03-10 03:32:16', '2026-03-10 03:35:05'),
(641, 301, 'Are Sherpa guides included in the expedition?', '<p>Yes, professional Sherpa guides and support staff are included. They assist with climbing, safety, and logistics throughout the expedition.</p>', 12, 1, '2026-03-10 03:32:16', '2026-03-10 03:35:05'),
(642, 301, 'What type of accommodation is provided?', '<p>Accommodation includes hotels in Kathmandu, lodges during trekking, and tents at base and higher camps. Meals are provided according to the itinerary.</p>', 13, 1, '2026-03-10 03:32:16', '2026-03-10 03:35:05'),
(643, 301, 'What meals are provided during the expedition?', '<p>Breakfast is served in Kathmandu hotels, while full board meals (breakfast, lunch, dinner) are provided during trekking and climbing. Special dietary requirements can usually be accommodated if informed in advance.</p>', 14, 1, '2026-03-10 03:32:16', '2026-03-10 03:35:05'),
(644, 301, 'Is oxygen required for the Pumori summit?', '<p>Supplemental oxygen is optional but recommended for climbers who may struggle at higher altitudes. Emergency oxygen is always available at base camp.</p>', 15, 1, '2026-03-10 03:32:16', '2026-03-10 03:35:05'),
(645, 301, 'Can I rent climbing gear in Nepal?', '<p>Yes, most essential climbing gear, including crampons, harnesses, and helmets, can be rented in Kathmandu or provided by the expedition operator. Personal gear like boots and down jackets are recommended to bring.</p>', 16, 1, '2026-03-10 03:32:16', '2026-03-10 03:35:05'),
(646, 301, 'What kind of weather should I expect on Pumori?', '<p>Expect cold temperatures, snow, and strong winds at higher altitudes. Trekking sections have milder conditions, but climbers must be prepared for sudden weather changes.</p>', 17, 1, '2026-03-10 03:32:16', '2026-03-10 03:35:05'),
(647, 301, 'Is Pumori suitable for beginners?', '<p>No, Pumori is recommended only for experienced climbers with previous high-altitude expedition experience. Beginners should attempt lower peaks or guided treks first.</p>', 18, 1, '2026-03-10 03:32:16', '2026-03-10 03:35:05'),
(648, 301, 'What safety measures are in place during the climb?', '<p>Safety includes fixed ropes, high-altitude medical kits, experienced guides, and acclimatization schedules. Emergency evacuation plans are part of the expedition plan.</p>', 19, 1, '2026-03-10 03:32:16', '2026-03-10 03:35:05'),
(649, 301, 'Why should I choose Summit 8000 for my Pumori expedition?', '<p>Summit 8000 provides expert guides, base camp support, meticulous planning, and personalized assistance. Choosing them ensures a safe, successful, and memorable expedition experience.</p>', 20, 1, '2026-03-10 03:32:16', '2026-03-10 03:35:05'),
(650, 304, 'test 2', 'njhhiauwkaj;oi', 1, 1, '2026-03-10 20:20:26', '2026-03-10 20:20:26'),
(651, 304, 'test 3', 'test 3', 2, 1, '2026-03-10 20:20:26', '2026-03-10 20:20:26'),
(652, 302, 'What is Putha Hiunchuli?', '<p>Putha Hiunchuli is a 7,246-meter (23,773 feet) peak located in the remote Dolpo region of western Nepal. It\'s part of the Dhaulagiri massif and offers exceptional climbing in one of Nepal\'s least-visited areas.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-11 02:07:37', '2026-03-13 17:12:46'),
(653, 302, 'Why choose Putha Hiunchuli over other 7,000m peaks?', '<p>This mountain sees far fewer climbers than popular peaks, offering a genuine wilderness experience. The approach through Dolpo provides pristine Tibetan Buddhist culture and authentic expedition-style mountaineering.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-11 02:07:37', '2026-03-13 17:12:46'),
(654, 302, 'When is the best time to climb Putha Hiunchuli?', '<p>The optimal seasons are pre-monsoon (April-June) and post-monsoon (September-November). Pre-monsoon generally offers more stable weather and is preferred by most expeditions.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-11 02:07:37', '2026-03-13 17:12:46'),
(655, 302, 'How difficult is Putha Hiunchuli?', '<p>The climb is rated Alpine Grade PD+ to AD, meaning moderately difficult with technical sections. You\'ll encounter glacier travel, crevasse hazards, mixed climbing, and the primary challenge of operating above 7,000 meters.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-11 02:07:37', '2026-03-13 17:12:46'),
(656, 302, 'Is Putha Hiunchuli climb with supplemental oxygen?', '<p>No, it\'s typically climbed without supplemental oxygen using natural acclimatization. Emergency oxygen is available at base camp for medical situations.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-11 02:07:37', '2026-03-13 17:12:46'),
(657, 302, 'What is the summit success rate?', '<p>Success rates vary between 40-70% depending on season, weather, and team preparation. Weather is the primary factor affecting summit attempts, and safety always takes priority over summit success.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-11 02:07:37', '2026-03-13 17:12:46'),
(658, 302, 'What prior climbing experience do I need?', '<p>You must have previous high-altitude experience of at least 6,000 meters. Technical skills with crampons, ice axes, jumars, and fixed ropes are essential.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-11 02:07:38', '2026-03-13 17:12:46'),
(659, 302, 'What physical fitness level is required?', '<p>Excellent cardiovascular fitness is essential, as you should handle 6-8 hours of daily climbing with moderate loads. At least 6 months of structured training, including cardio, strength work, and elevation hiking, is recommended.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-11 02:07:38', '2026-03-13 17:12:46'),
(660, 302, 'Do I need technical climbing certification?', '<p>Formal certification isn\'t required, but documented climbing experience is essential. Mountaineering courses from recognized institutions and ice climbing experience are highly valuable.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-11 02:07:38', '2026-03-13 17:12:46'),
(661, 302, 'Can beginners attempt this expedition?', '<p>No, Putha Hiunchuli is not suitable for beginners or first-time high-altitude climbers. Start with trekking peaks (5,000-6,000m) and build experience gradually before attempting 7,000+ meter peaks.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-11 02:07:38', '2026-03-13 17:12:46'),
(662, 302, 'What\'s the minimum age requirement?', '<p>The minimum age is 18 years old with appropriate climbing experience. There\'s no maximum age limit if you meet fitness and experience requirements with recent medical clearance.</p>', 11, 1, '2026-03-11 02:07:38', '2026-03-13 17:12:46'),
(663, 302, 'How long is the entire expedition?', '<p>The complete expedition is 34 days from arrival to departure. This includes 17 days dedicated to the climbing period with built-in weather contingency days.</p>', 12, 1, '2026-03-11 02:07:38', '2026-03-13 17:12:46'),
(664, 302, 'Can the itinerary be shortened?', '<p>The itinerary cannot be significantly shortened due to acclimatization requirements and remote location. Proper acclimatization is critical for safety and success at this altitude.</p>', 13, 1, '2026-03-11 02:07:38', '2026-03-13 17:12:46'),
(665, 302, 'What if flights are delayed due to weather?', '<p>Mountain flights frequently experience weather delays this is normal in the Himalayas. We build buffer days into the itinerary, and participants should have flexible return flights.</p>', 14, 1, '2026-03-11 02:07:38', '2026-03-13 17:12:46'),
(666, 302, 'How do I get to Nepal?', '<p>Most climbers fly into Tribhuvan International Airport in Kathmandu. Major airlines serve Kathmandu from international hubs in the Middle East, Asia, and Europe.</p>', 15, 1, '2026-03-11 02:07:38', '2026-03-13 17:12:46'),
(667, 302, 'What equipment does Summit 8000 provide?', '<p>We provide group equipment including tents, ropes, cooking gear, base camp facilities, and communication equipment. High-altitude tents, fixed ropes, and snow protection are also supplied.</p>', 16, 1, '2026-03-11 02:07:38', '2026-03-13 17:12:46'),
(668, 302, 'What\'s the accommodation like during trekking?', '<p>You\'ll stay in basic teahouses and lodges with twin-sharing rooms. Facilities are simple with shared bathrooms and limited electricity.</p>', 17, 1, '2026-03-11 02:07:38', '2026-03-13 17:12:46'),
(669, 305, 'What is the height of Tilicho Peak?', '<p>Tilicho Peak stands at an altitude of 7,134 meters (23,406 ft) above sea level and is considered a challenging expedition for climbers with previous high-altitude experience.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-11 03:18:02', '2026-03-13 17:08:54'),
(670, 305, 'Where is Tilicho Peak located?', '<p>Tilicho Peak is in the Annapurna region of Nepal, inside the Annapurna Conservation Area, north of the Annapurna range, near Tilicho Lake.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-11 03:18:02', '2026-03-13 17:08:54'),
(671, 305, 'What is the best season to climb Tilicho Peak?', '<p>The best time to climb Tilicho Peak is pre-monsoon (April–May) and post-monsoon (September–November) when the weather is stable, and the skies are clear</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-11 03:18:02', '2026-03-13 17:08:54'),
(672, 305, 'How many days does the expedition take?', '<p>Typically, the expedition takes 30 to 36 days, including trekking, acclimatization, and climbing days. However, it can be more and less depending upon your pace.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-11 03:18:02', '2026-03-13 17:08:54'),
(673, 305, 'What level of experience is required?', '<p>You should have prior high-altitude trekking or climbing experience and be physically fit for long trekking days and steep climbing.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-11 03:18:02', '2026-03-13 17:08:54'),
(674, 305, 'Is a guide or Sherpa necessary?', '<p>Yes, a guide or a sherpa is necessary for the Tilicho peak expeditions because its a high-altitude mountain was your every step counts due to which Hiring an experienced guide or climbing Sherpa is highly recommended for safety, navigation, and support.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-11 03:18:02', '2026-03-13 17:08:54'),
(675, 305, 'What meals are provided during the expedition?', '<p>Required meals that are necessary for your body to function in the mountains, such as the breakfast, lunch, and dinner during the trek and at the expeditions is provided.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-11 03:18:02', '2026-03-13 17:08:54'),
(676, 305, 'What personal gear do I need to bring?', '<p>Essential gear includes climbing boots, crampons, harness, helmet, down jacket, sleeping bag, gloves, and trekking poles.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-11 03:18:02', '2026-03-13 17:08:54'),
(677, 305, 'Is altitude sickness a concern on Tilicho Peak?', '<p>Yes, the peak is high-altitude at an altitude of 7,134 meters (23,406 ft), so proper acclimatization and monitoring for symptoms of AMS (Acute Mountain Sickness) are essential.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-11 03:18:02', '2026-03-13 17:08:54'),
(678, 305, 'Can beginners attempt Tilicho Peak?', '<p>It is not recommended for complete beginners. Prior trekking or climbing experience at high altitudes is strongly advised.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-11 03:18:02', '2026-03-13 17:08:54'),
(679, 305, 'Are rescue and emergency services available?', '<p>Emergency evacuation by helicopter is possible but expensive. Guides are trained in basic first aid, and climbers are encouraged to carry insurance covering high-altitude rescue.</p>', 11, 1, '2026-03-11 03:18:02', '2026-03-13 17:08:54'),
(680, 305, 'What is the approximate cost of the expedition?', '<p>Costs vary depending on services, group size, and season but generally range between $3,000–$5,000 USD per person for a fully supported expedition.</p>', 12, 1, '2026-03-11 03:18:02', '2026-03-13 17:08:54'),
(681, 306, 'What is the best season to climb Pachermo Peak?', '<p>The ideal seasons are pre-monsoon (March to May) and post-monsoon (late September to November) when skies are clear, and the weather is stable for climbing and trekking.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-11 20:33:49', '2026-03-11 20:51:08'),
(682, 306, 'Do I need prior climbing experience?', '<p>Basic trekking experience is required. No advanced technical climbing is mandatory, but climbers must be physically fit. Our guides provide full training on snow, ice, and glacier techniques.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-11 20:33:49', '2026-03-11 20:51:08'),
(683, 306, 'How difficult is the Pachermo Peak climb?', '<p>It’s a moderately challenging 6,000-meter expedition. The trek involves high-altitude terrain, glaciers, and steep ridges. With proper acclimatization and guidance, it is achievable for fit adventure seekers.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-11 20:33:49', '2026-03-11 20:51:08'),
(684, 306, 'How long is the Pachermo Peak Climbing Expedition?', '<p>The full itinerary spans 16 days, including acclimatization, trekking, and summit day. The climb is short for a Himalayan peak but requires endurance and focus.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-11 20:33:49', '2026-03-11 20:51:08'),
(685, 306, 'What is the altitude at Pachermo Peak?', '<p>Pachermo Peak stands at 6,187–6,273 meters (20,300–20,581 feet) above sea level.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-11 20:33:49', '2026-03-11 20:51:08'),
(686, 306, 'What is included in the expedition support?', '<p>Our team provides experienced guides, porters, climbing gear, technical training, first aid, and emergency evacuation support. We prioritize safety and summit success.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-11 20:33:49', '2026-03-11 20:51:08'),
(687, 306, 'Can beginners attempt Pachermo Peak?', '<p>Yes, beginners with good physical fitness can attempt it, thanks to structured acclimatization, expert guidance, and technical training provided by our team.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-11 20:33:49', '2026-03-11 20:51:08'),
(688, 306, 'What kind of accommodation will I stay in during the trek?', '<p>You will stay in local teahouses in villages and tented camps at high camps and base camp. Comfort is ensured, but it’s basic to suit high-altitude conditions.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-11 20:33:49', '2026-03-11 20:51:08'),
(689, 306, 'How can I prepare for Pachermo Peak?', '<p>Cardio fitness, strength training, and hiking experience are recommended. Familiarity with walking on snow or using trekking poles will be helpful. Pre-trip briefings and equipment guidance are provided.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-11 20:33:49', '2026-03-11 20:51:08'),
(690, 306, 'Is Pachermo Peak crowded?', '<p>No. The Rolwaling region is remote and less frequented, offering a peaceful Himalayan experience away from Everest and Annapurna crowds.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-11 20:33:49', '2026-03-11 20:51:08'),
(691, 307, 'Do I need prior mountaineering experience to climb Tent Peak?', '<p>While Tent Peak is classified as a trekking peak and is suitable for motivated beginners, some prior physical preparation is strongly advised. You do not need formal technical mountaineering experience, but you should be comfortable with long trekking days, high altitude, and basic fitness challenges. Before the expedition, we recommend completing at least 3–4 months of cardiovascular and endurance training (hiking, trail running, cycling). Your climbing guide will teach all essential techniques crampon use, ice axe handling, rope work, and rope-team movement during the Base Camp and High Camp acclimatization days.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-12 02:13:30', '2026-03-12 02:37:48'),
(692, 307, 'What is the best season to climb Tent Peak?', '<p>Tent Peak can be climbed in two main seasons: Spring (March to May) and Autumn (September to November). Both offer excellent conditions with high summit success rates. Spring (March–May) is particularly popular because rhododendron forests are in full bloom along the Annapurna trekking route, creating spectacular scenery. Autumn (October–November) offers the clearest skies and sharpest mountain views. Winter (December–February) and Monsoon (June–August) climbs are possible but come with significant weather challenges and are not recommended for first-time Himalayan climbers.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-12 02:13:30', '2026-03-12 02:37:48'),
(693, 307, 'How difficult is the Tent Peak climb on summit day?', '<p>Summit day is the most demanding part of the expedition. The ascent begins in the early hours (around midnight to 1:00 AM) and involves 5–7 hours of climbing on snow and ice slopes, using crampons, ice axe, and fixed ropes with guide support. The technical difficulty is graded PD (Peu Difficile) on the Alpine scale meaning it involves moderate glacier travel and snow slopes up to 45–50 degrees but no extreme vertical ice or rock sections. The main challenges are altitude, cold, and endurance rather than technical complexity. Turnaround times are strictly enforced by your guide for safety. If weather deteriorates or a climber shows signs of serious altitude sickness, descent is non-negotiable.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-12 02:13:30', '2026-03-12 02:37:48'),
(694, 307, 'What personal gear and equipment do I need to bring?', '<p>Essential personal mountaineering gear includes: double-layered mountaineering boots (compatible with crampons), technical 12-point crampons, a mountaineering ice axe, a climbing harness, a certified climbing helmet, and a down suit or very warm layering system rated to at least -20°C. You will also need a sleeping bag rated to -20°C or below, moisture-wicking base layers, insulating mid-layers, waterproof outer shells (jacket and trousers), warm gloves (liner + outer), high-altitude goggles, UV-protection sunglasses, gaiters, and trekking poles. Summit 8000 provides a comprehensive personal gear checklist upon booking confirmation. We can also arrange rental of certain items (crampons, ice axe, harness) in Kathmandu for an additional fee.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-12 02:13:30', '2026-03-12 02:37:48'),
(695, 307, 'What permits are required and does Summit 8000 arrange them?', '<p>Three permits are required: (1) Tent Peak Climbing Permit issued by the Nepal Mountaineering Association (NMA); (2) Annapurna Conservation Area Permit (ACAP); and (3) the TIMS (Trekkers\' Information Management System) card. Yes Summit 8000 Adventure arranges and processes all three permits on your behalf. Permit costs are fully included in the expedition package price. You simply need to provide a passport-sized photo and a copy of your passport at the time of booking confirmation.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-12 02:13:30', '2026-03-12 02:37:48'),
(696, 307, 'Is travel insurance mandatory, and what should it cover?', '<p>Yes, comprehensive travel insurance is absolutely mandatory for all participants. This is a non-negotiable safety requirement. Your policy must cover: helicopter rescue and evacuation from altitude (up to 5,700 m), emergency medical treatment and hospitalization, trip cancellation and curtailment, and personal baggage loss. We strongly recommend purchasing your policy well in advance of travel and carrying both a digital and physical copy throughout the expedition. Your insurance details must be shared with Summit 8000 Adventure before departure.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-12 02:13:30', '2026-03-12 02:37:48'),
(697, 307, 'What is the altitude sickness risk, and how is it managed?', '<p>Acute Mountain Sickness (AMS) is a real risk above 3,500 m. Symptoms include headache, nausea, dizziness, fatigue, and disturbed sleep. In rare cases it can progress to HACE (High Altitude Cerebral Edema) or HAPE (High Altitude Pulmonary Edema), both of which are life-threatening. The itinerary is carefully designed with gradual altitude gain and rest days to support acclimatization. Your guide is trained in Wilderness First Aid and AMS recognition. The expedition carries a pulse oximeter, supplemental oxygen kit, and a Gamow bag at Base Camp. If you are concerned about AMS, consult your physician about Diamox (acetazolamide) before departure. Stay well hydrated (3–4 litres per day above Deurali), ascend slowly, and never ignore symptoms. The golden rule: never ascend with AMS symptoms.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-12 02:13:30', '2026-03-12 02:37:48'),
(698, 307, 'How many people are in each expedition group?', '<p>Summit 8000 Adventure runs Tent Peak expeditions for groups of 1 to 10 climbers. Smaller groups (1–4 climbers) receive a 1:1 guide-to-climber ratio on summit day, which is the gold standard for safety and support. For groups of 5 or more, an additional climbing guide is provided. We do not allow summit-day groups exceeding a 1:4 guide-to-climber ratio. Private expeditions can be arranged for individuals or groups at any time during the climbing seasons. Contact us for customized group pricing.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-12 02:13:30', '2026-03-12 02:37:48'),
(699, 307, 'What is the summit success rate for Tent Peak?', '<p>Summit 8000 Adventure maintains a strong summit success rate of approximately 75–85% across all Tent Peak expeditions, which is above the industry average for this peak. Success depends primarily on weather conditions, individual acclimatization, and physical fitness. Our experienced guides use real-time weather forecasting to optimize summit day timing. In seasons with stable weather windows, success rates reach 90%+. It is important to note that even an unsuccessful summit attempt can be an extraordinary Himalayan experience. The journey through the Annapurna Sanctuary alone is worth every step.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-12 02:13:30', '2026-03-12 02:37:48'),
(700, 307, 'Can the itinerary be customized or extended?', '<p>Yes, Summit 8000 Adventure offers full itinerary customization. Popular add-ons include extra acclimatization days at ABC or Tent Peak Base Camp, an extension to include the Mardi Himal Trek, a Chitwan National Park safari post-expedition, or city tours of Kathmandu\'s UNESCO heritage sites. Pre-expedition training treks (such as the Annapurna Circuit or Mardi Himal) can also be combined with the Tent Peak climb for clients who want additional acclimatization or trekking experience. Contact our team with your preferences and we will design a bespoke Himalayan adventure tailored to your goals and timeline.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-12 02:13:30', '2026-03-12 02:37:48'),
(701, 308, 'Where is Naya Kanga Peak located?', '<p>Naya Kanga Peak (Ganja La Chuli) lies in the beautiful Langtang region of Nepal, inside Langtang National Park. The mountain rises above the Langtang Valley and is commonly approached via Kyanjin Gompa, a popular trekking destination.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-12 03:32:00', '2026-03-12 03:33:50'),
(702, 308, 'What is the height of Naya Kanga Peak?', '<p>The summit of Naya Kanga Peak stands at 5,844 meters (19,173 feet) above sea level, making it one of the attractive trekking peaks in the Langtang region.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-12 03:32:00', '2026-03-12 03:33:50'),
(703, 308, 'How difficult is Naya Kanga Peak climbing?', '<p>Naya Kanga is considered a moderately technical trekking peak. Climbers should be comfortable trekking at high altitude and using basic mountaineering equipment such as crampons, ropes, and an ice axe.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-12 03:32:00', '2026-03-12 03:33:50'),
(704, 308, 'Do I need previous climbing experience for Naya Kanga?', '<p>Previous high-altitude trekking experience is recommended. Basic mountaineering skills are helpful, but many climbers successfully summit the peak with guidance from experienced climbing guides.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-12 03:32:00', '2026-03-12 03:33:50'),
(705, 308, 'How long does the Naya Kanga Peak climbing trip take?', '<p>Most expeditions take 16–18 days, including trekking through Langtang Valley, acclimatization days, and the summit attempt.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-12 03:32:00', '2026-03-12 03:33:50'),
(706, 308, 'What is the best time to climb Naya Kanga Peak?', '<p>The best seasons are spring (March–May) and autumn (September–November) when weather conditions are stable and the mountain views are clear.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-12 03:32:00', '2026-03-12 03:33:50'),
(707, 308, 'Do I need a permit for Naya Kanga Peak climbing?', '<p>Yes. Climbers need a Naya Kanga climbing permit issued by the Nepal Mountaineering Association, along with a Langtang National Park entry permit.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-12 03:32:00', '2026-03-12 03:33:50'),
(708, 308, 'What is the usual route for Naya Kanga Peak climbing?', '<p>The expedition normally begins with a drive from Kathmandu to Syabrubesi, followed by trekking through Langtang Valley to Kyanjin Gompa, and then crossing Ganja La Pass before the summit climb.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-12 03:32:00', '2026-03-12 03:33:50'),
(709, 308, 'What kind of accommodation is available during the climb?', '<p>Trekkers stay in tea houses during the trekking section and tented camps during the climbing phase near base camp and high cam</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-12 03:32:00', '2026-03-12 03:33:50'),
(710, 308, 'Is altitude sickness a concern on this climb?', '<p>Yes. Since the climb reaches nearly 6,000 meters, proper acclimatization and gradual ascent are important to reduce the risk of altitude sickness.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-12 03:32:00', '2026-03-12 03:33:50'),
(711, 308, 'Do I need a guide for Naya Kanga Peak climbing?', '<p>Yes, climbing Naya Kanga Peak requires a licensed climbing guide for safety, route navigation, and technical support during the summit attempt.</p>', 11, 1, '2026-03-12 03:32:00', '2026-03-12 03:33:50'),
(712, 308, 'What type of climbing equipment is required?', '<p>Climbers typically use crampons, ropes, an ice axe, a helmet, a harness, and mountaineering boots for the summit section.</p>', 12, 1, '2026-03-12 03:32:00', '2026-03-12 03:33:50'),
(713, 308, 'What mountains can be seen from the summit of Naya Kanga?', '<p>From the summit, climbers can enjoy spectacular views of Langtang Lirung, Dorje Lakpa, Shishapangma, and other Himalayan peaks.</p>', 13, 1, '2026-03-12 03:32:00', '2026-03-12 03:33:50'),
(714, 308, 'How physically demanding is the expedition?', '<p>The climb requires good physical fitness and endurance, as trekkers walk several hours daily and climb at high altitude in challenging terrain.</p>', 14, 1, '2026-03-12 03:32:00', '2026-03-12 03:33:50'),
(715, 308, 'What is the success rate of Naya Kanga Peak climbing?', '<p>With proper acclimatization, good weather conditions, and experienced guides, the success rate for climbers is generally quite high compared to more technical Himalayan peaks.</p>', 15, 1, '2026-03-12 03:32:00', '2026-03-12 03:33:50'),
(716, 308, 'Can beginners attempt Naya Kanga Peak?', '<p>Fit beginners with trekking experience and proper preparation can attempt the climb with guidance from a professional climbing team.</p>', 16, 1, '2026-03-12 03:32:00', '2026-03-12 03:33:50'),
(717, 308, 'What makes Naya Kanga Peak special?', '<p>Naya Kanga offers a combination of trekking adventure and technical climbing, along with stunning landscapes, glaciers, and panoramic Himalayan views.</p>', 17, 1, '2026-03-12 03:32:00', '2026-03-12 03:33:50'),
(718, 309, 'Why should I climb Chulu East Peak in Nepal?', '<p>Chulu East is the best choice if you want to experience Himalayan climbing without tackling extremely technical peaks. The expedition combines trekking through scenic villages and the Manang Valley with a real climbing experience. Plus, the summit rewards you with breathtaking views of Annapurna II, Tilicho Peak, Gangapurna, and the Manaslu range.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-13 03:19:28', '2026-03-13 03:21:22'),
(719, 309, 'What is the difficulty level of the Chulu East Peak climb?', '<p>The difficulty level of the Chulu East Peak expedition is suitable for trekkers with some hiking experience who want to try mountaineering. The climb involves snow slopes and glacier sections, but with the guidance of our experienced climbing team, it’s achievable even for first-time Himalayan climbers.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-13 03:19:28', '2026-03-13 03:21:22'),
(720, 309, 'How long is the Chulu East Peak expedition?', '<p>The Chulu East peak expedition typically takes 12 days, including trekking, acclimatization, summit attempt, and return to Kathmandu.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-13 03:19:28', '2026-03-13 03:21:22'),
(721, 309, 'What is the best time to climb Chulu East Peak?', '<p>The best time to climb Chulu East Peak is spring (March to May) and autumn (September to November). During these months, the weather is stable, the skies are clear, and mountain views are at their best. Spring offers blooming rhododendrons, while autumn gives crisp, clear panoramas of the Himalayas.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-13 03:19:28', '2026-03-13 03:21:22'),
(722, 309, 'What is included in the cost of the Chulu East peak expedition?', '<p>The Chulu East peak expeditions cost usually covers permits, experienced guides, support staff, accommodation in Kathmandu and along the trek, meals during trekking, transportation in Nepal, climbing equipment, and acclimatization support.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-13 03:19:28', '2026-03-13 03:21:22'),
(723, 309, 'Do I need prior mountaineering experience to attempt Chulu East Peak?', '<p>No, you will not need prior technical mountaineering experience to attempt Chulu East Peak. Because basic trekking experience helps, and our guides provide training on crampons, ice axes, and climbing techniques during the expedition.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-13 03:19:28', '2026-03-13 03:21:22'),
(724, 309, 'How physically fit should I be for this Chulu East expedition?', '<p>You will need to be at a good level of fitness for the Chulu East peak expedition. You should be comfortable with daily treks of 4–7 hours and able to handle moderate altitude. Regular cardio and strength training before the expedition is highly recommended.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-13 03:19:28', '2026-03-13 03:21:22'),
(725, 309, 'What happens if the weather is bad on summit day?', '<p>We have a reserve day built into the itinerary for weather delays or extra acclimatization. Safety is our top priority, and summit attempts may be rescheduled to ensure a safe climb.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-13 03:19:28', '2026-03-13 03:21:22'),
(726, 309, 'What kind of accommodation can I expect?', '<p>Accommodation includes 4–5 star hotels in Kathmandu and comfortable teahouses along the trek. Teahouses provide basic but clean facilities and local meals, helping you experience mountain life while staying comfortable.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-13 03:19:28', '2026-03-13 03:21:22'),
(727, 309, 'How do I get to Chulu East Peak from Kathmandu?', '<p>To get to Chulu east peak from Kathmandu, you will need a scenic drive from Kathmandu to Chame, the gateway to the Annapurna region, followed by trekking through Manang Valley and higher alpine landscapes toward the peak.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-13 03:19:28', '2026-03-13 03:21:22'),
(728, 309, 'Will I be guided throughout the expedition?', '<p>Yes, our experienced Himalayan guides and climbing team accompany you throughout the trek and summit attempt, ensuring safety, proper acclimatization, and technical support during the climb.</p>', 11, 1, '2026-03-13 03:19:28', '2026-03-13 03:21:22'),
(729, 310, 'How difficult is the Kusum Kanguru expedition?', '<p>The Kusum Kanguru expedition is one of the most technically demanding climbs in the Khumbu region. It involves steep rock, ice, and mixed terrain that requires prior alpine experience, confident crampon and ice axe technique, and solid rope management skills.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-15 20:54:34', '2026-03-15 21:04:58'),
(730, 310, 'What is the total duration of the expedition?', '<p>The Kusum Kanguru expedition is 18 days long. You can extend the itinerary based on your schedule, acclimatization needs, or weather conditions. Contact Summit 8000 for a customized itinerary.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-15 20:54:34', '2026-03-15 21:04:58'),
(731, 310, 'How high is Kusum Kanguru?', '<p>Kusum Kanguru stands at 6,367 metres (20,883 feet) above sea level. On a clear summit day, the peak offers direct views of Everest, Lhotse, and Ama Dablam.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-15 20:54:34', '2026-03-15 21:04:58'),
(732, 310, 'How do you get from Kathmandu to Kusum Kanguru?', '<p>From Kathmandu, you take a 35-minute domestic flight to Lukla, followed by a seven to nine-day trek through the Hinku Valley to reach Kusum Kanguru Base Camp at 4,900 metres.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-15 20:54:34', '2026-03-15 21:04:58'),
(733, 310, 'Which is the best route to climb Kusum Kanguru?', '<p>The best route to climb Kusum Kanguru is the North Face. It offers a direct and technically rewarding line with sustained ice and mixed terrain. Summit 8000 installs fixed ropes on the most exposed sections for safe ascent and descent.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-15 20:54:34', '2026-03-15 21:04:58'),
(734, 310, 'When is the best season to climb Kusum Kanguru?', '<p>The best seasons to climb Kusum Kanguru are spring (March–May) and autumn (September–November). Both seasons offer the most stable weather conditions and the highest summit success rates.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-15 20:54:34', '2026-03-15 21:04:58'),
(735, 310, 'What does the Kusum Kanguru expedition cost include?', '<p>The Kusum Kanguru expedition cost includes airport transfers, Kathmandu hotel accommodation, domestic flights, all climbing permits, Sherpa and guide team, teahouse and camp meals, Base Camp and high-camp setup, fixed rope installation, and the farewell dinner.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-15 20:54:34', '2026-03-15 21:04:58'),
(736, 310, 'What is excluded from the Kusum Kanguru expedition cost?', '<p>The Kusum Kanguru expedition cost excludes international flights, Nepal visa fees, personal climbing gear, sleeping bag, travel and evacuation insurance, crew tips, alcoholic beverages, and any costs arising from weather delays or itinerary extensions.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-15 20:54:35', '2026-03-15 21:04:58'),
(737, 310, 'Is travel insurance required for the Kusum Kanguru expedition?', '<p>Yes, travel and helicopter evacuation insurance is mandatory for the Kusum Kanguru expedition. Confirmed insurance documentation must be submitted before the expedition begins.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-15 20:54:35', '2026-03-15 21:04:58'),
(738, 310, 'Why do climbers choose Summit 8000 for the Kusum Kanguru expedition?', '<p>Climbers choose Summit 8000 for the Kusum Kanguru expedition because of our extensive field experience across Nepal\'s Himalayan range. We manage all logistics in-house permits, Sherpa staffing, high-camp setup, and emergency protocols ensuring a safe and well-organized climb from start to finish.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-15 20:54:35', '2026-03-15 21:04:58'),
(739, 310, 'Is there an acclimatization day on the Kusum Kanguru expedition?', '<p>Yes, the Kusum Kanguru expedition includes a dedicated acclimatization day at Thangnak (4,350m) on Day 8. Climbers take a short hike to higher elevation before returning to sleep low, preparing the body for the upper mountain.</p>', 11, 1, '2026-03-15 20:54:35', '2026-03-15 21:04:58'),
(740, 310, 'What happens if weather prevents a summit attempt on Kusum Kanguru?', '<p>If weather prevents a summit attempt on Kusum Kanguru, Summit 8000 guides make all decisions based on real-time conditions. Contingency time is built into the program where possible. Costs from extended stays or rescheduled flights due to weather are not covered by the standard package.</p>', 12, 1, '2026-03-15 20:54:35', '2026-03-15 21:04:58'),
(741, 311, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2026-03-15 21:28:39', '2026-03-15 21:28:39'),
(742, 312, 'Is it good idea to trek to Everest base camp?', '<p>Yes, trekking to Everest Base Camp is an absolutely wonderful idea for anyone who loves the outdoors and is looking for a truly life-changing adventure. The Everest Base Camp trek rewards you with panoramic views of the world\'s highest peaks including Everest (8,849 m), Lhotse, Nuptse, and Ama Dablam, while immersing you in the rich Sherpa culture, ancient Buddhist monasteries, and the raw beauty of the Khumbu Valley. It is one of the most celebrated treks on Earth for good reason and it does not require technical climbing skills, making it achievable for any fit and determined traveller.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-19 17:31:58', '2026-03-20 13:02:54'),
(743, 312, 'How difficult is the Everest base camp?', '<p>The Everest Base Camp trek is considered a moderately challenging to strenuous trek, but it is not technically difficult — you do not need any mountaineering experience or specialist equipment to complete it. The main challenge of the Everest Base Camp trek is the high altitude, with the trail reaching 5,364 m at Base Camp and 5,545 m at Kala Patthar. Long walking days of 5–7 hours, steep ascents such as the climb to Namche Bazaar, and cold temperatures at higher elevations all test your stamina. A reasonable level of fitness, proper preparation, and following a slow acclimatization schedule will make this trek very achievable.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-19 17:31:58', '2026-03-20 13:02:54'),
(744, 312, 'How much does the Everest base camp trek cost?', '<p>The total cost of the Everest Base Camp trek typically ranges from $1,200 to $2,500 USD for a fully guided experience, which includes your Lukla flights, teahouse accommodation, three meals a day, a licensed guide, and a porter. On top of this, you will need to budget for the Sagarmatha National Park entry permit (around $30) and the Khumbu Pasang Lhamu Rural Municipality fee (around $20). Budget trekkers going more independently can bring the cost of the Everest Base Camp trek down to around $800–$1,000, though hiring at least a guide is always strongly recommended for safety at high altitude.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-19 17:31:58', '2026-03-20 13:02:54'),
(745, 312, 'What permits do I need for the Everest base camp?', '<p>To trek to Everest Base Camp, you need two main permits. The first is the Sagarmatha National Park entry permit (approximately $30 USD), which covers your entry into the UNESCO World Heritage protected area that the entire route passes through. The second is the Khumbu Pasang Lhamu Rural Municipality permit (approximately $20 USD), which is required for trekking in the Khumbu region. Both permits are arranged in Kathmandu before you fly to Lukla, and a licensed trekking agency or guide will typically handle the full permit process on your behalf.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-19 17:31:58', '2026-03-20 13:02:54'),
(746, 312, 'Do I need guide for the Everest base camp?', '<p>While the Everest Base Camp trek is technically possible without a guide, hiring a licensed, experienced guide is very strongly recommended for safety, navigation, and overall experience. A good guide for the Everest Base Camp trek manages your acclimatization schedule, identifies early signs of altitude sickness, communicates with local teahouses, and can arrange emergency evacuations if needed — all things that are very difficult to handle alone at high altitude. Your guide should hold a valid Nepal Tourism Board (NTB) license and have specific experience on the Everest trail. Booking through a registered trekking agency in Kathmandu is the safest and most reliable way to find one.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-19 17:31:58', '2026-03-20 13:02:54'),
(747, 312, 'What is altitude sickness and How do I avoid it in EBC trek?', '<p>Altitude sickness medically known as Acute Mountain Sickness (AMS) is a condition caused by ascending too quickly to high altitude, where reduced oxygen levels cause symptoms including headaches, nausea, dizziness, fatigue, and disrupted sleep. On the Everest Base Camp trek, altitude sickness is the most common reason trekkers are forced to turn back or require helicopter evacuation. To avoid altitude sickness on the EBC trek, follow a gradual acclimatization schedule (built into a proper 16-day itinerary), take mandatory rest days at Namche Bazaar and Dingboche, drink at least 3–4 litres of water daily, avoid alcohol at altitude, and never push forward if you are experiencing worsening symptoms. The golden rule of high-altitude trekking is: walk high, sleep low.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-19 17:31:58', '2026-03-20 13:02:54'),
(748, 312, 'Do I need travel insurance for Everest base camp?', '<p>Yes, travel insurance is absolutely essential not optional for the Everest Base Camp trek. Your insurance policy must specifically cover high-altitude trekking above 5,000 m and emergency helicopter evacuation, as a rescue helicopter from the upper Khumbu can cost anywhere from $3,000 to $10,000 USD or more without coverage. Standard travel insurance policies often do not include high-altitude activities, so always read the fine print and confirm your policy covers the EBC trek at its maximum elevation of 5,545 m (Kala Patthar). Purchasing comprehensive insurance before departing for Nepal is one of the most important steps in your pre-trek preparation.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-19 17:31:58', '2026-03-20 13:02:54'),
(749, 312, 'How cold does it get on the Everest base camp trek?', '<p>Temperatures on the Everest Base Camp trek vary significantly depending on the season and elevation. During the peak autumn season (October–November), daytime temperatures at lower elevations like Namche Bazaar sit around 10–15°C, while at Gorakshep (5,164 m) nights regularly drop to -10°C or colder. In spring, similar daytime conditions apply but nights remain very cold above 4,000 m. At Kala Patthar (5,545 m) during the pre-dawn summit, temperatures can feel bitterly cold with wind chill. Packing a high-quality down jacket, thermal base layers, and a sleeping bag rated to at least -10°C is essential for a comfortable Everest Base Camp trek experience.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-19 17:31:58', '2026-03-20 13:02:54'),
(750, 312, 'Can beginners do the Everest base camp trek?', '<p>Yes, beginners can absolutely do the Everest Base Camp trek and thousands of first-time trekkers complete it successfully every year. The Everest Base Camp trail does not require any technical climbing skills, ropes, or mountaineering experience. What beginners need before attempting the EBC trek is a solid base of cardiovascular fitness (regular hiking, running, or cycling in the months before departure), a well-paced 16-day itinerary with proper acclimatization days built in, and a licensed guide who can manage the pace and monitor health. Starting with some day hikes or multi-day treks before attempting EBC is a great way for beginners to build confidence and test their gear.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-19 17:31:58', '2026-03-20 13:02:54'),
(751, 313, 'What is the Annapurna Sanctuary Trek?', '<p>The Annapurna Sanctuary Trek, also known as the Annapurna Base Camp (ABC) Trek, is a popular trekking route in Nepal that leads to a natural amphitheater surrounded by Himalaya peaks above 6,000 meters. It offers close-up views of Annapurna I, Machapuchare, and Annapurna South.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-24 02:43:07', '2026-03-24 02:46:40'),
(752, 313, 'How hard is the Annapurna Sanctuary Trek?', '<p>The Annapurna Sanctuary Trek is a moderate trek. It involves daily walking of 5–7 hours with gradual altitude gain up to 4,130 meters. While no technical climbing is required, good fitness and stamina are necessary.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-24 02:43:07', '2026-03-24 02:46:40'),
(753, 313, 'Can beginners do the Annapurna Base Camp (ABC) Trek?', '<p>Yes, beginners can do the ABC trek if they have basic fitness and prepare properly. The trail is well-marked, has teahouses, and does not require technical skills, making it beginner-friendly compared to high-altitude expeditions.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-24 02:43:07', '2026-03-24 02:46:40'),
(754, 313, 'How many days does it take to hike ABC?', '<p>The Annapurna Base Camp trek usually takes 10 to 15 days, depending on your itinerary, pace, and starting point like Pokhar</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-24 02:43:07', '2026-03-24 02:46:40'),
(755, 313, 'How difficult is the ABC trek?', '<p>The ABC trek is considered moderately difficult. The main challenges are long walking hours, steep stair sections, and altitude above 3,000 meters, which may cause mild altitude sickness.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-24 02:43:07', '2026-03-24 02:46:40'),
(756, 313, 'Which is easier, ABC or Everest Base Camp (EBC)?', '<p>The Annapurna Base Camp trek is generally easier than Everest Base Camp. ABC is shorter, lower in altitude, and has less extreme weather conditions compared to EBC.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-24 02:43:07', '2026-03-24 02:46:40'),
(757, 313, 'Is ABC trek worth it?', '<p>Yes, the ABC trek is absolutely worth it. It offers stunning mountain views, diverse landscapes, cultural villages, and a close-up Himalayan experience at a relatively affordable cost.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-24 02:43:07', '2026-03-24 02:46:40'),
(758, 313, 'What is the difference between the Annapurna Circuit and the ABC trek?', '<p>The Annapurna Circuit is a longer trek (12–20 days) that circles the Annapurna range, while ABC trek is shorter (7–12 days) and goes directly to Annapurna Base Camp.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-24 02:43:07', '2026-03-24 02:46:40'),
(759, 313, 'Which month is best for the Annapurna Base Camp trek?', '<p>The best months are March–May (spring) and September–November (autumn) for clear skies, stable weather, and best mountain views.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-24 02:43:07', '2026-03-24 02:46:40');
INSERT INTO `cl_trip_faqs` (`id`, `trip_detail_id`, `title`, `content`, `ordering`, `status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(760, 313, 'Can you sleep at Annapurna Base Camp?', '<p>Yes, you can stay overnight at Annapurna Base Camp in teahouses. It is safe and offers an unforgettable sunrise view over the Annapurna massif.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-24 02:43:07', '2026-03-24 02:46:40'),
(761, 313, 'What are the biggest risks on the ABC trek?', '<p>The main risks include: * Altitude sickness * Slippery trails and steep stairs * Sudden weather changes * Avalanches in winter (rare but possible)</p>', 11, 1, '2026-03-24 02:43:07', '2026-03-24 02:46:40'),
(762, 313, 'What is the most beautiful trek in Nepal?', '<p>The Annapurna Base Camp trek is considered one of the most beautiful treks in Nepal because of its diverse scenery, cultural villages, and panoramic Himalayan views.</p>', 12, 1, '2026-03-24 02:43:07', '2026-03-24 02:46:40'),
(763, 314, 'How long is the Annapurna Circuit Trek?', '<p>The Annapurna circuit trek spans approximately 179 km (111 miles) and typically takes 17 days, including acclimatization days. Daily trekking distances vary between 10 and 20 km, depending on the terrain and stops.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-24 21:48:43', '2026-03-24 21:55:04'),
(764, 314, 'What is the total elevation gain on the Annapurna circuit trek?', '<p>The total elevation gain on the Annapurna circuit trek ranges from 1,000 meters (3,280 ft) in the lowlands to 5,416 meters (17,769 ft) at Thorong La Pass, the highest point of the circuit.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-24 21:48:43', '2026-03-24 21:55:04'),
(765, 314, 'What is the best time to do the Annapurna Circuit Trek?', '<p>The best time to do the Annapurna circuit trek is from spring (March–May) and autumn (September–November) for clear skies, moderate temperatures, and stable trekking conditions. Winter is cold and snowy at higher altitudes, while the monsoon season (June–August) brings heavy rain and slippery trails.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-24 21:48:43', '2026-03-24 21:55:04'),
(766, 314, 'How much does the Annapurna Circuit Trek cost?', '<p>Annapurna circuit trek Costs vary depending on your style of travel. On average: * Budget trekking: $800–$1,200 per person * Mid-range trekking: $1,200–$1,800 per person * Luxury trekking: $1,800+ per person This usually includes accommodation, meals, guide/porter services, and permits (TIMS and ACAP).</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-24 21:48:43', '2026-03-24 21:55:04'),
(767, 314, 'What does the ACT cost include?', '<p>The ACT cost includes are: * Accommodation in tea houses/lodges * Breakfast, lunch, and dinner during trekking * Experienced trekking guide and porter * Trekking permits (TIMS, ACAP) * Transportation from Kathmandu to the starting point and back</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-24 21:48:43', '2026-03-24 21:55:04'),
(768, 314, 'Do I need a guide or porter for the Annapurna circuit trek?', '<p>Yes, you will need a guide and porter for the Annapurna circuit trek becuase its important for you to look after your safety, navigation, and cultural insights. Porters can help carry heavy luggage and make your trek more comfortable.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-24 21:48:43', '2026-03-24 21:55:04'),
(769, 314, 'How difficult is the Annapurna Circuit Trek?', '<p>The Annapurna circuit tre is moderate to strenuous, with long walking days and high-altitude challenges. Proper physical preparation, acclimatization, and pacing are essential to avoid altitude sickness.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-24 21:48:43', '2026-03-24 21:55:04'),
(770, 314, 'What kind of accommodation can I expect on the trek?', '<p>Most nights are spent in tea houses or lodges offering basic rooms with beds, blankets, and shared bathrooms. Hot showers are available in larger villages but may be limited in remote areas.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-24 21:48:43', '2026-03-24 21:55:04'),
(771, 314, 'Can I do the Annapurna circuit trek independently or with a tour operator?', '<p>Both are possible. Independent trekkers should have trekking experience and good navigation skills. Joining a tour operator ensures support with logistics, permits, accommodation, and local knowledge.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-24 21:48:43', '2026-03-24 21:55:04'),
(772, 314, 'Is the Annapurna Circuit Trek safe?', '<p>Yes, generally, the Annapurna circuit trek is safe. Risks include altitude sickness, weather changes, and slips/falls, so it’s important to acclimatize, trek in good conditions, and follow safety advice from guides.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-24 21:48:43', '2026-03-24 21:55:04'),
(773, 314, 'Are there cultural experiences on the trek?', '<p>Absolutely. You’ll visit traditional villages, monasteries, and local markets, interact with Gurung, Thakali, and Manangi communities, and experience Nepalese mountain hospitality firsthand.</p>', 11, 1, '2026-03-24 21:48:43', '2026-03-24 21:55:04'),
(774, 314, 'How fit do I need to be for this trek?', '<p>Moderate fitness is required. Daily treks of 5–8 hours, sometimes on steep or rocky terrain, demand cardiovascular endurance, leg strength, and stamina. Pre-trek conditioning, like hiking, running, or cycling, is recommended.</p>', 12, 1, '2026-03-24 21:48:43', '2026-03-24 21:55:04'),
(775, 315, 'How difficult is the Langtang Gosainkunda Trek?', '<p>The difficulty level of the Langtang Gosainkunda trek is moderate to challenging. The main difficulty comes from altitude and the Lauribina Pass crossing. However, with proper acclimatization and pacing, most trekkers can complete it successfully.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-24 22:31:16', '2026-03-24 22:35:14'),
(776, 315, 'What is the best time to do the Langtang Gosainkunda Trek?', '<p>The best time to do the Langtang Gosainkunda trek is in spring (March to May) and autumn (September to November). During these months, you get clear mountain views and stable weather conditions.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-24 22:31:16', '2026-03-24 22:35:14'),
(777, 315, 'Do I need a guide for this trek?', '<p>While it is possible to trek independently, I strongly recommend hiring a guide. The route after Gosainkunda can be less obvious, and a guide enhances safety, navigation, and cultural understanding.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-24 22:31:16', '2026-03-24 22:35:15'),
(778, 315, 'Is altitude sickness a concern?', '<p>Yes, especially after 3,000 meters. This itinerary includes acclimatization days to reduce risks. Staying hydrated and maintaining a steady pace helps significantly.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-24 22:31:16', '2026-03-24 22:35:15'),
(779, 315, 'What permits are required for the Langtang Gosainkunda trek?', '<p>You need a Langtang National Park Permit and a TIMS Card to walk inside the Langtang Gosainkunda. These are usually arranged by your trekking agency.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-24 22:31:16', '2026-03-24 22:35:15'),
(780, 315, 'How much should I budget per day?', '<p>On average, you should budget $30–$50 per day if trekking independently. This includes food, accommodation, and basic expenses.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-24 22:31:16', '2026-03-24 22:35:15'),
(781, 315, 'Is the trek suitable for beginners?', '<p>Yes, beginners with good physical fitness can complete this trek. Proper preparation and a well-paced itinerary make a big difference.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-24 22:31:16', '2026-03-24 22:35:15'),
(782, 316, 'Why shall I do the Manaslu Circuit Trek?', '<p>You should do the Manaslu Circuit Trek because Manaslu is one of the hidden trekking trails in Nepal, offering a chance to explore pristine Himalayan landscapes, high mountain passes, and remote villages away from crowded tourist routes. The trek combines adventure, culture, and stunning views of peaks like Manaslu, Himalchuli, and Ngadi Chuli, making it a once-in-a-lifetime experience for every trekker.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-27 01:16:26', '2026-03-27 01:17:45'),
(783, 316, 'Who can do the Manaslu Circuit Trek in 2026?', '<p>The Manaslu Circuit Trek is ideal for trekkers with moderate to good fitness levels who are comfortable with multi-day high-altitude trekking. It is suitable for both experienced trekkers and adventurous beginners who are willing to prepare physically, acclimatize properly, and travel in groups of at least two, as required by the restricted area regulations.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-27 01:16:26', '2026-03-27 01:17:45'),
(784, 316, 'Do I need special permits for the Manaslu Circuit Trek?', '<p>Yes, you need special permits because the Manaslu region is a restricted area in Nepal. You must obtain the Restricted Area Permit (RAP), Manaslu Conservation Area Permit (MCAP), and Annapurna Conservation Area Permit (ACAP) to legally enter the trail. These permits help preserve the fragile ecosystem and local culture of the region.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-27 01:16:26', '2026-03-27 01:17:45'),
(785, 316, 'What is the best time to do the Manaslu Circuit Trek?', '<p>The best time to trek the Manaslu Circuit is during autumn (September to November) and spring (March to May). During these seasons, the weather is stable, the skies are clear, and the mountain views are spectacular. Snowfall in winter can make high passes like Larkya La challenging, while monsoon rains from June to August make trails slippery and risky.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-27 01:16:26', '2026-03-27 01:17:45'),
(786, 316, 'How difficult is the Manaslu Circuit Trek?', '<p>The trek is moderate to challenging, mainly due to the high altitude and long trekking days. The crossing of Larkya La Pass (5,160 m) is the toughest part, requiring stamina and acclimatization. While the trek is demanding, proper physical preparation, trekking in groups, and rest days make it achievable for most healthy adventurers.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-27 01:16:26', '2026-03-27 01:17:45'),
(787, 316, 'What kind of villages and culture will I experience?', '<p>You will experience remote Tibetan-influenced villages such as Samagaun, Samdo, and Namrung, where locals practice Buddhist traditions, maintain monasteries, and celebrate festivals. The Nubri community welcomes trekkers warmly, offering a glimpse into traditional lifestyles, prayer ceremonies, and stone architecture that is unique to this high Himalayan region.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-27 01:16:26', '2026-03-27 01:17:45'),
(788, 316, 'What do I need to carry for the trek?', '<p>You should carry warm clothing, trekking boots, a sleeping bag, trekking poles, and layered outfits for variable temperatures. Other essentials include personal toiletries, sunscreen, a water bottle, and a basic first-aid kit. Most teahouses provide meals and hot drinks, but it’s good to have personal snacks for energy on long trekking days.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-27 01:16:26', '2026-03-27 01:17:45'),
(789, 316, 'Can I do the Manaslu Circuit Trek independently?', '<p>Independent trekking is possible, but it is highly recommended to hire a licensed guide and/or porter. Guides help with navigation, cultural understanding, and permit compliance, while porters make the trek more comfortable by carrying your luggage. The trek is in a restricted area, so traveling in at least two people or in a group is mandatory.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-27 01:16:26', '2026-03-27 01:17:45'),
(790, 316, 'How long is the Manaslu Circuit Trek?', '<p>The complete Manaslu Circuit Trek typically takes 14–18 days, including arrival in Kathmandu, acclimatization days, trekking through villages, crossing Larkya La Pass, and returning to the capital. The duration depends on your pace, rest days, and the chosen itinerary.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-27 01:16:26', '2026-03-27 01:17:45'),
(791, 316, 'What is included in a standard Manaslu Circuit Trek package?', '<p>A standard package usually includes RAP, MCAP, ACAP permits, a licensed guide, porter service, accommodation in teahouses, three meals per day, hot drinks, maps, WiFi where available, and emergency support. Items like international flights, travel insurance, personal gear, tips, and extra Kathmandu accommodation are generally excluded.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-27 01:16:26', '2026-03-27 01:17:46'),
(792, 317, 'Is the Kanchenjunga Circuit Trek difficult?', '<p>Yes, the Kanchenjunga Circuit Trek is considered challenging to strenuous. It involves long trekking days, remote trails, and high altitudes reaching up to 5,143 meters at Pangpema. Unlike popular routes, facilities are basic, so you need good physical fitness and prior trekking experience.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-03-27 02:06:20', '2026-03-27 02:07:40'),
(793, 317, 'How many days do you need for the Kanchenjunga Circuit Trek?', '<p>You will need 20 to 26 days to complete the full Kanchenjunga circuit. This duration includes proper acclimatization, travel time from Kathmandu, and visits to both North and South Base Camps.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-03-27 02:06:20', '2026-03-27 02:07:40'),
(794, 317, 'Do I need a permit for the Kanchenjunga Trek?', '<p>Yes, you need special permits because it is a restricted area. You must have a Kanchenjunga Conservation Area Permit (KCAP) and a Restricted Area Permit (RAP). Solo trekking is not allowed—you must trek with a licensed guide and at least one other person.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-03-27 02:06:20', '2026-03-27 02:07:40'),
(795, 317, 'What is the best time to do the Kanchenjunga Circuit Trek?', '<p>The best time to do the Kanchenjunga circuit trek is during spring (March to May) and autumn (September to November). These seasons offer clear mountain views, stable weather, and the best trekking conditions around Mount Kanchenjunga.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-03-27 02:06:20', '2026-03-27 02:07:40'),
(796, 317, 'What is the highest point of the Kanchenjunga Circuit Trek?', '<p>The highest point on the Kanchenjunga circuit trek is Pangpema (North Base Camp) at 5,143 meters. It offers the closest and most spectacular views of Mount Kanchenjunga.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-03-27 02:06:20', '2026-03-27 02:07:40'),
(797, 317, 'Can beginners do the Kanchenjunga Circuit Trek?', '<p>This Kanchenjunga circuit trek is not recommended for beginners. Due to its remoteness, high altitude, and long duration, it is better suited for experienced trekkers who have already completed multi-day Himalayan treks.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-03-27 02:06:20', '2026-03-27 02:07:40'),
(798, 317, 'Is there internet or Wi-Fi on the Kanchenjunga Trek?', '<p>Yes, there is Internet access on the Kanchenjunga trek, but it is very limited and unreliable. Some lower villages may offer basic Wi-Fi, but as you go higher, connectivity becomes almost non-existent. It’s best to prepare for a complete digital detox.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-03-27 02:06:20', '2026-03-27 02:07:41'),
(799, 317, 'What kind of accommodation is available?', '<p>Accommodation is mainly in basic teahouses. Rooms are simple, usually twin-sharing, with shared bathrooms. Facilities become more limited as you go higher into remote areas.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-03-27 02:06:20', '2026-03-27 02:07:41'),
(800, 317, 'What food is available during the trek?', '<p>You’ll find simple but nutritious meals like dal bhat, noodles, soups, potatoes, Tibetan bread, and momos. Food options become limited at higher altitudes, but meals are filling and designed for trekkers.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-03-27 02:06:20', '2026-03-27 02:07:41'),
(801, 317, 'Is travel insurance required?', '<p>Yes, travel insurance is mandatory. It should cover high-altitude trekking (above 5,000 meters) and emergency helicopter evacuation, especially in remote areas like the Kanchenjunga region.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-03-27 02:06:20', '2026-03-27 02:07:41'),
(802, 317, 'How much does the Kanchenjunga Circuit Trek cost?', '<p>The Kanchenjunga circuit cost generally ranges from USD 1,800 to USD 3,500 per person, depending on services, group size, and itinerary. The price includes permits, guide, accommodation, meals, and transportation from Kathmandu.</p>', 11, 1, '2026-03-27 02:06:20', '2026-03-27 02:07:41'),
(803, 317, 'Is the Kanchenjunga Trek crowded?', '<p>No, this is one of the least crowded treks in Nepal. If you want solitude and untouched nature, this trek around Mount Kanchenjunga is perfect.</p>', 12, 1, '2026-03-27 02:06:20', '2026-03-27 02:07:41'),
(804, 317, 'How do I get to the Kanchenjunga trek starting point?', '<p>You typically fly from Kathmandu to Bhadrapur and then take a long drive to Taplejung, where the trek begins.</p>', 13, 1, '2026-03-27 02:06:20', '2026-03-27 02:07:41'),
(805, 317, 'What makes the Kanchenjunga Circuit Trek special?', '<p>Its remoteness, untouched trails, diverse landscapes, and authentic culture make it unique. Trekking around Mount Kanchenjunga offers a rare opportunity to experience the Himalayas in their purest form.</p>', 14, 1, '2026-03-27 02:06:20', '2026-03-27 02:07:41'),
(806, 318, 'What is Langshisha Ri Peak Climbing?', '<p>Langshisha Ri Peak Climbing is a technically demanding Himalayan adventure in Nepal that takes you to the summit of a 6,427 m alpine peak. This climb involves ice, snow, and glacier travel, making it ideal for mountaineers seeking a real Himalayan challenge beyond regular trekking peaks.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-04-01 02:09:12', '2026-04-01 02:17:26'),
(807, 318, 'Where is Langshisha Ri located?', '<p>Langshisha Ri is located in the Langtang region of Nepal, near Kyanjin Gompa. This area is part of the Langtang National Park, offering pristine landscapes, glaciers, and panoramic views of iconic peaks like Langtang Lirung, Shishapangma, Dorje Lakpa, and the Ganesh Himal range.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-04-01 02:09:12', '2026-04-01 02:17:26'),
(808, 318, 'How difficult is Langshisha Ri Peak Climbing?', '<p>Langshisha Ri Peak Climbing is considered a technically challenging alpine climb. It involves steep snow slopes, ice, and glacier travel, requiring proper mountaineering skills and experience. Climbers need to be physically fit and prepared for high-altitude conditions.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-04-01 02:09:12', '2026-04-01 02:17:26'),
(809, 318, 'Do I need previous mountaineering experience to climb Langshisha Ri?', '<p>While some trekking experience is helpful, previous mountaineering experience is recommended for Langshisha Ri Peak Climbing. The climb includes technical sections on ice and snow where using crampons, ice axes, and ropes is essential. Proper guidance from experienced Sherpa climbers makes it achievable for motivated climbers.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-04-01 02:09:12', '2026-04-01 02:17:26'),
(810, 318, 'What is the best time to climb Langshisha Ri Peak?', '<p>The best time for Langshisha Ri Peak Climbing is during the spring (March to May) and autumn (September to November) seasons. These months offer clear weather, stable snow conditions, and spectacular mountain views, increasing your chances for a successful summit.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-04-01 02:09:12', '2026-04-01 02:17:26'),
(811, 318, 'How long does the Langshisha Ri expedition take?', '<p>The Langshisha Ri Peak Climbing expedition typically takes 20 days, including the trek to Kyanjin Gompa, acclimatization, ascent, and return. This allows proper altitude adjustment and preparation for technical climbing.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-04-01 02:09:12', '2026-04-01 02:17:26'),
(812, 318, 'What permits are required for Langshisha Ri Peak Climbing?', '<p>For Langshisha Ri Peak Climbing, climbers need the Langtang National Park Permit, TIMS Permit, and the Langshisha Ri Peak Permit. Summit 8000 handles all necessary permits as part of the expedition package.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-04-01 02:09:12', '2026-04-01 02:17:26'),
(813, 318, 'What is included in the Langshisha Ri climbing package?', '<p>The Langshisha Ri climbing package includes lodge accommodations up to Kyanjin Gompa, tented camps during the climb, transport from Kathmandu to Syabrubesi and back, certified Sherpa guides, porters, cooks, climbing and kitchen equipment, meals during trek and climb, and staff wages and insurance.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-04-01 02:09:12', '2026-04-01 02:17:26'),
(814, 318, 'What kind of training or fitness is needed for Langshisha Ri Peak Climbing?', '<p>For Langshisha Ri Peak Climbing, climbers need good physical fitness, stamina, and experience with trekking at high altitudes. Regular cardio, strength training, and practice with hiking or climbing with a backpack are recommended before the expedition.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-04-01 02:09:12', '2026-04-01 02:17:26'),
(815, 318, 'How is the accommodation during Langshisha Ri Peak Climbing?', '<p>During Langshisha Ri Peak Climbing, accommodation is in guesthouses or lodges up to Kyanjin Gompa. Beyond that, during the climb, climbers stay in tented camps at Langshisha Kharka, Base Camp, and High Camp, providing a safe and comfortable setup in alpine conditions.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-04-01 02:09:12', '2026-04-01 02:17:26'),
(816, 318, 'What kind of food is available during the Langshisha Ri expedition?', '<p>During Langshisha Ri Peak Climbing, meals include Nepali, Indian, Chinese, Italian, and European dishes served three times a day. One main course is provided per meal, prepared by the expedition kitchen crew to ensure balanced nutrition for climbers.</p>', 11, 1, '2026-04-01 02:09:12', '2026-04-01 02:17:26'),
(817, 318, 'Is it safe to climb Langshisha Ri Peak?', '<p>Langshisha Ri Peak Climbing is safe when proper preparation, acclimatization, and guidance from experienced Sherpa guides are followed. Summit 8000 ensures safety measures, equipment, and staff support throughout the expedition to minimize risks.</p>', 12, 1, '2026-04-01 02:09:12', '2026-04-01 02:17:26'),
(818, 318, 'How crowded is Langshisha Ri Peak?', '<p>Langshisha Ri Peak is off the beaten path, much less crowded than Everest or Annapurna expeditions. Climbers enjoy solitude, pristine landscapes, and a more authentic Himalayan climbing experience.</p>', 13, 1, '2026-04-01 02:09:12', '2026-04-01 02:17:26'),
(819, 318, 'How successful are climbers on Langshisha Ri Peak?', '<p>Climbers have a high success rate on Langshisha Ri Peak due to defined routes, proper acclimatization, and guidance by experienced Sherpa teams. Careful preparation and gradual ascent increase the likelihood of a safe and rewarding summit.</p>', 14, 1, '2026-04-01 02:09:12', '2026-04-01 02:17:26'),
(820, 319, 'What is Larke Peak Climbing in Nepal?', '<p>Larke Peak Climbing is an adventurous Himalayan journey that combines trekking in the remote Manaslu Region with a non-technical peak ascent above 5,000 meters. It is ideal for trekkers who want to step into mountaineering while enjoying stunning landscapes and rich culture.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-04-01 02:56:15', '2026-04-01 02:57:00'),
(821, 319, 'Where is Larke Peak located?', '<p>Larke Peak lies near the famous Larkya La Pass along the Manaslu Circuit Trek in northern Nepal, close to the border with Tibet.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-04-01 02:56:15', '2026-04-01 02:57:00'),
(822, 319, 'How difficult is Larke Peak Climbing?', '<p>Larke Peak Climbing is considered moderately challenging. While it does not require advanced technical climbing skills, it demands good physical fitness, stamina, and the ability to trek and climb at high altitudes.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-04-01 02:56:15', '2026-04-01 02:57:00'),
(823, 319, 'What is the maximum altitude of the expedition?', '<p>The highest point of the trip is Larke Peak Base Camp at around 5,135 meters, along with crossing Larkya La Pass (5,160 m). The summit attempt may reach slightly higher depending on the climbing route.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-04-01 02:56:15', '2026-04-01 02:57:00'),
(824, 319, 'Do I need prior climbing experience?', '<p>No, prior technical climbing experience is not mandatory. However, previous trekking experience at high altitude is highly recommended. Basic training is provided before the summit attempt.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-04-01 02:56:15', '2026-04-01 02:57:00'),
(825, 319, 'When is the best time for Larke Peak Climbing?', '<p>The best seasons are spring (March to May) and autumn (September to November). During these months, the weather is stable, and mountain views including Mount Manaslu, are at their best.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-04-01 02:56:15', '2026-04-01 02:57:00'),
(826, 319, 'Will I cross Larkya La Pass during the climb?', '<p>Yes, crossing Larkya La Pass is a major highlight of the expedition. It offers breathtaking panoramic views and marks a key achievement of the journey.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-04-01 02:56:15', '2026-04-01 02:57:00'),
(827, 319, 'What type of accommodation can I expect?', '<p>You will stay in teahouses/lodges during the trek and in tents during the climbing phase at higher altitudes. Accommodation is basic but comfortable considering the remote location.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-04-01 02:56:15', '2026-04-01 02:57:00'),
(828, 319, 'What kind of food is available during the trek?', '<p>Teahouses offer a variety of meals including Nepali, Tibetan, and basic international dishes such as dal bhat, noodles, soups, and tea. Meals are nutritious and designed to support high-altitude trekking.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-04-01 02:56:15', '2026-04-01 02:57:00'),
(829, 319, 'Is altitude sickness a concern on this trip?', '<p>Yes, altitude sickness can be a risk as you go above 5,000 meters. The itinerary includes proper acclimatization days in places like Samagaun and Samdo to help your body adjust safely.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-04-01 02:56:15', '2026-04-01 02:57:00'),
(830, 319, 'Do I need a special permit for this trek?', '<p>Yes, since the Manaslu Region is a restricted area, you need special permits including the Manaslu Restricted Area Permit and Manaslu Conservation Area Project (MCAP) permit.</p>', 11, 1, '2026-04-01 02:56:15', '2026-04-01 02:57:00'),
(831, 319, 'How long is the Larke Peak Climbing itinerary?', '<p>The standard itinerary takes around 18–20 days, depending on acclimatization, climbing days, and weather conditions.</p>', 12, 1, '2026-04-01 02:56:15', '2026-04-01 02:57:00'),
(832, 319, 'Is travel insurance necessary?', '<p>Yes, travel insurance is mandatory. It must cover high-altitude trekking and emergency helicopter evacuation in Nepal.</p>', 13, 1, '2026-04-01 02:56:15', '2026-04-01 02:57:00'),
(833, 319, 'What makes Larke Peak Climbing unique?', '<p>It offers a perfect mix of trekking and climbing in a less crowded region, along with authentic Himalayan culture and stunning views of peaks like Mount Manaslu.</p>', 14, 1, '2026-04-01 02:56:15', '2026-04-01 02:57:00'),
(834, 319, 'Can the itinerary change during the trip?', '<p>Yes, the itinerary may change due to weather, health conditions, or other unforeseen circumstances to ensure safety and a successful experience.</p>', 15, 1, '2026-04-01 02:56:15', '2026-04-01 02:57:00'),
(835, 320, 'What is the Nirekha Peak itinerary?', '<p>The Nirekha Peak itinerary is a 22-day Himalayan expedition starting with arrival in Kathmandu, followed by a scenic flight to Lukla, trekking through Namche Bazaar, Thame, Lungdeng, and Gokyo, reaching Nirekha Base Camp, and then ascending the peak. The summit attempt is followed by descent via Cho-La Pass and a return to Kathmandu. The itinerary includes acclimatization days, rest days, and optional treks around Gokyo Lake to ensure a safe and enjoyable climb.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-04-02 01:55:30', '2026-04-02 01:58:51'),
(836, 320, 'How much does Nirekha Peak climbing cost?', '<p>The cost of Nirekha Peak climbing typically ranges from USD 4,500 to 5,500 per person. This cost generally includes permits, accommodation in Kathmandu and teahouses/lodges, meals during the trek, experienced guides and Sherpa support, domestic flights to Lukla, and trekking/climbing support such as rope fixing and camp setup. Costs usually exclude international flights, personal gear, insurance, and optional expenses.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-04-02 01:55:30', '2026-04-02 01:58:51'),
(837, 320, 'How difficult is Nirekha Peak climbing?', '<p>Nirekha Peak climbing is considered moderately technical. It involves glacier travel, rope-assisted sections, and steep snow slopes. While it is easier than higher Himalayan summits, climbers should have prior trekking experience and basic mountaineering skills. Physical fitness, proper acclimatization, and guidance from experienced Sherpas are essential to safely complete the climb.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-04-02 01:55:30', '2026-04-02 01:58:51'),
(838, 320, 'Do I need experience for Nirekha Peak?', '<p>Yes, you do need experience for Nirekha Peak. While it is classified as a “trekking peak,” climbers should have previous trekking experience at high altitude and basic skills in ice climbing, using crampons, and rope techniques. Beginners with no high-altitude experience are advised to gain practice on smaller peaks before attempting Nirekha.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-04-02 01:55:30', '2026-04-02 01:58:51'),
(839, 320, 'How long does the Nirekha Peak climb take?', '<p>The Nirekha Peak climb typically takes 22 days, including trekking to base camp, acclimatization at higher camps, and the summit attempt. The expedition duration may vary depending on weather conditions, group pace, and rest days. This timeline ensures proper acclimatization and safety throughout the climb.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-04-02 01:55:30', '2026-04-02 01:58:51'),
(840, 320, 'What is the height of Nirekha Peak?', '<p>The height of Nirekha Peak is 6,159 meters (20,202 feet). It offers climbers spectacular panoramic views of the Himalayas, including Everest, Lhotse, Cho Oyu, and Makalu, without the extreme technical challenges of higher 7,000+ meter peaks.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-04-02 01:55:30', '2026-04-02 01:58:51'),
(841, 320, 'When is the best time to climb Nirekha Peak?', '<p>The best time to climb Nirekha Peak is during the spring (March to May) and autumn (September to November) seasons. Spring offers moderate temperatures, clear skies, and blooming rhododendrons, while autumn provides stable weather, crisp air, and excellent visibility of the Himalayan range.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-04-02 01:55:30', '2026-04-02 01:58:51'),
(842, 320, 'Is Nirekha Peak technical?', '<p>Yes, Nirekha Peak is moderately technical. The climb requires navigating snow and ice slopes, glaciers, and rope-fixed sections. While it is achievable for climbers with prior trekking peak experience, using an experienced guide is highly recommended for safety and guidance on technical sections.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-04-02 01:55:30', '2026-04-02 01:58:51'),
(843, 320, 'What does the Nirekha Peak cost include and exclude?', '<p>The Nirekha Peak cost includes permits, accommodation, meals during the trek, guides and Sherpa support, domestic flights, camp setup, and emergency support. The cost excludes international airfare, personal climbing gear, travel insurance, visa fees, personal expenses, tips for staff, and optional excursions. Most climbers should budget an extra USD 200–400 for personal expenses and gear rental.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-04-02 01:55:30', '2026-04-02 01:58:51'),
(844, 321, 'Is Yubra Peak dangerous for climbing?', '<p>Yubra Peak is considered safe for beginners, with a non-technical route. The main challenges are high altitude, cold weather, and snow-covered trails, but with proper acclimatization, professional guides, and reliable gear, the climb is manageable. Summit 8000 ensures your safety with trained guides, rescue plans, and step-by-step climbing instructions, making it an adventurous yet secure experience.</p>', 1, 1, '2026-04-02 03:18:48', '2026-04-02 03:27:00'),
(845, 321, 'Who should do the Yubra Peak expedition?', '<p>This expedition is perfect for trekkers with good fitness who want to experience high-altitude Himalayan mountaineering for the first time. Adventure lovers who seek a remote and authentic climbing experience, away from crowded trails, will find Yubra Peak ideal. It’s also excellent for those who want to learn basic climbing skills while enjoying breathtaking alpine landscapes.</p>', 2, 1, '2026-04-02 03:18:48', '2026-04-02 03:27:00'),
(846, 321, 'What is the difficulty and technical challenge of Yubra Himal?', '<p>Yubra Himal is a moderately difficult peak. It does not require advanced climbing skills, but basic knowledge of crampons, ropes, and ice axes is recommended, especially near the summit. The biggest challenge is altitude, as climbers ascend above 6,000 meters. The trek involves steep trails, glaciers, and snowy terrain, but with expert Summit 8000 guides, it becomes a safe and highly rewarding climb.</p>', 3, 1, '2026-04-02 03:18:48', '2026-04-02 03:27:00'),
(847, 321, 'What is the best time to climb Yubra Peak?', '<p>The best time is during spring (March–May) and autumn (September–November). During these months, the weather is stable, skies are clear, and the mountain views are breathtaking. Avoid monsoon months as trails can be slippery, and winter brings extreme cold that makes climbing more challenging.</p>', 4, 1, '2026-04-02 03:18:48', '2026-04-02 03:27:00'),
(848, 321, 'How do I get to the starting point of the trek?', '<p>From Kathmandu, Summit 8000 arranges a private vehicle transfer to Syabrubesi, the gateway to the Langtang region. The drive takes 7–8 hours along scenic Himalayan routes, offering views of rivers, forests, and foothills. This ensures a comfortable and stress-free start to your expedition.</p>', 5, 1, '2026-04-02 03:18:48', '2026-04-02 03:27:00'),
(849, 321, 'Can beginners attempt Yubra Peak?', '<p>Yes. Yubra Peak is suitable for beginners with good fitness, as the climb is non-technical. Summit 8000 guides provide training in mountaineering techniques, including ice axe and crampon use, making it safe for first-time climbers to experience the remote and authentic Himalayas.</p>', 6, 1, '2026-04-02 03:18:48', '2026-04-02 03:27:00'),
(850, 321, 'What type of accommodation is provided?', '<p>During the trek, you stay in comfortable teahouses at lower elevations and tents at Base and High Camp. In Kathmandu, you enjoy a 4-star hotel with all modern facilities. Meals, tea, and coffee are included throughout, ensuring a pleasant and hassle-free experience.</p>', 7, 1, '2026-04-02 03:18:48', '2026-04-02 03:27:00'),
(851, 321, 'What gear do I need for Yubra Peak?', '<p>Essential gear includes warm clothing, down jacket, trekking boots, gloves, hats, and sunglasses. Summit 8000 provides camping equipment, and climbing gear like ropes, harnesses, crampons, and ice axes can be rented or provided by the team. Proper gear ensures safety, comfort, and success on the climb.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-04-02 03:18:48', '2026-04-02 03:27:00'),
(852, 321, 'How fit do I need to be?', '<p>You should be in good physical condition, capable of trekking 5–7 hours a day on uneven terrain. Previous trekking experience is helpful but not required. With proper preparation and guidance, most climbers can successfully reach the summit while enjoying the breathtaking views along the way.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-04-02 03:18:48', '2026-04-02 03:27:00'),
(853, 321, 'What makes Yubra Peak unique?', '<p>Yubra Peak is a remote, less-crowded Himalayan climb offering authentic cultural encounters, scenic trekking trails, and breathtaking summit views. Unlike more popular peaks, it allows climbers to experience the raw beauty of the Himalayas with a sense of solitude, making it a truly unforgettable adventure.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-04-02 03:18:48', '2026-04-02 03:27:00'),
(854, 286, 'How many camps does Ama Dablam have?', '<p>Ama Dablam has three high camps above base camp. Camp I is at 5,800m, Camp II at 6,000m, and Camp III at 6,400m. Climbers typically rotate between these camps multiple times before their summit push to acclimatize properly.</p>', 16, 1, '2026-04-07 13:25:40', '2026-04-07 13:30:21'),
(855, 286, 'What is the Yellow Tower on Ama Dablam?', '<p>The Yellow Tower is the most technically demanding section of the Ama Dablam Southwest Ridge route. Located above Camp III at approximately 6,600m, it is a steep rock band requiring UIAA Grade IV climbing on fixed ropes. Most guided expeditions use pre-fixed ropes through this section installed by lead Sherpa teams at the start of each season.</p>', 17, 1, '2026-04-07 13:25:40', '2026-04-07 13:30:21'),
(856, 286, 'What is the Puja ceremony on Ama Dablam?', '<p>The Puja ceremony is a Buddhist blessing ritual performed at Ama Dablam base camp before every expedition begins. Led by a Lama, the ceremony asks the mountain deities for safe passage and permission to climb. All Sherpa guides consider it mandatory regardless of client preference and it typically takes place on Day 10 of the itinerary at base camp.</p>', 18, 1, '2026-04-07 13:25:40', '2026-04-07 13:30:21'),
(857, 282, 'Is Mount Everest an expedition?', '<p>Yes, Mount Everest is a high-altitude expedition in Nepal that requires technical climbing, guides, permits, and acclimatization.</p>', 8, 1, '2026-04-08 14:33:47', '2026-04-08 14:43:26'),
(858, 282, 'Who climbed Everest 7 times?', '<p>Multiple climbers have summited 7+ times, but one notable climber is Apa Sherpa, who held the record for the most Everest summits for many years.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-04-08 14:33:47', '2026-04-08 14:43:26'),
(859, 282, 'How many Everest expeditions are there a year?', '<p>There are On average, about 40–50 commercial expeditions attempt to climb Everest each spring, and 10–20 in autumn, though numbers vary by season and conditions.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-04-08 14:33:47', '2026-04-08 14:43:26'),
(860, 282, 'Why does it cost $40,000+ to climb Mount Everest?', '<p>The reason why climbers need more than 40,000 USD to climb Mount Everest is because of the Nepal government permit costs, guides, Sherpa support, oxygen, gear, food, logistics, insurance, and contingency plans for emergencies.</p>', 11, 1, '2026-04-08 14:33:47', '2026-04-08 14:43:26'),
(861, 282, 'What is the biggest killer on Everest?', '<p>The biggest killer on Everest is Altitude-related illnesses (HAPE, HACE), falls, avalanches, and many more, due to which the success rate of this peak is around 60 to 70% only.</p>', 12, 1, '2026-04-08 14:33:47', '2026-04-08 14:43:26'),
(862, 282, 'Why can\'t you climb Mount Everest after 2pm?', '<p>You can’t climb Mount Everest after 2 PM because of the afternoon storms, and ensure enough daylight for descent.</p>', 13, 1, '2026-04-08 14:33:47', '2026-04-08 14:43:26'),
(863, 282, 'How many climbers die on Everest each year?', '<p>Deaths vary, but roughly 5–10 climbers die annually on Everest each year, and some years are higher depending on weather and crowding.</p>', 14, 1, '2026-04-08 14:33:47', '2026-04-08 14:43:26'),
(864, 282, 'What is the oldest dead body on Everest?', '<p>The oldest dead body on Everest is Green Boots, which is believed to have died in the early 1990s.</p>', 15, 1, '2026-04-08 14:33:47', '2026-04-08 14:43:26'),
(865, 282, 'How cold is it on Mount Everest?', '<p>The temperature on Mount Everest can drop below −40°C at the summit during winter, with wind chills making it feel colder.</p>', 16, 1, '2026-04-08 14:33:47', '2026-04-08 14:43:26'),
(866, 282, 'Why can\'t you climb Everest in the summer?', '<p>You cannot climb Mount Everest in the summer because it is monsoon season, bringing heavy snow, avalanches, poor visibility, and unstable conditions, making climbing extremely dangerous.</p>', 17, 1, '2026-04-08 14:33:47', '2026-04-08 14:43:26'),
(867, 282, 'How long do bodies last on Everest?', '<p>The dead bodies on Everest can last forever due to the freezing temperatures and low oxygen, which slows down the process of decomposing.</p>', 18, 1, '2026-04-08 14:33:47', '2026-04-08 14:43:26'),
(868, 282, 'What is banned on Mount Everest during climbing?', '<p>There are many things that are banned on Mount Everest during climbing, such as littering, leaving human waste, and using non-permitted routes or unlicensed guides. Climbers are expected to follow strict environmental and safety regulations.</p>', 19, 1, '2026-04-08 14:33:47', '2026-04-08 14:43:26'),
(869, 282, 'Is K2 colder than Everest?', '<p>Yes, K2 is colder than Everest because it lies in a higher latitude and steeper, more exposed terrain.</p>', 20, 1, '2026-04-08 14:33:47', '2026-04-08 14:43:26'),
(870, 282, 'What animals live on Mount Everest?', '<p>The Everest region is the coldest, due to which some of the rare animals live, such as the snow leopards, Himalayan tahr, yaks, birds like choughs, and Himalayan snowcock at lower altitudes.</p>', 21, 1, '2026-04-08 14:33:47', '2026-04-08 14:43:26'),
(871, 282, 'Can birds fly over Mount Everest?', '<p>Yes, some birds, such as the bar-headed goose, can fly over the summit at extreme altitudes.</p>', 22, 1, '2026-04-08 14:33:47', '2026-04-08 14:43:26'),
(872, 282, 'Why are dead bodies not removed from Everest?', '<p>The dead bodies are not removed from Everest because of Harsh conditions, high altitude, technical difficulty, and cost, which make body recovery extremely dangerous; many remain as markers of the mountain’s risks.</p>', 23, 1, '2026-04-08 14:33:47', '2026-04-08 14:43:26'),
(873, 282, 'Who was the most famous dead body on Everest?', '<p>The famous dead body on Everest was Green Boots, who is the most well-known, serving as a landmark in the North-East ridge route.</p>', 24, 1, '2026-04-08 14:33:47', '2026-04-08 14:43:26'),
(874, 282, 'What is the most common death on Everest?', '<p>The most common deaths on Everest is Falls, avalanches, and altitude sickness (HAPE/HACE).</p>', 25, 1, '2026-04-08 14:33:47', '2026-04-08 14:43:26'),
(875, 283, 'How to prevent altitude sickness on Annapurna?', '<p>Altitude sickness, or AMS, is common above 3,000 meters. On Annapurna, prevention is all about gradual acclimatization, hydration, and listening to your body. Climbers follow a rotation schedule: ascending to higher camps, then returning to base camp to let the body adjust. Avoid alcohol, get plenty of rest, and report any symptoms immediately. Our Sherpa guides monitor each climber carefully to reduce risks.</p>', 9, 1, '2026-04-09 14:38:39', '2026-04-09 14:42:26'),
(876, 283, 'What are the symptoms of HAPE and HACE at high altitude?', '<p>HAPE (High-Altitude Pulmonary Edema) and HACE (High-Altitude Cerebral Edema) are life-threatening conditions. HAPE symptoms include extreme breathlessness, persistent cough, and fatigue. HACE symptoms include confusion, loss of coordination, severe headache, and nausea. Immediate descent and medical attention are critical; our team carries emergency oxygen and Gamow bags for these situations.</p>', 10, 1, '2026-04-09 14:38:39', '2026-04-09 14:42:26'),
(877, 283, 'Can anyone climb Annapurna, or is fitness level important?', '<p>Fitness is crucial. Annapurna is technically challenging, with steep ice, crevasses, and avalanche-prone slopes. Climbers must be physically strong, mentally resilient, and experienced in high-altitude conditions. Beginners should train extensively and climb smaller peaks first. Summit 8000 ensures climbers are well-prepared before attempting the summit.</p>', 11, 1, '2026-04-09 14:38:39', '2026-04-09 14:42:26'),
(878, 283, 'How long is the Annapurna expedition from start to finish?', '<p>Our Annapurna expedition is 40 days from arrival in Kathmandu to departure. This includes acclimatization, rotations through the camps, summit attempt, and return. The extended schedule maximizes safety and increases summit success.</p>', 12, 1, '2026-04-09 14:38:39', '2026-04-09 14:42:26'),
(879, 283, 'What is the best season to climb Annapurna?', '<p>The ideal climbing seasons to Annapurna are spring (March–May) and autumn (September–November). The weather is most stable, avalanche risks are lower, and visibility is better for summit attempts. Monsoon and winter climbs are possible but extremely dangerous.</p>', 13, 1, '2026-04-09 14:38:39', '2026-04-09 14:42:26'),
(880, 283, 'How many camps are there on the standard route?', '<p>The standard North Face / Northwest Ridge route has four high camps above base camp: </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Camp I – technical glacier sections </li>\r\n<li>Camp II – steep ice and avalanche-prone zones </li>\r\n<li>Camp III – high-altitude acclimatization camp </li>\r\n<li>Camp IV – final push to the summit</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Base Camp → Camp I → Camp II → Camp III → Camp IV → Summit.</p>', 14, 1, '2026-04-09 14:38:39', '2026-04-09 14:42:26'),
(881, 283, 'Can I climb Annapurna without Sherpa guides?', '<p>Technically, yes, you can climb Annapurna without Sherpa guides, but not recommended. Annapurna is extremely dangerous with unpredictable avalanches and weather. Our Sherpa guides provide route expertise, fixed rope systems, emergency response, and acclimatization management, which dramatically increase safety and chances of success.</p>', 15, 1, '2026-04-09 14:38:39', '2026-04-09 14:42:26'),
(882, 283, 'What permits are required for Annapurna?', '<p>Climbing permits required for Annapurna are:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Expedition Royalty Permit (DoT)</li>\r\n<li>Annapurna Conservation Area Permit (ACAP)</li>\r\n<li>Liaison Officer Assgnment (DoT)</li>\r\n<li>Garbage Deposit Fee</li>\r\n<li>Climber’s Insurance (verified by DoT)</li>\r\n</ul>', 14, 1, '2026-04-09 14:38:39', '2026-04-09 14:42:26'),
(883, 283, 'How much does it cost to climb Annapurna with Summit 8000?', '<p>To climb Annapurna with a summit 8000, our expedition is priced at $20,000 USD per person, including flights, heli transfer, base camp tents, Sherpa guides, meals, satellite phone, and medical support. Group size affects per-person cost: solo climbers pay $28,000–35,000, small groups $22,000–26,000, standard group $20,000.</p>', 15, 1, '2026-04-09 14:38:39', '2026-04-09 14:42:26'),
(884, 283, 'Is insurance mandatory for Annapurna expeditions?', '<p>Yes, personal high-altitude rescue and medical insurance is mandatory for the Annapurna expedition and verified by Nepal’s Department of Tourism. Coverage must include helicopter evacuation, treatment at altitude, and repatriation. Summit 8000 recommends purchasing before arrival.</p>', 16, 1, '2026-04-09 14:38:39', '2026-04-09 14:42:26'),
(885, 283, 'Do I need prior climbing experience for Annapurna?', '<p>Yes, prior experience is strongly recommended for Annapurna. Climbers should have technical ice and rock climbing skills, crampon and ice-axe experience, and high-altitude trekking experience. Annapurna is not a beginner-friendly peak.</p>', 17, 1, '2026-04-09 14:38:39', '2026-04-09 14:42:26'),
(886, 283, 'What is the difference between climbing Annapurna I vs trekking ABC?', '<p><strong>Trekking ABC (Annapurna Base Camp) – </strong>moderate trekking up to 4,130 m, no technical climbing.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Climbing Annapurna I –</strong> a high-altitude technical expedition up to 8,091 m, requires mountaineering skills, acclimatization rotations, and Sherpa support. The risks and commitment are significantly higher.</p>', 18, 1, '2026-04-09 14:38:39', '2026-04-09 14:42:26'),
(887, 283, 'How much oxygen will I need during the summit?', '<p>Supplemental oxygen is mandatory above Camp IV (~7,400 m). Our system is carefully rationed to last for the summit push and descent to Camp IV. The exact amount depends on the climber’s fitness and the duration of summit window, and Sherpas monitor oxygen usage closely.</p>', 19, 1, '2026-04-09 14:38:39', '2026-04-09 14:42:26'),
(888, 283, 'What is the fatality rate of Annapurna compared to Everest or K2?', '<ul>\r\n<li>Annapurna I: 32%</li>\r\n<li>K2: 23%</li>\r\n<li>Everest: 1%</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Annapurna’s high fatality is due to unpredictable weather, avalanches, and technical terrain.</p>', 20, 1, '2026-04-09 14:38:39', '2026-04-09 14:42:26'),
(889, 283, 'How do Sherpas ensure safety during the expedition?', '<p>Sherpas ensure safety during expedition by:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Route fixing and monitoring avalanche zones</li>\r\n<li>Managing acclimatization rotations</li>\r\n<li>Real-time weather assessment</li>\r\n<li>Carrying emergency oxygen and medical kits</li>\r\n<li>Coordinating rescue or helicopter evacuation if needed Experience and intuition gained over decades make</li>\r\n<li>Sherpas indispensable on Annapurna.</li>\r\n</ul>', 21, 1, '2026-04-09 14:38:39', '2026-04-09 14:42:26'),
(890, 283, 'Can Annapurna be climbed during the monsoon season?', '<p>Technically possible to climb Annapurna in the monsoon season, but extremely dangerous. Heavy rainfall, avalanches, and poor visibility make monsoon climbs high-risk. We strongly advise spring or autumn for safe and successful expeditions.</p>', 22, 1, '2026-04-09 14:38:39', '2026-04-09 14:42:26'),
(891, 283, 'What is the Puja ceremony before starting the climb?', '<p>Before the climb, climbers perform a Puja ceremony at base camp, asking the goddess Annapurna for a safe ascent. Local monks bless climbers, offering spiritual protection and respect for the sacred mountain. It’s a traditional ritual that is an integral part of Himalayan climbing culture.</p>', 23, 1, '2026-04-09 14:38:39', '2026-04-09 14:42:26'),
(892, 283, 'What local cultures or ethnic groups will I encounter?', '<p>You will meet Gurung, Magar, Thakali, and Tibetan-influenced mountain communities. They are known for warm hospitality, traditional lifestyles, and connection with the mountains. Interactions include visiting villages, tasting local foods, and learning about customs and festivals.</p>', 24, 1, '2026-04-09 14:38:39', '2026-04-09 14:42:26'),
(893, 283, 'Are there stories or legends about Annapurna that climbers should know?', '<p>Annapurna is considered a sacred deity. Locals believe the mountain protects the region and controls the harvest. The French expedition in 1950, led by Maurice Herzog, first summited Annapurna I, a legendary feat that inspired generations of climbers. Many Sherpa stories recount miraculous rescues and close calls that highlight the mountain’s unpredictability.</p>', 25, 1, '2026-04-09 14:38:39', '2026-04-09 14:42:26');
